string.text: Jon Rojs, viadomy jak Bronzavy. Jon, - Šlachcič Runnaha Kamienia i hłava starejšaj haliny Doma Rojsaŭ. Šlachcič Rojs viadomy turnirny rycar, jaki ŭbrany ŭ bronzavuju braniu padčas spabornictvaŭ. Ličycca, što hetaj brani tysiačahodździ, a napisanyja na joj runy byccam mohuć uścierahčy ichniaha ułaśnika ad biady.
Lady Royce of Runestone, wife of Lord Yohn Royce.

Lord Nestor Royce is the senior member of a cadet branch of House Royce and Keeper of the Gates of the Moon. He is the cousin of Lord Yohn Royce, and is a widower. He has served as High Steward of the Vale for the fourteen years.
Ser Robar Royce also known as Robar the Red is a knight from House Royce and is the second eldest son of the Lord of Runestone. He has aspirations to serve as a Kingsguard.
Rhea Royce is a noblewoman of House Royce and is the daughter of Lord Yohn Royce of Runestone.
Ysilla Royce is a noblewoman of House Royce and is the daughter of Lord Yohn Royce of Runestone.
Ser Andar Royce is a knight from House Royce and is the eldest son and heir of Yohn Royce, Lord of Runestone.

Sučasny Pieršasny Šlachcič Račnych Ziamiel syn i spadkajemca pamierłaha Šlachciča Chostera Talli, a taksama rycar haspadarstva. Edmur byŭ zbrojanosam Brendana Starka da jaho śmierci. Jon vybuchny, ale jaho serca znachodzicca ŭ słušnym miescy. Taksama jon zjaŭlajecca trecim i samym małodšym dziciom.
Norbert Vance is the Lord of Atranta and the head of House Vance of Atranta. Norbert squired for Lord Darry in his youth, alongside a young Brynden Talli.
Clement Piper is the Lord of Pinkmaiden and head of House Piper. He has at least two sons, Ser Marq and Lewys Piper.
Ser Marq Piper is a knight from House Piper. He is the heir of Clement Piper, Lord of Pinkmaiden Castle.

Walder Frey is the Lord of the Crossing and head of House Frey. Though Walder is very, very old and infirm, he still maintains an active hand in the running of his house at the Twins. Walder has become famous for siring many children and surviving many wives. He is to marry his eighth wife and has over a hundred descendants, base and trueborn. Walder has had twenty-two trueborn sons and seven trueborn daughters from his marriages, with an unknown number of bastard sons and daughters. He places a great emphasis on family loyalty, though his descendants jockey ruthlessly for his favor. Many Freys name their sons Walder and daughters Walda hoping that the lord will favor them.
Lady Joyeuse Erenford is a member of House Erenford and the eighth wife of Lord Walder Frey.
Ser Stevron Frey is a knight from House Frey, Lord Walder Freys firstborn son, and heir to the Twins. His mother was Lady Perra Royce.
Lothar Frey, often called Lame Lothar, is a member of House Frey, the twelfth son of Lord Walder Frey, and his eldest son by his fourth wife Lady Alyssa Blackwood.

Ser Aenys Frey is a knight from House Frey and is the third son of Walder Frey, Lord of the Crossing, and his first spouse, Lady Perra Royce. Aenys is married to Tyana Wylde, and has two sons with her, Aegon and Ser Rhaegar.

Walder Frey, called Black Walder to differentiate him from others with the same name, is a member of House Frey. He is the second son of Ser Ryman Frey, grandson to Ser Stevron Frey, and great-grandson of Lord Walder Frey. It is rumored that Black Walder has fathered many of Lord Walders alleged children.
Ser Emmon Frey is a knight from House Frey and is the second son of Lord Walder Frey and Lady Perra Royce. He is married to Lady Genna Łańnistar.

Roslin Frey is a noblewoman of House Frey, the only daughter of Lord Walder Frey by his sixth wife, Lady Bethany Rosby, but his fifth overall. Roslin has four older brothers –Ser Perwyn, Ser Benfrey, Maester Willamen, and Olyvar– and many half-siblings.
Ser Walder Rivers is the eldest of Walder Freys bastards. Though not a trueborn Frey, he is often put in positions of responsibility due to his strong reputation as a warrior.

Łedzi Korbrej - dońka handlara i druhaja žonka Lionneła Korbreja, Šlachciča Doma Serca i hłavy Doma Korbrej. Picyr Bejliš kolišni mytnik porta Horada Čajek, staŭ pasiarednikam u šlubie miž dońkaj handlara i Šlachcičam Lionnełam Korbrejam z Doma Serca paśla śmierci jaho pieršaj žonki.
Lucas Corbray is a knight of House Corbray. He is the younger brother of Lord Lyonel and Ser Lyn Corbray.
Lyonel Corbray is Lord of Hearts Home and head of House Corbray. He has two brothers, Ser Lyn and Ser Lucas.
Ser Lyn Corbray is a knight from House Corbray who wields Lady Forlorn, a sword of Valyrian steel. He is the heir of his elder brother, Lord Lyonel Corbray of Hearts Home.
Utherydes Wayn is the steward of Biahučajaraka under Edmur Talli. He is the only known member of House Wayn.

Ser Brynden Talli, also known as Brynden Blackfish, Brynden the Blackfish, or simply the Blackfish, is a knight from House Talli. He is the younger brother of Hoster Talli, Lord Paramount of the Trident, and the uncle of Lady Katelin Stark, Lady Lysa Arryn, and Ser Edmur Talli. The Blackfish has served as the Knight of the Gate for House Arryn since Roberts Rebellion. He has since resigned from his position in the Vale and returned to his Talli roots to defend the Račnyje Ziemli against the Lannisters.
Ser Tristan Ryger is a knight of House Ryger who serves the Tullys in Biahučajaraka. He is a childhood friend of Edmur Talli.
Ser Eustace Hunter is a knight from House Hunter. He is the second son of Lord Eon Hunter.
Ser Gilwood Hunter is a knight from House Hunter of Longbow Hall. He is the eldest son and heir of Lord Eon Hunter.
Eon Hunter is the Lord of Longbow Hall and the head of House Hunter. He has three quarrelsome sons: Gilwood, Eustace and Harlan Hunter.
The lord of Seagard and a tourney knight. During Roberts rebellion it is said that he slew three of Rhaegar Targaryens bannermen himself to avenge the death of his brother.
The son and heir of Jason Mallister. It is said that he enjoys drink, the company of women and hawking. He is also good friends with Ser Edmur Talli.

Tytos Blackwood is the Lord of Raventree Hall and the head of House Blackwood in the riverlands. Lord Blackwood appreciates honor and chivalry. He is noted to be a skilled warrior and friend of the Starki of Minańnie Zimy. Tytos has a feud with Lord Jonos Bracken.
Eldest son and heir of Lord Tytos Blackwood.
The only daughter of Lord Tytos Blackwood and is a gentle and sheltered girl.
Hoster Blackwood, called Hos by family and friends, is the third son of Lord Tytos Blackwood of Raventree Hall.
William Mooton is Lord of Maidenpool and head of House Mooton.

Bułava Tajreł is the Lord of Vysokisad, Lord Paramount of the Mander, Defender of the Marches, High Marshal of the Miaža, Warden of the South, and head of House Tajreł. Bułava became Lord of Vysokisad once his father, Lord Luthor Tajreł, rode off a cliff while hawking.

Ser Garlan Tajreł, known as Garlan the Gallant, is a knight of House Tajreł and the second son of Lord Bułava Tajreł and Lady Alerie Hightower. He is an exceptionally skilled swordsman, preferring to train against three or four swordsmen, so as to better prepare himself for actual battle, but his lack of interest in gaining glory makes him less famous than Loras.
Mardžery Tajreł is the only daughter of Lord Bułava Tajreł and his wife, Lady Alerie Hightower. She has three older brothers, Willas, Ser Garlan, and Ser Loras.

Megga Tajreł is a member of House Tajreł, being the granddaughter of Ser Quentin Tajreł, a cousin of Bułava Tajreł, the Lord of Vysokisad. The only daughter of Ser Olymer Tajreł and his wife, Lysa Meadows, Megga has two older brothers: Raymund and Rickard Tajreł.
Willas Tajreł is a member of House Tajreł and the eldest son of Lord Bułava Tajreł and Lady Alerie Hightower. He is the heir to Vysokisad.

Ser Loras Tajreł, also known as the Knight of Flowers, is a knight from House Tajreł and the third son of Lord Bułava Tajreł of Vysokisad and his wife, Lady Alerie Hightower. He is a highly skilled knight and jouster. His tournament successes, dazzling good looks, and ostentatious showmanship has made him a celebrated figure in the courts of the Seven Kingdoms. He is currenlty serving as Renli Barateons Lord Commander of the Rainbow Guard.
Łord Kanca Štormu i brat niabožčyka karala Robierta Barateona.
Ser Cortnay Penrose is a knight of House Penrose. The son of Lord Penrose, he is named by Renli Barateon as castellan of Storms End.

Taksama viadomy jak Brajs Pamiarancavy, staŭ hłavoj svajho Domu paśla śmierci jaho baćki, maci, brata i ŭsich siaścior ad žudasnaha choładu ŭ 289 hodzie n.e. Adziny viadomy žyvy svajak Brajsa - jaho zvodny brat-bastard, Ser Rołłand Štorm, jaki dałučyŭsia da Viasiołkavaj Varty Haspadara Renli.

Stańnis Barateon is the head of House Barateon of Cmačyny Kamień and the Lord of Cmačyny Kamień. He is the secondborn son of Steffon Barateon, Lord of Storms End, and Lady Cassana Estermont. He has an older brother, King Robert I Barateon, and a younger brother, Lord Renli Barateon. Stańnis serves on Roberts small council as the master of ships. Influenced by Melisandre, Stańnis adopts a new sigil which depicts the Barateon stag enclosed within a red heart surrounded by orange flame.
Ser Andrew Estermont is a knight from House Estermont and son of Ser Lomas Estermont. Ser Andrew served as Stańnis Barateons former squire.

Melisandre is a red priestess of Rhllor and a shadowbinder, hailing from the city of Asshai in the Further East of Essos. She has joined the court of Stańnis Barateon, Lord of Cmačyny Kamień, believing him to be Azor Ahai reborn, a hero destined to defeat the Great Other. She has become an influential advisor to him and his family.
Adzinaje dzicio Stańnisa Barateona. U malenstvie jana zachvareła šeraj chvarobaj, ale była vylečana. Z-za hetaha jaje tvar nazaŭždy źniaviečany.

Ser Axell Florent is a knight of House Florent who serves as the castellan of Cmačyny Kamień for his nephew-in-law, Lord Stańnis Barateon. He is the younger brother of Lord Alester Florent of Brightwater Keep.
Ralph Buckler is Lord of Bronzegate and head of House Buckler. He is a Bannerman of House Barateon.
Ser Balon Swann is a knight from House Swann and the second son of Lord Gulian Swann of Stonehelm. Balon aspires to be a member of the Kingsguard and is a skilled swordsman.
Ser Brus Buckler is a knight from House Buckler. He is the cousin of Ralph Buckler, Lord of Bronzegate.

Selwyn Tarth, or Selywn of Tarth, is the Lord of Tarth, Lord of Evenfall, and the head of House Tarth. Known as the Evenstar, Selwyn has one remaining child, his daughter and heir, Brienne who has joined Renlis Rainbow Guard.

Monford Velaryon is the Lord of the Tides, the Master of Driftmark, and the head of House Velaryon. Aurane Waters, the Bastard of Driftmark, is his bastard half-brother. He has a young son and heir, Monterys Velaryon.
Monterys Velaryon is a member of House Velaryon and is the young heir of Monford Velaryon, Lord of the Tides.

Ser Davos Seaworth, commonly called the Onion Knight, and sometimes Davos Shorthand, is the head of House Seaworth. He was once a smuggler, but after Roberts Rebellion he became a landed knight and Stańnis Barateons most honest and loyal supporter. Davos created his own house sigil, a black ship with an onion on the sails upon a grey field. Davos captains Black Betha. He has seven sons, many of them serving on ships in Stańniss fleet. His wife Marya tends his lands on Nakidka Wrath.
Marya Seaworth is the wife of Ser Davos Seaworth, and mother of his seven sons.
Maci Cmokaŭ, čyjo hałoŭnaje žadańnie - viarnuć tron svajho baćki ŭ Karaleŭskaj Prystani.
Najeźnik kryvi dotrakijcaŭ, jaki zastaŭsia addany Danaerys paśla śmierci Chała Droha.

The Bastard of the Deadfort, known to be cruel and sick, Ramsay is the product of Roose raping his mother and killing her husband. It is also whispered that Ramsay killed his legitimate brother so hed be his fathers only son.
Known as the Leech Lord as he sees leeching as a means to stay healthy. He is known to practice the the first night which is outlawed in the Seven Kingdoms, but was a First Man tradition.

Walda Frey, known as Fat Walda, is the second daughter of Merrett Frey and Mariya Darry, and a granddaughter of Lord Walder Frey, the head of House Frey. had offered Roose his prospective brides weight in silver for her dowry. Lord Bolton chose the fattest available female member of House Frey.
Myranda is a servant of House Bolton of the Dreadfort and one of Ramsay Snows bedwarmers. She is the daughter of the Kennel Master Ben Bones.
Arstan Selmy is the Lord of Harvest Hall and the head of House Selmy. He is the nephew of the famous Barrystan Sełmi.

Balon Greyjoy is the Lord of the Iron Islands and the head of House Greyjoy of Pyke. The captain of the Great Kraken, he is a follower of the Old Way of the ironborn and desires to bring them back to prominence. In 289 AC he proclaimed their independence from the Žalezny Tron, but Greyjoys Rebellion was defeated by King Robert I Barateons forces. Since the death of Ned Stark, Balon has proclaimed himself King of both the Iron Islands and the North and has declared war on Rob Stark in subsequence.
Alannys Harlaw is the wife of Lord Balon Greyjoy and sister to Lord Rodrik Harlaw. She had four children with Balon; Rodrik, Maron, Asha and Theon. She is nicknamed Lanny by her brother, Lord Rodrik.
Victarion Greyjoy is a member of House Greyjoy and is a younger brother of Balon Greyjoy, Lord of the Iron Islands. He is the Lord Captain of the Iron Fleet, and his flagship is the Iron Victory.
Jara Hrejdžoj is a member of House Greyjoy and is the eldest daughter of Lord Balon Greyjoy by his wife, Alannys Harlaw.

Euron Greyjoy, known as Crows Eye and Euron Crows Eye, is a member of House Greyjoy and is the eldest of Lord Balon Greyjoys younger brothers. Euron is captain of the Silence, a ship crewed entirely by mutes whose tongues he ripped out. Eurons personal coat-of-arms is a red eye with a black pupil beneath a black iron crown supported by two crows.

Mans Najeźnik was once a man of the Nights Watch before breaking his vows and abandoning his post. He has since become extremely influential among the free folk, and is called the King-Beyond-the-Wall.
Val is a member of the free folk. She is the sister of Dalla, the wife of Mans Najeźnik.
The Weeper, also known as the Weeping Man, is a notorious free folk raider and leader of a war band.
Dalla is a wildling and the wife of Mans Najeźnik. She has a sister, Val.
Ryk, known as Longspear Ryk, is a free folk raider and a member of Rayders war band. Ryk is called Longspear because he is well endowed.

Rodrik Harlaw is the Lord of Harlaw, Lord of the Ten Towers, and head of House Harlaw. He is nicknamed Rodrik the Reader because he is always reading, which is uncommon amongst the ironborn. He is the captain of Sea Song.
Harriet Pyke is the daughter of Hotho Harlaw. She has flowered and Hotho is looking for suitable matches.

Ser Harras Harlaw, known as the Knight, is the head of House Harlaw of Grey Garden and the knight of Grey Garden. A knight, Harras is the heir of House Harlaw of Ten Towers, as its current lord, Rodrik Harlaw, has no surviving children.

Lady Gwynesse Harlaw is a noblewoman of House Harlaw. She is a sister of Lord Rodrik Harlaw. Gwynesse is a widow and mourns her husband as deeply as she did when he died. She has grown forgetful, however, and cannot always recall his name.
Hotho Harlaw, known as Hotho Humpback, is a member of House Harlaw and the master of the Tower of Glimmering. He has a daughter.
Allyria Dayne is a member of House Dayne, and is the younger sibling of Ser Arthur Dayne and Lady Ashara Dayne. She is the aunt of the young Edric Dayne, Lord of Starfall.

Edric Dayne, also known as Ned, is the young Lord of Starfall and head of House Dayne. His father, whose name is unknown, was the elder brother of Ser Arthur, Lady Ashara, and Lady Allyria Dayne. As Lord Beric Dondarrions squire, Edric is part of the force sent by Eddard to the riverlands to apprehend Ser Hrehor Klihan.
Ser Gerold Dayne, known as Darkstar, is the Knight of High Hermitage. His house is a cadet branch of the Daynes of Starfall.

The Lord of Bones, also mocked as Rattleshirt, is a free folk leader of renown. His given name is unknown. The raider is considered sly, cruel and treacherous. The Lord of Bones distrusts wargs and the Nights Watch. Before Mans Najeźnik made peace between them while becoming King-Beyond-the-Wall, Rattleshirt warred with Harma Dogshead.
Ragwyle is a member of the wildling scouting party commanded by Rattleshirt. She is a Spearwife, an elite Wildling warrior. She is also very big.
Rykard Karstark - Šlachcič Trymańnia Karaŭ i hłava Doma Karstarkaŭ. Jon maje troch synoŭ: Charryjona, Eddarda i Torrena dy adnu dońku, Alis. Jon luty vajar, surovy i pomślivy čałaviek.
Alys Karstark is a noblewoman of House Karstark and is the only daughter of Rickard Karstark, Lord of Karhold.
Youngest son of Lord Rickard Karstark.
Ygritte a Wildling woman with strong skill with a spear and a bow. Ygritte came from the same village as Longspear Ryk, whom she regards as a brother.

Tormund is a trusted leader in his own right of a large warband of Adzičełyja. He has joined his forces to those of King-Beyond-the-Wall Mans Najeźnik, and now functions as one of Mances most trusted lieutenants. Tormund is not just a capable leader, but also a very dangerous fighter. Tormund, often called Tormund Praklon Vołataŭ or Tormund Thunderfist, is a famous free folk raider from Ruddy Hall. He has four sons, Toregg, Torwynd, Dryn, and Dormund, and one daughter, Munda. He is styled Tall-talker, Horn-blower and Breaker of Ice, Husband to Bears, the Mead-king of Ruddy Hall, Speaker to Gods and Father of Hosts.
Gorold Goodbrother is the Lord of Hammerhorn and the head of House Goodbrother.
Gysella Goodbrother is one of the twelve daughters of Lord Gorold Goodbrother.
Greydon Goodbrother is the eldest son and heir of Gorold Goodbrother, Lord of Hammerhorn.

Prince Doran Nymeros Martell, also known simply as Doran Martell, is the head of House Martell, the Prince of Dorne, and the Lord of Sunspear. Married to Lady Mellario, of the Free City of Norvos, he has three children: Arianne, Quentyn, and Trystane. Hes also the elder brother of Elia and Oberyn Martell.
Tyene Sand is the bastard daughter of Prince Oberyn Martell and a septa. She is one of the infamous Sand Snakes.

Areo Hotah is originally from Norvos, one of the northern Free Cities. He joined the Martell household at Sunspear along with Prince Dorans wife, a Norvoshi noblewoman. He has been a trusted servant of the Martells for many years, and is renowned for his skill with his halberd. Hotahs motto is Serve, Protect, Obey.
Obara Sand is the bastard daughter of Oberyn Martell and an Oldtown whore. She is the eldest of the infamous Sand Snakes and a formidable warrior.

Prince Oberyn Nymeros Martell, also known as the Red Viper, is a member of House Martell and is the younger brother of Doran Martell, Prince of Dorne. Oberyn has eight bastard daughters called the Sand Snakes, the four youngest of whom are by his current paramour, Ellaria Sand. Prince Oberyn trained at the Citadel in his youth, in order to become a maester. Although he ultimately grew bored and abandoned his studies, he managed to forge several links in a maesters chain, and became well versed in the use of poisons in the process. When he was sixteen, an older nobleman caught Oberyn in bed with his mistress and wife, and challenged Oberyn to a duel to first blood. Oberyn won the duel, and several days later the man died from festering wounds, likely because Oberyn had poisoned his blade. Oberyn also traveled to Essos in his youth. For a time, he served in the mercenary company known as the Second Sons. It is implied that Oberyn fought duels in the infamous fighting pits of Meereen.
Nymeria Sand, nicknamed Lady Nym, is a bastard daughter of Oberyn Martell and a noblewoman from Volantis. She is the second oldest of the infamous Sand Snakes.
Born in 287 AC, Trystane is the youngest child of his father, Prince Doran Martell, and mother, Lady Mellario of Norvos.
Franklyn Fowler, called the Old Hawk, is the Lord of Skyreach and the head of House Fowler. He also holds the title Warden of the Princes Pass. He is the father of the Fowler twins.
Daeron Vaith is Lord of the Red Dunes and head of House Vaith.

Anders Yronwood is the Lord of Yronwood and head of House Yronwood. He also holds the titles the Bloodroyal and Warden of the Stone Way. He has a son, Cletus and two daughters, Ynys, and Gwyneth. Prince Quentyn Martell had previously been his ward.
Gwyneth Yronwood is the youngest daughter of Lord Anders Yronwood.
Dagos Manwoody is the Lord of Kingsgrave and head of House Manwoody.
Mors Manwoody is the eldest son and heir of Dagos Manwoody, Lord of Kingsgrave.

The Warden of the West and Lord of Skała Kasterli. Tajŭjin served as Hand of the King of Aerys II Tarharyjen, his friend for many years until he went mad. Tajŭjin is one of the most powerful men in the Seven Kingdoms and some say even more powerful than the King himself. Brutal, efficient, and callus Tajŭjin is a man that achieves his goals no matter the cost. He has recently taken command of the army of the Crownlands and Westerlands to do battle against the Starki and their bannermen, although he has been suffering unexpected defeats as of late, Tajŭjins cunning is not to be trifled with.

Eldest of Tywins children and Queen of the Seven Kingdoms of Westeros. She is cunning, manipulative, beautiful, and ruthless. She may be a woman but she is a fighter. She is the twin sister of Jamie Łańnistar, the Kingslayer.

Prince Tommen Barateon is known to the Seven Kingdoms as the youngest child of King Robert I Barateon and Queen Cerseja Łańnistar. A member of House Barateon of Kings Landing, his siblings are Prince Džoffry and Princess Myrcella.Tommen, unlike Džoffry, is regarded as a good-hearted lad who always tries his best. Tommen is tenderhearted and not as strong-willed as his brother. Many believe that he would be a much better king than Džoffry.

Princess Myrcella Barateon is known to the Seven Kingdoms as the middle child of King Robert Barateon and Queen Cerseja Łańnistar. A member of House Barateon of Kings Landing, her siblings are Princes Džoffry and Tommen. Myrcella has golden curls, emerald eyes, and full lips. She is described by her uncle, Tyrion Łańnistar, as having all of her mother Cersejas beauty, but none of her mothers nature. Myrcella is delicate, beautiful, and courteous. For her age, she displays courage, a strong will, and high intelligence.

The younger brother of Tajŭjin Łańnistar and husband of Lady Dorna Swyft. Kevan was a confidant and companion for his elder brother, Tajŭjin since childhood. Recognizing the competency of Tajŭjin at an early age, Kevan did his best to realize his brothers wishes, though this meant perpetually living in his shadow. In contrast, Tajŭjin had stormy relations with his other brothers, Tygett and Gerion.
Lancel Łańnistar is a member of House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli and is the eldest son of Ser Kevan Łańnistar. Lancel and his cousin, Tyrek Łańnistar, are squires to King Robert I Barateon.
Willem is the second son Ser Kevan Łańnistar and Lady Dorna Swyft and is a young squire in service of House Łańnistar

Ser Stafford Łańnistar is a knight of House Łańnistar. He is the good-brother to the Warden of the West as his sister, Lady Joanna, married their cousin, Lord Tajŭjin Łańnistar. hen he was a young squire, Stafford and two Lannisters of Lannisport were captured by Lady Ellyn Tarbeck in retaliation for the imprisonment of her husband, Lord Walderan Tarbeck, by Ser Tajŭjin Łańnistar. Lord Tytos Łańnistar forced the prisoners to be exchanged, however. Hostilities later erupted with the Reyne-Tarbeck rebellion, which Tajŭjin suppressed. He is considered to be a blundering fool by his superiors.

Randyll Tarly is Lord of Horn Hill and head of House Tarly. He is married to Lady Melessa Florent, and is the father of Samwell, Dickon, Talla and two other daughters. Randyll wields the Tarly ancestral blade Heartsbane, a Valyrian steel greatsword, in battle.
Talla Tarly is the daughter of Lord Randyll Tarly and his wife Lady Melessa Florent.

Lady Melessa Florent is a noblewoman of House Florent, the middle child and eldest daughter of Lord Alester Florent of Brightwater. She is married to Lord Randyll Tarly and the mother of Samwell, Talla, and Dickon Tarly, as well as two other daughters.

Ser Hyle Hunt is a knight of House Hunt and a captain in service to House Tarly. Ser Hyle served House Tarly at Horn Hill. When Lord Randyll Tarly tried to teach his son Samwell to swim by throwing him in a pond, Hyle had to rescue Sam.
Dickon Tarly is the second son and fifth child of Lord Randyll Tarly and Lady Melessa Florent. Since his less martial older brother Samwell has joined the Nights Watch, he is the heir to Horn Hill.

Lysa is the youngest daughter of Lord Hoster Talli of Biahučajaraka and his wife, Lady Minisa Whent, and widow of Jon Arryn, the late Lord of the Eyrie and Hand of the King to King Robert I Barateon. Since Jon Arryns death she has assumed control of the Vale via her son.

Harrold Hardyng, often called Harry the Heir and sometimes the Young Falcon, is a gallant, handsome squire, and a ward of Lady Anya Waynwood. He is the cousin and heir presumptive of Lord Robert Arryn and would ascend to rule of the Vale as Harrold Arryn should Lord Robert die without issue. He has recently had a few scandals at court involving serving girls and merchants daughters.
Ser Vardzisa Ehiena is Captain of the Guard of the Eyrie. He also has a young son.
Alys is the bastard daughter of Harrold Hardyng and a serving girl named Cissy from House Waynwood.

Robin Arryn, also called Sweetrobin by his mother, is the only son of Lord Jon Arryn and Lady Lysa Talli. Robert is named after King Robert I Barateon. Robert is small, painfully thin for his age and has been sickly all his days. Some suspect that Petyr Baelish is his real father, but he has been raised by Lord Arryn with love due to his inability to father more children.
Ser Baelor Hightower, also known as Baelor Brightsmile, is a knight from House Hightower. He is the eldest son and heir of Lord Leyton Hightower of Oldtown. Baelor is wed to Rhonda Rowan.
Rhonda Rowan is a member of House Rowan. She is married to Ser Baelor Hightower, the heir of House Hightower.

Ser Garth Hightower, called Greysteel, is a knight of House Hightower and the second son of Lord Leyton Hightower. Garth is a knight of some repute and is given the task of training new troops at Oldtown.
Ser Gunthor Hightower is a knight of House Hightower. He is the third son of Lord Leyton Hightower and is married to Jeyne Fossoway.
Ser Amory Lorch is a knight of House Lorch and bannerman of House Łańnistar
Polliver is a man-at-arms among the Mountains men in service to Ser Hrehor Klihan. Polliver is a grim and methodical fighter, but not as evil as his more violent comrades in the Mountains men.

Ser Hrehor Klihan is the Knight of Cleganes Keep and the head of House Clegane, a landed knight and bannerman to House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli. Gregor is a freakishly large man and for this he is often called the Mountain That Rides or simply the Mountain. His soldiers are known as the Mountains men.

Ser Addam Marbrand is a knight of House Marbrand and the son and heir of Lord Damon Marbrand of Ashemark. He is one of the chief knights in the service of Tajŭjin Łańnistar, Lord of Skała Kasterli. Gallant and charming, Addam is an excellent horseman and swordfighter. He is described as a daring commander whom others would willingly follow into battle. Addam is a trusted friend of Ser Jaime Łańnistar of House Łańnistar.
Leo Lefford is the Lord of the Golden Tooth and the head of House Lefford. Leo is a sour man.
Alysanne Lefford is the Lady of the Golden Tooth and heir of Lord Leo Lefford.
Lord Terrence Kenning is Lord of Kayce and head of House Kenning of Kayce.

Ser Harys Swyft is the Knight of Cornfield and the head of House Swyft. He is the good-father to Ser Kevan Łańnistar. When Tytos Łańnistar was Lord of Skała Kasterli, Ser Harys borrowed large sums of money from House Łańnistar. Upon Ser Tajŭjin Łańnistars return from the War of the Ninepenny Kings, the young heir of Skała Kasterli was determined to return his Houses status and began by demanding repayment of gold lent by his father, Tytos. Those who could not repay immediately had to send a hostage to the Rock until their debt was settled. Harys hastened to obey, stating, The lion has awoken. Unable to pay immediately, Harys surrendered his daughter, Dorna, into the custody of Tajŭjins younger brother Ser Kevan Łańnistar until the debt was settled. Kevan eventually married Dorna.
The daughter of Ser Steffon Swyft.
The daughter of Ser Steffon Swyft.
The daughter of Ser Steffon Swyft.
A knight of House Swyft as well as the son and heir of Ser Harys Swyft.
Roland Crakehall is the Lord of Crakehall and the head of House Crakehall.
Lady Crakehall is the wife of Lord Roland Crakehall. They have several children together.
Ser Tybolt Crakehall is a knight of House Crakehall. He is the eldest son and heir of Lord Roland Crakehall.
Renfred Rykker is Lord of Duskendale and head of House Rykker, a noble house of the crownlands.
Proclaimed himself King in the North once his father was executed in Kings Landing.

Chaŭłend Ryyd - Šlachcič Dazoru Šeraj Vady i hłava Doma Ryydaŭ, jaki vałodaje daminijonam ludziej krannohaŭ Šyi. Mira i Džodžen - dzieci Chaŭłenda ad jaho žonki Džyany. Jon byŭ blizkim siabram pamierłaha Šlachciča Eddarda Starka z Minańnia Zimy.
Jyana is a crannogwoman and the wife of Lord Howland Reed. Together they have two children: Meera and Jojen Reed.
Meera Reed is a member of House Reed. She is Lord Howland Reeds daughter and oldest child; her younger brother is Jojen Reed.
Jojen Reed is a member of House Reed. He is Lord Howland Reeds only son and Meera Reeds younger brother. Jojen has greensight, the power of prophetic green dreams.
Galbart Glover is the head of House Glover and Master of Deepwood Motte. The tactful Galbart is considered a good, loyal, and steady man, if unexceptional. He is also unwed.
Gawen Glover is a member of House Glover, the eldest son of Robett and Sybelle Glover.
Erena Glover is the daughter of Robett and Sybelle Glover.

Wyman is the Lord of White Harbor and the head of House . He also holds several honorary titles: Warden of the White Knife, Ščyt of the Faith, Defender of the Dispossessed, Lord Marshal of the Mander, and Knight of the Order of the Green Hand. A widower for the past eight years, Wyman has two adult sons, Ser Wylis and Ser Wendel . Wyman is amiable and has a loud, booming laugh. By his own admission, and because of his physical appearance, Wyman is seen by many as craven and foolish. This is a clever front, however, as Wyman is shrewd, calculating, and intelligent. Lord is also staunchly loyal to House Stark.
Wylla is the second daughter of Ser Wylis and Leona Woolfield.

Jon Umber, known as Greatjon Umber and the Greatjon, is Lord of the Last Hearth and head of House Umber, a vassal family to the Starki of Minańnie Zimy. His eldest son, also named Jon, is called the Smalljon. Jon is a large man, nearly seven feet tall and twice as wide as Hodor. He is heavily muscled and is a formidable warrior with fists as large as hams. Jaime Łańnistar regards him as one of the strongest living men in Westeros when thinking of who could match him in a fight.
Robett Glover is a member of House Glover. He is the brother of Galbart Glover, the husband of Sybelle Glover, and the father of two children, Gawen and Erena.

Lady Sybelle Glover, originally from House Locke, is the wife of Robett Glover and the mother of Gawen and Erena Glover. In the absence of the brothers Galbart and Robett, Sybelle is the Lady of Deepwood Motte, although it is the steward who truly rules at Deepwood Motte.
Ser Wylis , known as The Fat Bugger is a knight of House . He is the eldest son and heir of Wyman , Lord of White Harbor.
Small compared to his father, he is a fierce fighter, but known for his lack of morals.
The youngest son of Wyman . Not as large as his father and brother he is still a large man. He specializes with the bow.
Daaryjo Nacharys - lidar Druhich Synoŭ, najmickaj bandy z Zatoki Handlaroŭ Rabami.

Paxter Redwyne is the Lord of the Arbor and head of House Redwyne. He is married to his cousin, Mina Tajreł, the sister of his liege lord, Bułava Tajreł; he is thus twice a nephew of the Queen of Thorns, Olenna Redwyne. Paxter and Mina have two sons, Ser Horas and Ser Hobber, and a daughter, Desmera.

Ser Horas Redwyne, mocked as Ser Horror, is a knight of House Redwyne and heir to the Arbor. He is the son of Paxter Redwyne, Lord of the Arbor, and Lady Mina Tajreł, and he is the older twin to Ser Hobber

Dzizmera Čyrvonaje Vino čalec Doma Čyrvonaje Vino, dońka i małodšaje dzicio Šlachciča Pasktara Redŭjina i Miny Tajreł. Dzizmera viadomaja svaimi viaśniankami. Šlachcič Randził Tarli spadziajecca, što jaho syn i spadkajemca Samŭeł stanie pažam Šlachciča Pasktara ŭ Altanki i ŭ svoj čas voźmie šlub z Dzizmeraj.
Ser Hobber Redwyne, mocked as Ser Slobber, is a knight from House Redwyne. He is the son of Paxter Redwyne, Lord of the Arbor, and Lady Mina Tajreł, and he is the younger twin to Ser Horas.

Maege Mormont, known as the She-Bear, is the head of House Mormont and the Lady of Miadźviedžaja Vyspa. She inherited her title from her nephew, Ser Džorach Marmont, after he fled into exile. She is the younger sister of the Lord Commander of the Nights Watch, Jeor Mormont.
Lyanna Mormont is the youngest daughter of Lady Maege Mormont. She was named after Lyanna Stark.

King Džoffry Barateon is known to the Seven Kingdoms as the eldest son and heir of King Robert I Barateon and Queen Cerseja Łańnistar. A member of House Barateon of Kings Landing, his siblings are Princess Myrcella and Prince Tommen. After taking the Žalezny Tron as Roberts heir, Džoffry started his first court session by naming his grandfather, Lord Tajŭjin Łańnistar, as the new Hand of the King, appointing his mother to the small council and Jaime Łańnistar as Lord Commander of the Kingsguard, and dismissing the legendary knight Barrystan Sełmi from his service, against all traditions. He was also responsible for ordering the execution of Lord Eddard Stark.
Ser Meryn Trant is a knight from House Trant. He is a member of King Robert I Barateons Kingsguard. Jaime Łańnistar considers Meryn to be sly and cruel. House Trant is from the Stormlands.

Ser Osmund Kettleblack is a member of House Kettleblack who claims to be a hedge knight. He is the son of Oswell Kettleblack and he has two brothers, Osfryd and Osney. He and his brothers came to work for Queen Cerseja.
Ser Boros Blount is a knight from House Blount who serves in the Kingsguard of Robert I Barateon. House Blount is from the Crownlands.
Medger Cerwyn is the Lord of Cerwyn and head of House Cerwyn. He has two children: a daughter, Jonelle and a son, Cley. He is a soft spoken man and the head of House Cerwyn.

Jonelle Cerwyn is a member of House Cerwyn and is the daughter of Lord Medger Cerwyn. Jonelle accompanies her father to Minańnie Zimy when Rob Stark calls his banners. Robb tells his brother Bran that Lord Medger plans to take her south with Robbs host. Although Medger claims this is so she can cook for him, Theon Greyjoy believes that Robb will one night find her in his bed.
Cley Cerwyn is a member of House Cerwyn. He is the son of Lord Medger Cerwyn and the heir to Castle Cerwyn.
Lord of Hornwood and father of Daryn Hornwood and Larence Snow.
Daryn Hornwood is the heir to the Hornwood. He is the son of Lord Halys Hornwood and Lady Donella .
Donella Hornwood is the Lady of Hornwood, wife of Lord Halys Hornwood, and mother of Daryn Hornwood. Originally from House , she is a cousin of Wyman , Lord of White Harbor.

Barbrey Dustin, from House Ryswell, is the Lady of Barrowton as the widow of Willam Dustin, Lord of Barrowton. She was born into House Ryswell as the younger daughter of Rodrik Ryswell, Lord of the Rills. It is said that she She bears a grudge against Eddard Stark, who brought the bones of his sister, Lyanna, to Minańnie Zimy for burial in its crypt, but not the bones of her husband, Lord Dustin, to Barrowton.

Sawane Botley is Lord of Lordsport and head of House Botley. He is the captain of the Swiftfin. During Greyjoys Rebellion, Sawanes castle at Lordsport was burned to the ground by King Robert I Barateon. After the rebellion Sawane rebuilt in stone.
Germund Botley is a member of House Botley and the younger brother of Lord Sawane Botley. Germund wears a gilded breastplate that he took off a Łańnistar captain during Greyjoys Rebellion.
Harren Botley is the eldest son of Lord Sawane Botley and is the heir of House Botley. He has a younger brother, Tristifer.

Tristifer Botley, known as Tris, is the second son of Lord Sawane Botley. Tris has messy brown hair and large eyes. He was pimpled as a boy. Although now handsome, Tris has an unrequited love for Asha Greyjoy.

Hodryk Borreł - Šlachcič Šanoŭnaj Siastry, Ščyt Siastratona, Majstar Zamku Chvalarez, Zachoŭnik Načnika, hłava Domu Borreł i słuha svajho siuzierena Šlachciča Razłučanaj Ziamli. Chacia Hodryk maje čornuju reputacyju Šlachciča Rabaŭnika, jon pa-raniejšamu šanuje staražytnyja zakony haścinnaści.

Gerold Grafton is the Lord of Gulltown and head of House Grafton. Gerold is a wide man with thick arms and shoulders, but he is not tall. His hair is a dirty blond mop and he has a booming voice. Gerold is a courteous man.
Gyles Grafton is a squire of House Grafton and is the youngest son of Lord Gerold Grafton.
Denis Bar Emmon is the Lord of Sharp Point and head of House Bar Emmon.
Ardrian Celtigar, known as the Red Crab, is the Lord of Claw Isle and head of House Celtigar. Ardrian is known for his avarice and his wealth. He is considered a sour man.
Harwood Fell is the son of Silveraxe, the Lord of Felwood and is the heir of House Fell.
Ser Ronnet Connington, also known as Red Ronnet, is the Knight of Griffins Roost. He is a landed knight and the head of House Connington. Ronnet has a bastard son, Ronald Storm.
Ser Raymund Connington is the younger brother and heir of Ser Ronnet Connington, the Knight of Griffins Roost. He resides in Griffins Roost.
Macis Roŭan - Šlachcič Załatoha Haju i hłava Domu Roŭan. Jon žanaty na Šlachciankie Betani Čyrvonaje Vino i maje ad jaje troch doniek.
Lady Bethany Redwyne is the wife of Lord Mathis Rowan. Lord Hoster Talli intended to ask for Bethanys hand for his brother Ser Brynden, but Brynden stubbornly refused to marry.
Helen is the daughter of Lord Mathis Rowan and Lady Bethany Redwyne.
Dorna is the daughter of Lord Mathis Rowan and Lady Bethany Redwyne.

Harmen Uller is the Lord of Hellholt and head of House Uller. Harmen is the older brother of Ser Ulwyck Uller. He is the father of Ellaria Sand, the paramour of Prince Oberyn Martell. This makes him the grandfather of the four youngest Sand Snakes: Elia, Obella, Dorea and Loreza.

Ser Ulwyck Uller is a knight from House Uller and the younger brother of Lord Harmen Uller. He is the uncle of Ellaria Sand, the paramour of Prince Oberyn Martell. This makes him the granduncle of the four youngest Sand Snakes: Elia, Obella, Dorea and Loreza.
Lord Flint of Flints Finger is a Bannerman of house Stark. His House is a cadet branch of the Mountain Clan, the First Flints.
Lord Gregor Forrester known as Lord Gregor the good. He is fair and wise and courageous in battle. Lord Forrester is the Lord of Ironrath and a bannerman of House Stark.
Rodrik Forrester also known as Rodrik the Ruin, is the first-born son and heir of Lord Gregor. He has a prominent military background.
Asher Forrester is the second-born son of Lord Gregor. A very rebellious youth, Asher committed actions such as drinking and whoring which made him acquire his fathers disapproval.
Mira Forrester is the eldest daughter and third child of Lord Gregor Forrester and Lady Elissa Branfield.
Ethan Forrester is the third son of Lord Gregor Forrester and Lady Elissa Branfield. Ethan is the twin brother of Talia Forrester.
Talia Forrester is the second-eldest daughter of the House, and the twin-sister of Ethan Forrester. Talia, like her twin Ethan, enjoys music and often sings, while her brother plays.
Ryon is the youngest son of Lord Gregor Forrester.
Lord of Whitehill and known to be a very greedy and stubborn man. He has a long standing feud with House Forrester, who he sees as stealing their rightful Ironwood grove.
Youngest son of Ludd Whitehill and he was bullied by his brothers growing up. He is a childish, aggressive, sadistic, sociopathic, and brutal man.
Gwyn is the only daughter of Ludd Whitehill and ex-lover of Asher Forrester.

House Ryswell of the Rills is a noble family of the north, one of the prominent houses sworn to House Stark of Minańnie Zimy. The Ryswells rule the Rills, the extensive area between the barrowlands and the Stony Shore in the north.
Roger Ryswell is a son of Lord Rodrik Ryswell and a member of House Ryswell.
Rickard Ryswell is a son of Lord Rodrik Ryswell and a member of House Ryswell.
Harwood Stout is the Lord of Goldgrass and head of House Stout. He is a vassal of Lady Barbrey Dustin of Barrowton.

Ronnel Stout is a member of House Stout. Lord Roose Bolton leaves a strong force of Stout and Cerwyn men under the command of Ser Kyle Condon and Ronnel to strengthen the defense of the Trident against the Lannisters.
Alyn Orkwood, called Orkwood of Orkmont, is the head of House Orkwood and is the Lord of Orkmont.

Baelor Blacktyde is the Lord of Blacktyde and the head of House Blacktyde. Baelor captains the Nightflyer. Baelors father, Lord Blacktyde, died during the rebellion launched by Balon Greyjoy, Lord of the Iron Islands. After the war, Baelor spent eight years as a hostage in Oldtown. By the time he came back to the Iron Islands, he had converted to the Faith of the Seven.
Chortan Čyrvonaja Farteca - Šlachcič Čyrvonaj Fartecy i hłava Domu Čyrvonaja Farteca. Jon mieŭ try šlubu i maje čatyroch synoŭ: Sera Džaśpiera, Ser Krejtona, Sera Džona i Majkła.
Ser Jasper Redfort is a knight of House Redfort and is the son of Lord Horton Redfort.
Benedar Belmore is the Lord of Strongsong and the head of House Belmore. Benedar is very fat and has an unkempt reddish-grey beard. Littlefinger believes Benedar to be corrupt.
Ser Marwyn Belmore is a knight of repute from House Belmore. Some say he is next in line to become Captain of the Guards for House Arryn.
Royce Coldwater is Lord of Coldwater Burn and head of House Coldwater.
Ser Ben Coldwater is a knight from House Coldwater.
Ser Tytos Brax is a knight of House Brax. He is the eldest son of Lord Andros Brax and the heir to Hornvale.
Ser Flement Brax is a knight from House Brax and the third son of Lord Andros Brax. He is married to Morya Frey and they have three sons together: Robert, Walder and Jon.

Gawen Westerling is the Lord of the Crag and the head of House Westerling. As the Lord of the Crag, Gawen headed an old and proud, though impoverished, family. Gawen wed Sybell of House Spicer, a wealthy House of lowborn origins. This marriage is said to have somewhat sordid origins, and Gawen is rumored to have been entrapped into the marriage
Lady Sybell Spicer is the wife of Lord Gawen Westerling and is the Lady of the Crag. She is the granddaughter of Maggy the Frog, a well known prophetic fortune teller.
The Lord of Stone Hedge and head of House Bracken. Knowing for his glowers and blusters, he has only had one bastard son and five legitimate daughters.
Hendry Bracken is a member of House Bracken and nephew to Lord Jonos Bracken of Stone Hedge.
Barbara Bracken is a member of House Bracken, the first daughter of Lord Jonos Bracken of Stone Hedge by his first wife
Jayne Bracken is a member of House Bracken, the second daughter of Lord Jonos Bracken of Stone Hedge by his first wife
Catelyn Bracken is a member of House Bracken, the third daughter of Lord Jonos Bracken of Stone Hedge, and the first by his third wife
Bess Bracken is a member of House Bracken, the fourth daughter of Lord Jonos Bracken of Stone Hedge, and the second by his third wife
Alysanne Bracken is a member of House Bracken, the fifth daughter of Lord Jonos Bracken of Stone Hedge, and the third by his third wife
Theomar Smallwood is the Lord of Acorn Hall and head of House Smallwood. He is married to Lady Ravella Swann and is the father of Carellen Smallwood
Carellen Smallwood is a member of House Smallwood and is the daughter of Lord Theomar Smallwood and Lady Ravella Swann.
Ser Karyl Vance is a knight of House Vance of Wayfarers Rest. He has three daughters, Liane, Rhialta, and Emphyria
Ser Dafyn Vance is the husband of Maegelle Frey. They have three children, Marianne, Walder and Patrek Vance. He is a widower.
Liane Vance is a noblewoman of House Vance of Wayfarers Rest. She is the eldest daughter of the heir of Wayfarers Rest, Ser Karyl Vance.
Rhialta Vance is a noblewoman of House Vance of Wayfarers Rest. She is the second eldest daughter of the heir of Wayfarers Rest, Ser Karyl Vance.
Emphyria Vance is a noblewoman of House Vance of Wayfarers Rest. She is the youngest daughter of the heir of Wayfarers Rest, Ser Karyl Vance.
Ser Raymun Darry is a knight of House Darry and the lord of Castle Darry. He is the youngest of four brothers, all slain during Roberts Rebellion.
Lyman Darry is a nobleman of House Darry and the son and heir of Ser Raymun Darry, the lord of Castle Darry.
Gyles Rosby is the Lord of Rosby and the head of House Rosby. He is known to be a sickly man.
Wanda Rosby is the Lady of Rosby and wife of Lord Gyles Rosby. Wanda is the niece of Tanda Stokeworth, the matriarch of House Stokeworth.
Eustace Brune is Lord of the Dyre Den. He is the cousin of Lothor and Ser Bennard.
Ser Bennard Brune, the Knight of Brownhollow, is the head of House Brune of Brownhollow in the Crackclaw Point area of the Crownlands. He is the cousin of Lord Eustace Brune.

Ser Justin Massey is a knight from House Massey, and one of the Queens Men. Justin once squired for Robert Barateon, from whom it is said he acquired his appetite for women. Justin is an adviser to Stańnis and sits high in his councils.
Sebastion Errol is the heir of Haystack Hall and a member of House Errol.
Ser Eldon Estermont is a knight of House Estermont. He is the Lord of Greenstone.
Lady Sylva Santagar, known as Spotted Sylva, is a member of House Santagar and is the heir of Ser Symon Santagar, the Knight of Spottswood.
Ser Aemon Estermont is a knight of House Estermont. He is the son of Eldon Estermont.
Casper Wylde is Lord of the Rain House and head of House Wylde.
Quenten Banefort is the Lord of Banefort and head of House Banefort.
Lord Serrett is the Lord of Silverhill and the head of House Serrett.
Lady Serrett is the Lady of Silverhill and is married to Lord Serrett.
Lorent Caswell is the Lord of Bitterbridge and head of House Caswell.
Warryn Beesbury is the Lord of Honeyholt and head of House Beesbury.
Lord Branston Cuy is the Lord of Sunhouse and Sunflower Hall. He is head of House Cuy in the Miaža.
Ser Arys Oakheart is a knight from House Oakheart and a member of the Kingsguard of Robert I Barateon. Arys is the youngest son of Lady Arwyn Oakheart of Old Oak.
Ser Arys Oakheart is a knight from House Oakheart and a member of the Kingsguard of Robert I Barateon. Arys is the youngest son of Lady Arwyn Oakheart of Old Oak.
Victaria Tajreł is the daughter of Ser Victor Tajreł and is a cousin of the main branch of House Tajreł. She is the widow of Lord Jon Bulwer.
Alysanne is the daughter of Lord Jon Bulwer and Lady Victaria Tajreł, and she is a cousin of Lord Bułava Tajreł. She succeeded her father after he died of summer fever.
Ondrew Locke is the Lord of Oldcastle and the head of House Locke.
Ser Donnel Locke is a knight from House Locke and son of Lord Ondrew Locke.
Larra Blackmont is the Lady of Blackmont and the head of House Blackmont.
Jynessa Blackmont is a noblewoman of House Blackmont. She is the eldest child and heir of Larra Blackmont, the Lady of Blackmont.
Perros Blackmont is the son of the Lady of Blackmont and a member of House Blackmont. He is a squire.
Trebor Jordayne is Lord of the Tor and head of House Jordayne in Dorne.
Myria Jordayne is a member of House Jordayne and the daughter and heir of Lord Trebor Jordayne of the Tor. She is known to have a rivalry with Lady Toland.
Nymella Toland is the Lady of Ghost Hill and is the head of House Toland. She has two daughters, Valena and Teora. Lady Toland has a fierce rivalry with Lady Jordayne.
Valena Toland is the eldest daughter of the Lady Nymella Toland of Ghost Hill. Valena is tall, beautiful and fierce, with a blaze of bright red hair tumbling about her shoulders.
Lord Quentyn Qorgyle is Lord of Sandstone and head of House Qorgyle in Dorne.
Ser Gulian Qorgyle is a knight of House Qorgyle. He is the eldest child and heir of Lord Quentyn Qorgyle, Lord of Sandstone. He has a younger brother, Ser Arron.
The Great Walrus is a prominent wildling leader among the people of the Frozen Shore.
Devyn Sealskinner is a wildling leader among the people of the Frozen Shore.
Tootega Snowbear is a spearwife among the people of the Frozen Shore and eldest daughter of the Great Walrus and his mate.
Ahna Moonsinger is a spearwife among the people of the Frozen Shore and mate of The Great Walrus. She is a Seeress.
Ookpik is a spearwife among the people of the Frozen Shore and mate of Devyn Sealskinner.
Muktuk is the son of The Great Walrus and Ahna Moonsinger. He is sad to be very fond of whale meat.
Tonraq is the son of Devyn Sealskinner and Ookpik.
Pinga is the daughter of Devyn Sealskinner and Ookpik.
Brandon Norrey, called the Norrey, is the clan chief of House Norrey, one of the mountain clans in the north.
Brandon Norrey, called Brandon the Younger, is the son of the elder Brandon Norrey. He is the heir of Clan Norrey.
Owen Norrey is a member of the Northern Mountain Clan Norrey and one of Rob Starks elite battleguard.
Lady Norrey is a member of the Northern Mountain Clan Norrey and wife of Brandon the Norrey of Clan Norrey. She has several children.
Arra Norrey is a member of the Northern Mountain Clan Norrey and daughter of the elder Brandon Norrey.
Marna Norrey is a member of the Northern Mountain Clan Norrey and daughter of the elder Brandon Norrey.
Dunstan Drumm, also known as The Drumm and the Bone Hand, is head of House Drumm, Lord of Old Wyk, and captain of Thunderer.
Denys Drumm is a member of House Drumm, a son of Lord Dunstan Drumm of Old Wyk.
Donnel Drumm is a member of House Drumm, a son of Lord Dunstan Drumm of Old Wyk.
Andrik the Unsmiling is an ironborn warrior serving Lord Dunstan Drumm. According to singers, Andrik is the fiercest living ironborn warrior. The taciturn Andrik has a reputation for not smiling.
Wife of Dunstan Drumm, also known as The Drumm and the Bone Hand, is head of House Drumm, Lord of Old Wyk, and captain of Thunderer.
Eldest daughter of Dunstan Drumm, also known as The Drumm and the Bone Hand, is head of House Drumm, Lord of Old Wyk, and captain of Thunderer.
Second daughter of Dunstan Drumm, also known as The Drumm and the Bone Hand, is head of House Drumm, Lord of Old Wyk, and captain of Thunderer.
Youngest daughter of Dunstan Drumm, also known as The Drumm and the Bone Hand, is head of House Drumm, Lord of Old Wyk, and captain of Thunderer.
Meldred Merlyn, also known as the Merlyn, is the Lord of Pebbleton and the head of House Merlyn.
Maron Merlyn is the eldest son of Meldred Merlyn.
Maris Merlyn is the eldest daughter of Meldred Merlyn.
Wife of Meldred Merlyn, also known as the Merlyn, is the Lord of Pebbleton and the head of House Merlyn.
Manfryd Merlyn is the captain of the ship Kite in the Iron Fleet.
Merrell is the natural born bastard son of Manfryd Merlyn.

Gylbert Farwynd is Lord of the Lonely Light and head of House Farwynd. He claims to know of a land without winter beyond the Sunset Sea where death holds no sway and every man will be a king and his wife a queen.
Gyles Farwynd is the son of Lord Gylbert Farwynd. He resembles his father.
Ygon Farwynd is the son of Lord Gylbert Farwynd. He resembles his father.
Yohn Farwynd is the son of Lord Gylbert Farwynd. He resembles his father.
Lady Farwynd is the wife of Lord Gylbert Farwynd.
Triston Farwynd is the Lord of Sealskin Point.
Wex Sunderly is the Lord of Saltcliffe and head of House Sunderly of Saltcliffe.
Sylas Sunderly is the son of Lord of Saltcliffe and head of House Sunderly of Saltcliffe.
Shiera Sunderly is the daughter of Lord of Saltcliffe and head of House Sunderly of Saltcliffe.
Lady Sunderly is the wife of Lord of Saltcliffe and head of House Sunderly of Saltcliffe.
Donnor Saltcliffe is a Lord of Saltcliffe and the head of House Saltcliffe.

House Royce of Runestone is an old and powerful noble house of the Vale, sworn to House Arryn. Their seat is the castle Runestone, located on the coast of the narrow sea north of Gulltown.The Royces of Runestone blazon their arms with black iron studs on bronze, bordered with runes, and their motto is We Remember. The Royces are proud of their descent from the First Men. They have several sets of ancient bronze plate armor inscribed with runes that are thought to make their wearers immune to injury.

House Talli of Biahučajaraka is one of the Great Houses of the Seven Kingdoms. Lord Edmur Talli, the Lord Paramount of the Trident, rules over the riverlands from the Talli seat of Biahučajaraka. House Talli follows the Faith of the Seven, although Biahučajaraka still has a godswood. House Talli is an old noble house of First Men origin, dating back to the Age of Heroes. Ser Edmur Talli and his sons were allies of Tristifer IV Mudd, the King of the Rivers and the Hills, but the Tullys knelt to the Andalski conqueror Armistead Vance after Tristifers death. Edmures son, Axel Talli, received land at the confluence of the Red Fork and the Tumblestone, where he constructed Biahučajaraka.

House Frey of the Crossing is a noble house of the riverlands. Their main seat is the Twins, a pair of castles on each bank of the northern Green Fork of the Trident that serves as a vital bridge across the river. The lord of the house is called the Lord of the Crossing. Their sigil is two blue towers united by a bridge on silver-grey, representing the Twins. The strategic location of the Twins has allowed the house to become quite wealthy and can field larger armies than House Talli.

House Corbray of Hearts Home is a noble house from Hearts Home in the Vale of Arryn. It is an old but poor house. The ancestral Valyrian steel longsword of the Corbrays is Lady Forlorn. The Corbrays were an Andalski house during the coming of the Andals to Westeros. Corwyn Corbray conquered the Fingers by defeating Houses Brightstone and Shell, claiming for himself the title of Lord of the Five Fingers. When the First Men began to unite against the Andals, King Robar II Royce slew Qyle Corbray, King of the Fingers and stole Lady Forlorn. The Corbrays claim that Ser Jaime Corbray killed Robar in the Battle of the Seven Stars, reclaiming Lady Forlorn. During Roberts Rebellion, Lyn Corbray fought Lord Jon Arryn at the gates of Gulltown, but later supported his liege lord at the Battle of the Trident. In that battle, Lyn took Lady Forlorn after his father was injured, and he led a charge which broke the Dornishmen. Lyn slew the already-wounded Prince Lewyn Martell of the Kingsguard during the battle. Lyns father gave Lady Forlorn to him upon his death, something his older brother Lyonel resented.

The Tullys of Biahučajaraka are a noble house from the Račnyje Ziemli, sworn to House Stark of Minańnie Zimy. Brynden Talli, also known as the Blackfish, is a younger brother of Lord Hoster Talli, Lord Paramount of the Trident. He is known for his skill as a warrior and his stubbornness. Despite his achievements, Brynden refused to marry and was thus never lord of Biahučajaraka.

The Hunters are of First Man origin. During the Andalski invasion, they allied with Robar II Royce against the Andals. Robar outshot Lord Hunter in an archery contest to gain the Hunters as allies, although some claim Robar cheated. Robars forces were defeated in the Battle of the Seven Stars, however, and the Hunters submitted to Artys I Arryn, the new King of Mountain and Vale. Teora Hunter married Artyss grandson, King Roland I Arryn.

House Mallister of Seagard is one of the most prominent noble houses from the riverlands. Seagard is a fortress built to defend the coast against the reavers from the Iron Islands, and dates from before Aegons Conquest.

House Blackwood of Raventree Hall is an old house from Raventree Hall in the riverlands, one of the main families sworn to House Talli of Biahučajaraka. They once ruled the riverlands as kings during the Age of Heroes. The Blackwoods can field a much larger army than their liege lords. They also ruled the Wolfswood as kings during the Age of Heroes, until the Starki drove them out of the North. Their primary and ancient rivals are House Bracken.
House Mooton of Maidenpool is a noble house of the riverlands, sworn to House Talli. They are one of the largest port and trade centers in the Račnyje Ziemli and Bay of Crabs.

House Tajreł of Vysokisad is one of the Great Houses of the Seven Kingdoms, being Lords Paramount of the Mander and the liege lords of the Miaža. A large, wealthy house, its wealth is only surpassed among the Great Houses by House Łańnistar, and the Tajreły can field the greatest armies. Vysokisad is an ancient seat of rule and the heart of chivalry in the Seven Kingdoms; the Tajreły style themselves Defenders of the Marches and High Marshals of the Miaža, and traditionally, they have been Wardens of the South in addition to Lords Paramount of the Mander. Their sigil is a golden rose on a green field, and their words are Growing Strong. Members of the family tend to have curly brown hair and brown eyes.

House Barateon of Storms End is one of the Great Houses of Westeros, and the principal house in the stormlands. Renli Barateon was the youngest of the three sons of Lord Steffon Barateon and Lady Cassana Estermont. Renli was famous for his good looks, charm, and affability. He was a popular figure in court and enjoyed the support of many lords, but his claim to the Žalezny Tron was ultimately unsuccessful.

House Barateon of Cmačyny Kamień is a cadet branch of House Barateon of Storms End. Stańnis Barateon is the younger brother of the late King Robert Barateon. Stańnis is known for his stern and uncompromising sense of justice. He is also a devout worshipper of the Lord of Light, and it is said that he has been granted magical powers by the god.

House Buckler of Bronzegate is a noble house from Bronzegate in the stormlands sworn to Storms End. During Aegons Conquest, Lords Buckler, Errol, and Fell opposed Orys Barateon during his march from the Aegonfort toward Storms End, but the storm lords were forced to retreat when Rhaenys Tarharyjen had Meraxes set afire parts of what is now the southern kingswood.

House Tarth of Evenfall Hall is a noble house from Evenfall Hall in the stormlands. The family rules Tarth, a beautiful island northeast of Shipbreaker Bay that controls the Straits of Tarth between the island and mainland Westeros. They are one of the main houses sworn to House Barateon of Storms End. Their blazon is quartered with yellow suns on rose and white crescent moons on azure. Ancestors of House Tarth were once kings, and the head of the family is known as the Evenstar, which they claim dates back to the dawn of days. The island of Tarth came under the dominion of Storm Kings of House Durrandon when Durran the Fair married the daughter of Tarths king, Edwyn Evenstar.

House Velaryon of Driftmark rules the island of Driftmark, the largest island of Blackwater Bay in the crownlands. Their castles include Driftmark and High Tide. The head of House Velaryon is titled Lord of the Tides and Master of Driftmark. The Velaryons are sworn to Cmačyny Kamień. Their arms depict a silver seahorse on sea green. Their words are The Old, the True, the Brave. House Velaryon is of Valyrian descent, and its members often have Valyrian features, such as silver hair, purple eyes, and pale skin. It is traditional for the sons of House Velaryon to be given a taste of a seafarers life when young. The positions of master of ships and lord admiral are often filled by a member of House Velaryon, as the family provides most of the royal fleet.

House Footly of Tumbleton is a noble house from the Miaža. They have sworn their loyalty to House Tajreł of Vysokisad. Tumbleton is located on the lower reaches of the Blueburn river. The Footlys blazon their arms with a field of white and four green shamrocks. Their seat is Tumbleton.

House Ashford of Ashford is a noble house from the Miaža, sworn to House Tajreł of Vysokisad. The Ashfords are an ancient house, older even than the Tajreły. They blazon their arms with a white sun and crescent moon, on a field of pale green. Their words are not known. Their seat is Ashford Castle.

House Seaworth of Nakidka Wrath is a noble house from Nakidka Wrath in the stormlands. The blazon of the house is a black ship on a pale grey background, with an onion on its sails. Although their keep is in the stormlands, they are sworn not to House Barateon of Storms End but to House Barateon of Cmačyny Kamień in the crownlands.

House Tarharyjen is a noble family of Valyrian descent, who once ruled the Seven Kingdoms of Westeros. They were the royal house of the Kingdom of the Isles and Rivers and the Kingdom of the Rock before they conquered the rest of the continent with their dragons. House Tarharyjens sigil is a three-headed dragon on a black background, and their words are Fire and Blood. Their seat was the Red Keep in Kings Landing, until it was destroyed by dragonfire during the War of the Five Kings.

The Maegyr family is a wealthy and powerful family in the Free City of Volantis, known for their control of the slave trade. They are one of the oldest and most prestigious families in the city, tracing their lineage back to the ancient Valyrian Freehold. The Maegyrs are known for their silver-gold hair and violet eyes, which are seen as marks of their Valyrian ancestry.

Once known as the Red Kings , House Bolton was one of the Starki main and strongest rivals in the North. Feared because of their habit of flaying men and taking pride in flying Starki. It is said there is a room in the Dreadfort where flayed skins of their enemies are displayed.

The Antaryon family is a wealthy trading family from the Free City of Braavos, known for their control of the shipping and maritime trade in the Narrow Sea. They are considered one of the most powerful and influential of the Braavosi trading families, and have amassed a great fortune through their business ventures. The Antaryons are known for their fair hair and sea-green eyes.

The Aloran family is a minor noble house from the Free City of Lys, known for their expertise in shipbuilding and naval warfare. They are considered skilled shipwrights and sailors, and are often hired by other Free Cities to build and crew their warships. The Alorans have a reputation for being fiercely independent and proud, and are known for their bright red hair and golden eyes.

The Paenymion clan is a nomadic tribe that roams the deserts of Essos, primarily in the region known as the Red Waste. They are known for their expertise in survival and their ability to navigate the harsh desert terrain. They are also skilled warriors and are feared by many in the region.

House Selmy of Harvest Hall is one of the principal noble houses from the Stormlands. Its seat is Harvest Hall in the Dornish Marches. They blazon their arms with three stalks of yellow wheat on brown. Ser Barrystan Sełmi, also known as Barristan the Bold, is one of the greatest knights of the Kingsguard. Barristan is the eldest son of Ser Lyonel Selmy. He was in line to inherit the seat of House Selmy, but Barristan gave up his claim after he became a member of the Kingsguard. His cousin, who married the girl destined for Barristan, may also have taken over Barristans claim to Harvest Hall.

The Vhassar clan is a powerful and wealthy merchant family from the Free City of Volantis. They are one of the most influential families in the city and are involved in many aspects of its politics and commerce. They are known for their shrewd business acumen and their ability to navigate the complex web of alliances and rivalries that exist in Volantis.

The Celeris clan is a group of skilled horse breeders and riders from the Dothraki Sea. They are known for their expertise in breeding and training the fastest and strongest horses in the region, which they use to raid and conquer neighboring tribes. They are also skilled fighters and are feared by many in the region for their ferocity and their ability to strike quickly and unexpectedly.

House Nymeros Martell of Sunspear, usually simply called House Martell, is one of the Great Houses of the Seven Kingdoms and the ruling house of Dorne. Nymeros indicates of the line of Nymeria referring to the union of the Martells with the Rhoynish warrior queen Nymeria around 700 BC. The Prince of Dorne rules from Sunspear in southeastern Dorne. The Martells of old used a spear as their emblem, while Nymeria and her Rhoynar used the sun as theirs. When Nymeria wed Lord Mors Martell, the symbols were combined into a gold spear piercing a red sun on an orange field. Their words are Unbowed, Unbent, Unbroken. House Martell was founded by Morgan Martell, an Andalski adventurer who settled between the mouth of the Greenblood and the Broken Arm during the coming of the Andals to Dorne. Morgan led the defeat of the local First Men, including Houses Wade and Shell, establishing his rule over a strip of land fifty leagues long and ten leagues wide. They did not rule as kings, but were cautious vassals of kings from Houses Jordayne, Allyrion, and Yronwood, as well as petty kings of the Greenblood. At the time of the Rhoynish Wars, the Martells were one of the lesser ruling families of Dorne. At the time of the arrival of the Rhoynish warrior queen Nymeria, around 700 BC, the lands of the Martells were dwarfed by those of House Yronwood. Mors Martell, the Lord of the Sandship, saw an opportunity in the arrival of the Rhoynar, and took Nymeria to wife. Combining their strength, the two managed to unite all of Dorne under their rule in Nymerias War.

The Drahar are a wealthy and influential family from the city of Meereen in Slavers Bay. They are one of the most prominent of the citys Great Masters, and were among the leaders of the citys ruling council prior to Daenerys Tarharyjens conquest of the city.

The Mopatis family is a wealthy and influential family from the city of Pentos. They are known to have close ties with the Tarharyjen family, and are rumored to have provided financial support to Viserys Tarharyjen during his years of exile in the Free Cities.

House Vaith of the Red Dunes is a Dornish noble house. Their seat, also named Vaith, is placed on the river with the same name. West of Vaith are the deep sands of Dorne; the head of House Vaith has the title Lord of the Red Dunes. The Vaiths were adventuring Andals who settled in the hills east of the deep dunes and sands of Dorne. The nearby river soon took their name.

House Yronwood is the most powerful house in Dorne after the ruling Martells. Their seat, Yronwood, is the last fortress defending the Boneway; this is reflected in their title Warden of the Stone Way. House Yronwood claimed the title High King of Dorne before the arrival of the Rhoynar, and the head of the house continues to be called the Bloodroyal.

The Ormollen family is a powerful family from the city of Qarth, known for their wealth and their extensive trade network. They are one of the Thirteen ruling families of Qarth, and are said to have a great deal of influence in the citys politics and commerce.

House Manwoody of Kingsgrave is an old Dornish noble house. Its seat, Kingsgrave, is placed amidst the Princes Pass, guarding access to Dorne. They blazon their banners with a white skull with a golden crown, over a black field. The arms of the house and the name of its castle refer to the fact that the founder of the house slew there a King of the Miaža.

The Ryndoon family is a noble family from the Vale of Arryn, known for their skills in archery and hunting. They are sworn to House Royce, and are said to be among the finest hunters in the Vale. The Ryndoons are also known for their martial prowess, and are said to have a long history of service in the armies of the Vale.

The Moharis are a nomadic people that live in the Red Waste, a vast desert located to the east of the Dothraki Sea. They are known for their skill in trading and their ability to survive in harsh environments. The Moharis are a peaceful people, but they will fiercely defend themselves and their trade caravans if necessary.

The Lannisters have ruled over the Westerlands for thousands of years and have become very wealthy in the process and are easily the wealthiest House in Westeros. Legends say it was founded by Lann the clever during the rule of the First Men Kings.

House Tarly of Horn Hill is a noble house of the Miaža, one of the strongest sworn to House Tajreł. Horn Hill is located in the foothills of the Red Mountains. Their sigil is the striding huntsman on green. Their motto is First in Battle. Marcher lords of the Dornish Marches, the Tarlys are a family old in honor with rich lands and a strong keep. They are also the keepers of a Valyrian greatsword called Heartsbane.

House Arryn of the Eyrie is one of the Great Houses of Westeros, and is the principal noble house in the Vale of Arryn. Their main seat is the Eyrie, which is considered impregnable and it sits astride the Giants Lance, the tallest mountain in the Vale, the Gates of the Moon at its foot, the Eyrie at its top. The Arryn sigil is a sky-blue falcon soaring upwards, outlined against a white moon on a sky-blue field, and their words are As High as Honor. The Arryns are considered to come from the oldest and purest line of Andalski nobility, which they say reaches back to Andalos and possibly Hugor of the Hill. The Andals of the Vale united behind Ser Artys Arryn, the Falcon Knight, a native Valeman esteemed amongst his peers as the finest warrior of his day. Songs of the Vale conflate Artys with the legendary Winged Knight, who is said to have slain the Griffin King atop the Giants Lance. The First Men who did not accept Artys as their king were forced into the Mountains of the Moon, becoming the Vale mountain clans.

House Hightower of the Hightower is one of the most powerful of the noble houses in the Miaža. Their seat is the Hightower, located in the city of Oldtown. The sigil of House Hightower is a stone white watchtower, with a fire on the top. Their motto is We Light the Way. They possess a Valyrian steel sword called Vigilance. The Hightowers are among the oldest and proudest of the Great Houses. They have often preferred trade instead of war, and have also avoided many wars because of their support for the Faith of the Seven. The Hightowers can be legitimately referred to as being either of Hightower or of Oldtown.

House Clegane is a house of landed knights in the westerlands. They hold fealty to House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli, and are among their primary bannermen. The first Clegane of House Clegane was kennelmaster at Skała Kasterli. During one autumn year he saved Lord Tytos Łańnistar from a lioness, although he lost a leg and three dogs while doing so. Lord Tytos rewarded him with lands and a towerhouse. Ser Cleganes son was placed in Tytoss service as his squire. For his sigil Ser Clegane used the three dogs he lost saving Tytos, on the yellow of autumn grass.

House Lefford of the Golden Tooth is one of the principal houses sworn to House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli. The seat of the House is the Golden Tooth. House Lefford was formed by the union of an Andalski warlord with a noblewoman of the First Men. The Leffords presumably received the Golden Tooth when Cerion Łańnistar, King of the Rock, conquered the area.

House Kenning of Kayce is a noble house from the westerlands. House Kenning of Kayce was founded by Herrock Kenning, an ironborn warrior from House Kenning of Harlaw. During the decline of the driftwood kings of the ironborn, Herrock the Whoreson used his horn as a signal for the whores of Kayce to open a postern gate, allowing his men to take the town for House Łańnistar, the Kings of the Rock.

House Swyft of Cornfield is a knightly house from Cornfield in the westerlands. They are among the principal houses sworn to House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli. It was once a full fledged noble house. Ser Addison Hill was a member of the Kingsguard, and Lord Commander of the Kingsguard, during Aegon I Tarharyjens rule and was a legendary member.

House Crakehall of Crakehall is one of the primary noble houses from the westerlands. Their seat, Crakehall, is located along the Ocean Road between the Sunset Sea and a large forest. The Crakehalls are a house of First Men origin who claim descent from Crake the Boarkiller from the Age of Heroes.
House Rykker of Duskendale is a noble house from the crownlands. Their sigil depicts two black warhammers crossed on a white saltire on blue. Their seat is the castle of the Dun Fort in Duskendale.

House Redwyne of the Arbor is one of the main noble houses sworn to Vysokisad. Their seat is the Arbor, an island located off the southwestern-most part of Westeros, known for making the best wines in Westeros. The Redwynes control the Redwyne fleet, the largest fleet in Westeros, containing two hundred warships and five times as many merchant carracks, wine cogs, trading galleys, and whalers. The sigil of House Redwyne is a burgundy grape cluster on blue, symbolizing the famed wines of the Arbor.

The Kings of Winter, Warden of the North, Starki of Minańnie Zimy all of these are names and titles the Starki have held. Founded by Brandon the Builder, one of the most famous names in history, was said to have built the wall, Minańnie Zimy and other important places throughout Westeros like the Hightower and Storms End as well. House Stark untied the North through marriage and conquest. They are known to be a superstitious lot, holding on to the beliefs of the Old Gods and a strong sense of honor. It is said that Stark men are built sterner than others and history seems to prove that fact as many Starki have been both large and deadly fighters that inspire loyalty.

The Mormonts are a noble house from the island of Miadźviedžaja Vyspa, located in the North. They are known for their loyalty to House Stark and their fierce warriors. The Mormonts have a long tradition of sending their sons to the Nights Watch, a military order that guards the Wall and protects the Seven Kingdoms from the dangers that lie beyond. The Mormonts have a strong connection to the Nights Watch and have produced several notable members, including Jeor Mormont, the 997th Lord Commander.

House Reed of Greywater Watch is a noble house from Greywater Watch, and one of the principal families in the north. They rule the crannogmen, small men who live in the swamps and marshes of the Neck. the Reeds descend from the First Men. The Reeds first swore their oaths of fealty to House Stark when the Starki were Kings in the North, thousands of years ago. House Reed has led the crannogmen of the Neck since the defeat of the Marsh Kings by the Starki. Howland Reed was one of the six companions of Lord Eddard Stark who went with him to the Red Mountains of Dorne, and the only one who survived the ensuing combat at the tower of joy. Eddard said that he would not have survived the battle if it were not for Howland. Howland is said to have remained in the Neck since the end of Roberts Rebellion.

House of White Harbor is a noble family in the north whose seat is the New Castle in the city of White Harbor. They are among the most powerful and loyal vassals of House Stark as well as the richest northern family due to their control of the only city in the region. Unlike most other northern houses, the Manderlys follow the Faith of the Seven instead of the old gods, as the family emigrated from the Miaža after the coming of the Andals. The Manderlys are an ancient line who once lived along the banks of the mighty river Mander in the Kingdom of the Miaža, and some claim the river was named after them. A noble house of great lords descended from the First Men, they held the castle of Dunstonbury as their seat and had a fierce rivalry with House Peake. At some point, House overreached itself, and was driven from the Miaža by the Gardener Kings. According to Maester Yandel, the exile of House is credited to Lord Lorimar Peake upon the behest of King Perceon III Gardener, who feared the Manderlys growing influence and power in the Miaža. They fled north, and were welcomed by the Starki of Minańnie Zimy as their own bannermen. The Starki awarded the Wolfs Den to the Manderlys and tasked them with defending the White Knife in return for swearing an oath that they would always be loyal subjects of House Stark. This history instilled the Manderlys with great loyalty to their new liege lords.

House Umber is an ancient house who once ruled as First Men kings. After many struggles, the Umbers were reduced from royals to vassals of House Stark, the Kings of Winter. Amongst other possibilities, the Nights King is rumored to have been an Umber. House Umber of the Last Hearth is a noble house from the Last Hearth in the north. The Umbers proximity to the Wall puts them at risk of wildling raids and they have often been called upon to help defend the north against wildling raiders. The Umbers joined the Starki in defeating Gendel and Gorne, brother Kings-Beyond-the-Wall, three thousand years ago. Although the Umbers deny it, Roose Bolton claims they still practice the tradition of the lords right to the first night, which was banned during the reign of King Jaehaerys I Tarharyjen. The Umbers control land along the Bay of Seals, south of the New Gift and extending west to the kingsroad. Their lands include the northern Last River and the Lonely Hills. The kingsroad runs along the western marches of Umber territory for a hundred leagues. Most of their land is east of the kingsroad, but the Umbers graze their sheep in the high meadows of the northern mountains in summer.

Snow is the surname given to bastards born in the North. Džon Śnieh, the most famous member of this clan, is the bastard son of Eddard Stark, the Lord of Minańnie Zimy. Jon was raised at Minańnie Zimy with his half-siblings, but always felt like an outsider due to his status as a bastard. He eventually joined the Nights Watch, where he rose through the ranks and became Lord Commander. Jon is known for his bravery and his commitment to protecting the realm from its enemies.

House Glover of Deepwood Motte located in the Northern Wolfswood. They were once kings of the Wolfswood. The Glovers ruled as First Men kings after the Long Night, but they were eventually reduced to vassals by the Kings of Winter from House Stark
