House Mormont of Miadźviedžaja Vyspa is a noble house of the north, one of the principal families sworn to House Stark. Their seat is at Miadźviedžaja Vyspa, located in the Bay of Ice northwest of Minańnie Zimy. Their blazon is a black bear over a green wood and their motto is Here We Stand. House Mormont is one of the few houses to have an ancestral weapon of Valyrian steel: a bastard sword called Longclaw. However, due to Miadźviedžaja Vyspas lack of valuable resources, the Mormonts are a rather poor house. Their hall is made of huge logs, surrounded by an earthen palisade. On the gate is a carving of a woman in a bearskin with a child in one arm suckling at her breast and a battleaxe in the other. The Mormonts are an old house with a proud and honorable reputation. According to northern histories, Rodrik Stark, a King in the North, gave Miadźviedžaja Vyspa to the Mormonts after winning the isle in a wrestling match from a Driftwood King of the Žaleznanarodžany.

The Pono are a tribe of the Dothraki people, a nomadic group that roams the grasslands of Essos. The Pono are known for their skilled riders and their fierce warriors. They are often hired as mercenaries by various factions in Essos, and have a reputation for being difficult to control. Despite their violent nature, the Pono have a strong sense of honor and loyalty to their tribe and its leaders.

The Second Sons is a sellsword company operating in Essos. They are considered one of the most famous and reputable sellsword companies, with a reputation for never breaking a contract. The company is led by a captain-general who is elected by the companys members. The Second Sons are known for their skill with the crossbow.

Quarro is a Dothraki warrior and member of Khal Ponos khalasar. Quarro is a skilled warrior and tracker, with a reputation for being one of the most dangerous riders in the khalasar. He is a close friend and advisor to Khal Pono.

Jhago is a Dothraki warrior and member of Khal Drogos khalasar. Jhago is a fierce and skilled warrior, with a reputation for being one of the most dangerous riders in the khalasar. He is fiercely loyal to Khal Drogo and is known for his distinctive braid of black horsehair.

House Talordis is a noble house from the Free Cities. The house is known for its skill in shipbuilding and its extensive trading network. The Talordis family is heavily involved in the slave trade, and is considered one of the wealthiest and most powerful families in the Free Cities.
The Moro are a Dothraki khalasar led by Khal Moro. They were once loyal to Khal Drogo, but after his death, they became a separate khalasar.

The Stormcrows are a sellsword company led by Daario Naharis. They are known for their distinctive blue-and-white uniforms, and they fight with spears, swords, and crossbows. They were hired by Daenerys Tarharyjen to help her conquer the cities of Slavers Bay.

The Forzho are a Dothraki khalasar that follow the ancient ways of the Dothraki. They do not use weapons made of metal, but instead fight with weapons made of bone and stone. They are led by Khal Jhaqo, who once served under Khal Drogo.

The Adory are a noble house from the Free City of Lys. They are known for their skill in producing and trading in slaves, and for their support of the slave trade. They are one of the wealthiest families in Lys, and have a reputation for being ruthless in their business dealings.

House Greyjoy of Pyke is one of the Great Houses of Westeros. It rules over the Iron Islands, a harsh and bleak collection of forbidding islands off the west coast of Westeros, from the Seastone Chair in the castle of Pyke on the island of the same name. The head of the family is traditionally known as the Lord Reaper of Pyke. Their sigil is a golden kraken on a black field, and their house motto is We Do Not Sow. The Greyjoys of Pyke claim descent from the Grey King of the Age of Heroes. Lord Balon Greyjoy, rejected his fathers reforms and desired a return to the Old Way. He created the Iron Fleet and led his own rebellion against the Žalezny Tron, declaring himself King of the Iron Islands. His brothers Euron and Victarion led the burning of the Łańnistar fleet at anchor. After suffering defeats and the loss of sons and brothers Balon bent the knee to Robert and swore fealty to the Žalezny Tron once more. His last surviving son, the nine-year-old Theon, was given into the care of Lord Stark as a hostage to ensure Balons good behavior.

Mans Najeźnik, known as the King-Beyond-the-Wall, was a wildling leader and former member of the Nights Watch. He united the disparate clans of the far north and led them in a massive invasion south of the Wall. His ultimate goal was to settle his people in the Seven Kingdoms beyond the Wall. Despite initially achieving a number of victories, his army was ultimately defeated by the Nights Watch and their allies.

House Harlaw is one of the most powerful houses from the Iron Islands, sworn to House Greyjoy of Pyke. From the castle of Ten Towers, the Harlaws rule over the entire island of Harlaw, the richest and most populous of the isles.

House Dayne is a noble house from Starfall and High Hermitage in Dorne. They are among the principal houses sworn to House Martell. The Mieč of the Morning is a title given to a Dayne knight who is considered worthy of wielding the greatsword Dawn, a blade said to be created from the heart of falling star. Their blazon is a white sword and a falling star, crossing on a lavender background. Currently the young Lord, Edric Dayne is away serving as a squire to Lord Beric Dondarrion, which leaves Starfall under the care of Lady Allyria Dayne. A cadet branch of the family are the Daynes of High Hermitage and are led by Ser Gerold Dayne also known as the Darkstar.

Styr was a Thenn warrior and leader of the Thenn tribe. He was known as the Magnar, which is the Thenn title for their leader. Unlike many other Adzičełyja, the Thenns were organized and had a social hierarchy. Styr was a fierce warrior and was feared throughout the Seven Kingdoms for his brutality. He fought in the Battle of Čorny Zamak and was ultimately killed by Džon Śnieh.

Founded as a cadet branch of the Starki and one of the principal bannermen. Founded by Karlon Stark The Karstarks descend from Karlon Stark, a younger son of Minańnie Zimy. Possibly around 700 BC, Karlon put down a rebel lord and was granted lands for his valor. The castle he built near the Grey Cliffs was named Karls Hold, but that soon became Karhold, and over the centuries the Karhold Starki became Karstarks. Their blazon is a white sunburst on black and their motto is The Sun of Winter.
Tormund, often called Tormund Praklon Vołataŭ or Tormund Thunderfist, is a famous free folk raider from Ruddy Hall. He has four sons, Toregg, Torwynd, Dryn, and Dormund, and one daughter, Munda.

House Goodbrother of Hammerhorn is a noble house from the Iron Islands. They are one of the most powerful houses from Great Wyk, the largest of the islands, and are one of House Greyjoys primary bannermen. Their keep of Hammerhorn is inland, in the Hardstone Hills, their wealth not coming from the Sunset Sea but from their mines.

Ser Barrystan Sełmi, also known as Barristan the Bold, was one of the greatest knights of the Seven Kingdoms. He served as Lord Commander of the Kingsguard under King Robert Barateon and his successors Džoffry Barateon and Tommen Barateon. Barristan was renowned for his chivalry and honor, and was considered one of the greatest swordsmen in Westeros. He was ultimately dismissed from the Kingsguard by Džoffry Barateon, but later returned to serve Daenerys Tarharyjen.

Džoffry Barateon was the eldest son of King Robert Barateon and Queen Cerseja Łańnistar. He was initially believed to be the legitimate heir to the Žalezny Tron, but it was later revealed that he was actually the product of an incestuous relationship between Cerseja and her brother Jaime Łańnistar. Džoffry was cruel and sadistic, and was despised by many of his subjects. He was ultimately poisoned at his own wedding feast, in an event known as the Purple Wedding.

House Mormont is a noble house from Miadźviedžaja Vyspa, a remote island located in the Bay of Ice. Džorach Marmont is the lord of Miadźviedžaja Vyspa and the head of House Mormont. Jorah is a former knight and lord of Miadźviedžaja Vyspa who was exiled after selling poachers into slavery to provide for his wife. He became a sellsword in Essos before eventually ending up in the service of Daenerys Tarharyjen as an advisor.

Qhorin Halfhand is a legendary ranger of the Nights Watch. He earned his nickname after losing his fingers on his sword hand, and had his remaining fingers bound to his sword hand with a leather strap. Qhorin is known for his skill in combat and his knowledge of the Adzičełyja, having spent time as a captive among them. He led the mission to scout out Mans Najeźniks army and is rumored to have sacrificed himself to Džon Śnieh in order to get Jon into Mances army.

House Tallhart of Torrhens Square is a noble house from the north and is among the principal houses sworn to House Stark. Ser Helman Tallhart is the Master of Torrhens Square, which is located southwest of Minańnie Zimy. Their arms show three green sentinel trees, over a brown field. The Tallharts descend from the First Men

House Cerwyn of Cerwyn is a noble house from the north. They are one of the closest bannermen to the Starki, Castle Cerwyn being just a half days ride from Minańnie Zimy, and are among the most powerful as well. Their blazon is a black battle-axe on silver. Lord Cerwyn was believed to have been the closest friend of Cregan Stark, Lord of Minańnie Zimy and Warden of the North. Lord Cerwyn supported the blacks during the Dance of the Dragons and was at court in Kings Landing during the Hour of the Wolf.

House Hornwood of Hornwood is a noble house whose seat is Hornwood in the north. They are among the principal bannermen of Starki of Minańnie Zimy. Their sigil is a bull moose, brown on a field of dark orange. Their words are Righteous in Wrath. The lands of the house, which include the forest of the Hornwood and other castles beside Hornwood, border those of House Bolton and House . The Hornwoods lands extend west to the White Knife. Their ruler is known as the Lord of the Hornwood. Lord Hornwood declared for the blacks in the Dance of the Dragons. In late 130 AC he left the north and marched towards Kings Landing as part of the army led by his liege lord, Lord Cregan Stark. Once in the capital, his younger son disappeared in Flea Bottom during the Hour of the Wolf. Hallis Hornwood and Timotty Snow founded the Wolf Pack after the Dance of the Dragons.

House Dustin of Barrowton is a noble house from the north, one of the major families sworn to House Stark. Their castle is Barrow Hall in Barrowton, a prominent town in the north. The current head of the house is the widow Lady Barbrey Dustin, a Ryswell by birth. The Dustins claim descent from the First King of the First Men and the Barrow Kings of the barrowlands who ruled after him. When the last Barrow King submitted to House Stark of Minańnie Zimy at the end of the Thousand Years War, the King of Winter took his daughter for wife. House Dustins claims of shared blood and descent from the Barrow Kings is regarded as truth. Barrowton has prospered under the Dustins, who have loyally ruled the barrowlands for the Starki. House Dustin fought for the House Tarharyjen during the War of the Ninepenny Kings. Brandon Stark, heir to Lord Rickard Stark, was fostered at Barrowton by old Lord Dustin, though he spent most of his time in the Rills. Though Lord Rodrik Ryswell sought to wed his daughter Barbrey to Brandon, she would end up marrying Lord Willam Dustin, the son of the old Lord of Barrowton. Six months after their wedding, Lord Willam followed his liege Lord Eddard Stark in Roberts Rebellion against King Aerys II Tarharyjen. Lord Dustin was one of the six companions that fought alongside Lord Eddard at the tower of joy against the remaining members of the Mad Kings Kingsguard, where he was slain. His bones were buried beneath the red mountains of Dorne. While Lord Eddard returned Willams stead, he did not return his bones. Taking it as a slight, Lady Dustin held a grudge on the Starki and grew bitter with her overlords.
Harma the Dogshead, is a captain in Mans Najeźniks army, commanding the vanguard. Before Mans Najeźnik made peace between them, Harma once warred with Rattleshirt.

Varamyr Sixskins is a wildling skinchanger who is capable of controlling multiple animals at the same time. He is one of the most powerful skinchangers in the North, and was once the mentor to Džon Śniehs direwolf Ghost. After failing to take control of Džon Śniehs body, Varamyr dies and his spirit is trapped inside his wolf, One-Eye.

House Botley of Lordsport is a noble house from the Iron Islands, one of the principal houses sworn to the Greyjoys. Their seat of Lordsport is located on the island of Pyke, at the opposite side of the Greyjoys keep of Pyke.

House Borrell is a noble house from Sweetsister, a group of islands located in the Bite. The Borrells are known for their seafaring abilities and have a reputation as fierce fighters. Lord Godric Borrell is the head of House Borrell and the ruler of Sweetsister. He is a skilled sailor and a loyal vassal of House Stark.

House Grafton of Gulltown is a noble house from the Vale of Arryn, one of the main families sworn to House Arryn of the Eyrie. They rule over Gulltown, a main port and populated city, as well as the only city in the Vale. The Graftons were founded during the coming of the Andals to the Vale. Ser Gerold Grafton (the first of his name) was an Andalski knight from Andalos who supported King Osgood III Shett of Gulltown in battle against House Royce, marrying his daughters to Shett and his heir, while taking King Osgoods daughter to wife. While the Shetts defeated the Royces, Osgood III did not survive the battle.
House Paege is a noble house of landed knights sworn to Biahučajaraka in the riverlands.
The Coxes are a lesser house of the Račnyje Ziemli, vassals to House Frey. They are a small clan, mostly known for their fishing, hunting, and gathering along the rivers of the region.
House Bar Emmon of Sharp Point is a noble house from Sharp Point in the crownlands. They are sworn directly to Cmačyny Kamień.
House Celtigar rules Claw Isle, an island in the narrow sea off the coast of Crackclaw Point. The Celtigars are historically sworn to Cmačyny Kamień within the crownlands.

House Fell of Felwood is a noble house sworn to Storms End. Their seat is Felwood in the northern stormlands. During Aegons Conquest, Lords Fell, Errol, and Buckler ambushed Orys Barateons host as he crossed the Wendwater. The lords later hid in the kingswood, but Rhaenys Tarharyjen set the forests ablaze with Meraxes. At the beginning of Roberts Rebellion, Lord Fell remained loyal to the Žalezny Tron and together with Lords Grandison and Cafferen planned to join their forces to bring Lord Robert Barateons head to King Aerys II Tarharyjen. Robert defeated them in three battles at Summerhall, slaying Lord Fell in single combat and capturing his son Silveraxe, who turned to Roberts side afterwards.

House Connington of Griffins Roost is a house of landed knights from Griffins Roost in the stormlands, sworn to Storms End. It was formerly a lordly house whose lands once extended many leagues west, north, and south of Griffins Roost, including reaching near to the rainwood. When Robert Barateon was crowned king after the death of Aerys, he allowed Ronald to keep Griffins Roost, but the Conningtons lost their lordship and nine-tenths of their land was distributed among neighbors who were more fervent in their support of Robert. House Conningtons status thus fell from being a full noble house to landed knights. Members of House Connington tend to have red hair.

House Whitehead of Weeping Town is a noble house from the Stormlands, sworn to House Barateon. They are known for their naval skills, as the lords of Weeping Town have been admirals for generations. The Whiteheads maintain a small fleet of warships, which they use to protect their town from raiders and pirates.

House Rowan of Goldengrove is one of the most prominent and old families from the Miaža, its dominions extending all along its northern borders. This may mean that the Rowans were made Marshall of the Northmarch to replace the declining House Osgrey, now their bannermen. Their blazon is a golden tree on silver. Like several other major Miaža houses, the Rowans can trace their descent from the legendary Garth Greenhand, through his daughter Rowan Gold-Tree.

House Uller of Hellholt is one of the great noble houses in Dorne. Their keep, the Hellholt, is in the middle of the Dornish desert, and they are reputed to be impulsive and unpredictable. The Ullers were Andalski adventurers who settled along the Brimstone. The Hellholt is named after an event in which rivals were invited to the castle, locked within, and burned to death. This action inspired the Ullers arms. The Ullers supported House Nymeros Martell against House Yronwood during Nymerias War. After the death of her first husband, Nymeria was married to Lord Uller and then to Ser Davos Dayne, her final husband. Their arms are rayonne yellow over crimson.

The Uhorises are a clan of free folk living north of the Wall. They are skilled hunters and gatherers, and are known for their ability to survive in the harsh northern climate. They are a peaceful people, and generally avoid conflict with the Nights Watch and other groups in the region.

House Vaelaro of Volantis is a noble house from the Free City of Volantis, one of the wealthiest and most powerful cities in the known world. The Vaelaros are known for their wealth and influence, as they control much of the citys trade and commerce. They are a family of merchants and bankers, with interests in everything from spices and silks to slaves and mercenaries.

The Hortyr are a wildling clan that roams the Frostfangs, a mountain range in the far north beyond the Wall. They are known for their ferocity and skill at hunting and raiding. Their warriors often wear bone armor and wield weapons made from stone or bone. The Hortyr are fiercely independent and have resisted attempts to unite the wildling clans under a single leader.

The Saldorys are a powerful family of merchants from the city of Qarth in the eastern continent of Essos. They are known for their wealth and influence, and are heavily involved in the spice trade. The Saldorys maintain a private fleet of ships to transport their goods across the seas, and have strong connections to other wealthy families throughout the Free Cities.

The Phassar are a nomadic clan of Dothraki riders who roam the vast grasslands of the Dothraki Sea. They are known for their horsemanship and their mastery of the bow, and are feared by many for their ruthless raids on neighboring lands. The Phassar are fiercely independent and have little respect for the authority of the Dothraki khals who rule over other clans.

The Vaelaros are a noble Valyrian family from the city of Volantis in the eastern continent of Essos. They are known for their wealth and influence, and have played a prominent role in the political and economic life of the city for generations. The Vaelaros are staunch supporters of the Old Blood, the descendants of the ancient Valyrian dragonlords who once ruled over much of the world.

House Heggo of the North is a minor noble house that controls land in the northern part of the Wolfswood. They are a relatively new house, having been granted lands and titles by House Stark for their support during the recent conflicts in the North. The Heggo family is known for their skilled hunters and woodsmen, and they are fiercely loyal to House Stark.

The Stalwart Shields are a clan of mountain people from the Mountains of the Moon in the Vale of Arryn. They are known for their exceptional skill in the use of the bow and their fierce loyalty to the Arryns. They are often hired as mercenaries by House Arryn to defend the Vale against outside threats. The Stalwart Shields have a reputation for being honorable and courageous warriors, and they are feared by their enemies.
Vajskovy orden, jaki słužyć voli Vyšejšaha Septona i zabiaśpiečvaje vykanańnie słovaŭ Siamikancovaj Zorki siłaj zbroi.
Banda złačyncaŭ, čyjoj metaj zjaŭlajecca abarona prostych ludziej ad razburalnych vojnaŭ šlachty.
Adna z šmatlikich kampanijaŭ najomnych miačoŭ Uschodaskaha pachodžańnia.
Kampanija najomnych miačoŭ, uźnikšaja na Uschodasie, sumna viadomaja svajoj lutaściu.
Hornaje plemia z Horaŭ Miesiaca, jakoje žyvie ŭ kraju, zaraz viadomym jak Dalina Arryn.
Hornaje plemia z Horaŭ Miesiaca, jakoje žyvie ŭ kraju, zaraz viadomym jak Dalina Arryn.
Kampanija volnych najeźnikaŭ z Uschodasa, jakaja, pa čutkach, maje prynamsi 800 końnikaŭ.
Kampanija najomnych miačoŭ z Uschodasa jakaja, pa čutkach, maje prynamsi 1000 końnikaŭ i piachotnikaŭ.
Banda maładych vajaroŭ, jakija hojsajuć pa sielskaj miascovaści i piajuć rycarskija pieśni.
Kampanija najmitaŭ, što, u asnoŭnym, dziejničaje ŭ Volnych Haradach i na Uschodasie.
Padpolnaja paŭstanckaja hrupa, jakaja składajecca z rabaŭłaśnikaŭ.
House Flint of Flints Finger is a noble house from Flints Finger in the southwest of the north. They are a cadet branch with ancestry tracing back to the Mountain Clans of the North.

House Forrester is a noble house from the wolfswood in the north. It is sworn to House Glover of Deepwood Motte. Their seat is Ironrath, and their words are Iron from Ice. They control the majority of the ironwood forests in the wolfswood, much to the chagrin of their bitter rivals, House Whitehill. Ironrath was built over fifteen hundred years ago by Cedric Forrester and his triplet sons, Ironrath is a testament to the strength and endurance of ironwood. Ironrath sits on the edge of the largest ironwood forest in Westeros, which has proven to be a strategic advantage for the House.

One of the few houses in the North that practices the Faith of the Seven and had access to Ironwood. Due to overharvesting however the Ironwood grove they oversaw is now nearly depleted and they lust over House Forresters Ironwood. The head of House Whitehill is also the Lord of Highpoint.

House Greyjoy of Pyke is a major noble house from the Iron Islands. They are known for their seafaring skills and their fierce independence. The Greyjoys follow the Drowned God and are traditionally a raiding culture, although they have also become skilled traders in recent years. They are ruled by Lord Balon Greyjoy, who has recently launched a rebellion against the Žalezny Tron in an effort to reestablish the independence of the Iron Islands.

House Dalba is a minor noble house from the Westerlands. They are known for their skill in metalworking and are often called upon by the larger noble houses to craft their armor and weapons. The Dalba family is also known for their strong ties to House Łańnistar, and they have been loyal vassals to the Lannisters for generations. Despite their minor status, the Dalbas are a proud and honorable family, and they are respected by many in the Westerlands for their craftsmanship and loyalty.

House Ryswell of the Rills is a noble family of the north, one of the prominent houses sworn to House Stark of Minańnie Zimy. The Ryswells rule the Rills, the extensive area between the barrowlands, the Stony Shore, and Blazewater Bay in the north. House Ryder were First Men kings who ruled the Rills and eventually submitted to House Stark, the Kings of Winter from Minańnie Zimy. It is unknown how or when House Ryswell came to rule the Rills, although King Theon Stark once put down a rebellion in the Rills. An old story from before Aegons Conquest tells that when seventy-nine deserters left the Wall, one of them was the youngest son of Lord Ryswell, who decided to look for shelter at his fathers keep. However, Lord Ryswell returned his son and his companions to the Nightfort, where they were buried alive in the ice to forever stand the watch they had abandoned. Late in his life Lord Ryswell took the black to end his days watching behind his son.

The Flint, Lyessa clan is a minor clan in the North. They are loyal to House Stark and hold lands near the western coast of the North. The clan is known for its skilled hunters and foraging techniques in the dense forests and hilly terrain of the region.

House Stout of Goldgrass is a petty noble house from the north who have a modest keep near the eastern gate of Barrowton. It is sworn to House Dustin. They blazon their arms as chevronny russet and gold and their seat is named Goldgrass.
House Orkwood is a noble house from the Iron Islands, with its seat on the island of Orkmont. King Rognar II Greyiron was brought down by an alliance which included the Orkwoods.

House Blacktyde is a noble house from Blacktyde Castle on the island of Blacktyde, one of the seven major islands, though of little note. They are among the foremost bannermen to House Greyjoy, the overlords of the Iron Islands.

House Redfort of Redfort is one of the principal noble houses in the Vale of Arryn. They blazon their arms with a red castle on a white field within a red embattled border. The Redforts trace their descent to the First Men that inhabited the Vale before the coming of the Andals. The Redforts allied with Robar II Royce, High King of the Vale, the Fingers and the Mountains of the Moon, against the Andals. Robar was defeated in the Battle of the Seven Stars, however, and Torgold Tollett chopped off Lord Redforts arm during the battle. The Redforts submitted to Artys I Arryn and then served House Arryn, the Kings of Mountain and Vale.

House Belmore of Strongsong is a noble house from Strongsong in the Vale. They are one of the more powerful noble houses sworn to House Arryn. Their arms are six silver bells Members of House Belmore tend to have red hair. The Belmores are of First Man origin. During the Andalski invasion, they allied with Robar II Royce against the Andals. Robars forces were defeated in the Battle of the Seven Stars, however, and the Belmores submitted to Artys I Arryn, the new King of Mountain and Vale.

House Coldwater of Coldwater Burn is a noble house from Coldwater Burn in the Vale of Arryn. They are sworn to the Royces of Runestone. The Coldwaters are of First Men origin. During the coming of the Andals to the Vale, they allied with King Robar II Royce against the invading Andals. Robars forces were defeated in the Battle of the Seven Stars, however, and the Coldwaters submitted to Artys I Arryn, the new King of Mountain and Vale.

The Waxley clan is a minor clan from the Vale of Arryn. They are known for their skills in horsemanship and archery, and often serve as scouts and outriders for House Arryn. The clan holds lands near the Mountains of the Moon, and its members are fiercely loyal to the Arryns.

House Brax of Hornvale is a noble house from the westerlands, among the chief bannermen of House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli. Their seat is Hornvale. House Brax was established during the Andalski invasion through the marriage of First Men and Andalski nobles.

House Westerling of the Crag is a noble house from the Crag in the northwestern westerlands. They are sworn to House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli, and are considered among their principal bannermen. The Westerlings are an ancient and proud house descended from the First Men of the Age of Heroes.

An ancient house sworn to House Talli of the Račnyje Ziemli. They fought against the Andals when they invaded and lost, adopting the Faith of the Seven. They are bitter rivals with House Blackwood ever since they usurped their title as a River King in ancient history.

House Smallwood of Acorn Hall is a noble house from Acorn Hall in the riverlands. Their sigil is six brown acorns on yellow. The lands of House Smallwood are near those that belonged to House Goodbrook.
House Vance rules over wider domains and can field a much larger army than their liege lords, House Talli.

House Darry is a noble house from Castle Darry in the riverlands. Historically it had been one of the more prominent and powerful houses of the Trident, until the fall of the Tarharyjeny in Roberts Rebellion. House Darry traces their rule to the days when the Andals cast down the First Men. During the coming of the Andals, three sons of Lord Darry held back the Andals of Vorian Vypren at the Widows Ford before being slain. During Roberts Rebellion, the Darrys defended King Aerys II Tarharyjen against Robert Barateon, Lord of Storms End, and their liege, Hoster Talli, Lord Paramount of the Trident. After the Battle of the Bells, Ser Jonothor Darry and Ser Barrystan Sełmi of the Kingsguard were sent to Stoney Sept to rally remants of the loyalist army of Jon Connington, Lord of Griffins Roost. The defeat of the Tarharyjeny cost the Darrys half of their lands, most of their wealth, and almost all their power.

House Rosby of Rosby is a noble house from the crownlands. They rule the castle of Rosby and its village, which are located just northeast of Kings Landing. The Rosbys are not known for their robustness. Their blazon consists into three red chevronels on ermine. House Rosby was one of the first houses to yield peacefully to House Tarharyjen during Aegons Conquest, surrendering to Rhaenys Tarharyjen and Meraxes. The Rosby lands became part of the crownlands surrounding Kings Landing. Lord Jon Rosby was named Warden of the Sands by King Aegon I Tarharyjen during the First Dornish War, but Jon was killed in the Defenestration of Sunspear.

House Brune is a house of landed knights from Brownhollow and Dyre Den, which are located in Crackclaw Point in the crownlands. The Brothers Brune were legendary champions who brought peace to Crackclaw.

The Staunton clan is a minor clan in the Stormlands. They are known for their skills as blacksmiths and armorers, and often supply House Barateon with weapons and armor. The clan holds lands near the Rainwood, and its members are respected for their craftsmanship and loyalty.

The Massey clan is a minor clan from the Crownlands. They are known for their skills as sailors and shipbuilders, and often serve as merchant traders and naval officers for House Tarharyjen. The clan holds lands near the Blackwater Bay, and its members are respected for their nautical expertise and loyalty to the Tarharyjeny.

House Errol of Haystack Hall is a noble house from Haystack Hall in the stormlands, one of the principal houses sworn to House Barateon. House Errol is one of the houses from the stormlands that supports Renli Barateon when the War of the Five Kings starts.

House Estermont of Greenstone is a noble house from Greenstone in the stormlands and is one of the principal houses sworn to House Barateon of Storms End. They rule the small island of Estermont east of Nakidka Wrath. It is as yet unconfirmed if the Estermonts are of First Men or Andalski ancestry. During the coming of the Andals, the Storm Kings from House Durrandon and many of their bannermen intermarried with Andals. Their arms depict a dark green sea turtle on pale green.
House Wylde of the Rain House is a noble house from the Rain House in the stormlands. They blazon their arms with a blue-green maelstrom on gold.

House Mertyns is a noble house from the Stormlands. Their seat, Mistwood, is a castle located along the coast of Shipbreaker Bay. They are sworn to House Barateon of Storms End. They have a history of good relations with the Dornish, and are one of the few houses that practice the Dornish custom of giving women the right to inherit their lands and titles.

House Dondarrion is a noble house from the Stormlands. Their seat, Blackhaven, is a castle located in the Dornish Marches. They are sworn to House Barateon of Storms End. Their sigil is a forked purple lightning bolt on a black field, and their words are Ours Is The Fury. They are known for their ancestral sword, a Valyrian steel blade named Dawn.

House Banefort of Banefort is a noble house from Banefort in the westerlands, one of the main families sworn to Skała Kasterli The Baneforts were petty First Men kings of the Age of Heroes, claiming descent from the Hooded Man. The last Hooded King was Morgon Banefort, whose thralls were defeated after twenty years of war by Loreon I Łańnistar, King of the Rock.

House Serrett of Silverhill is a noble house from Silverhill in the Westerlands. It is one of the principal houses sworn to Skała Kasterli. House Serrett was formed by the union of First Men and Andalski nobles during the Andalski invasion.

House Caswell of Bitterbridge is a noble house from the Miaža. Their seat is Bitterbridge, where the Roseroad meets the river Mander. Their blazon is a yellow centaur with bow on white. The Caswells carry the title Defender of the Fords.
House Beesbury of Honeyholt is a noble house from the Miaža, sworn to the Hightowers. Honeyholt is located next to the Honeywine river, which flows towards Oldtown and the Whispering Sound.

House Blackbar is a noble house from the Miaža. Their seat, Bandallon, is a castle located in the heart of the Miaža. They are sworn to House Tajreł of Vysokisad. Their sigil is a black fess on a yellow field, and their words are The Last To Yield. They are known for their skilled horsemen and their loyalty to House Tajreł.
House Cuy of Sunhouse is a noble house from Sunhouse in the Miaža, sworn to the Hightowers. Sunhouse is located by the town Cuy, along the coast southeast of Oldtown.

House Oakheart of Old Oak is an old and powerful family from Old Oak in the Miaža, one of the main houses sworn to House Tajreł. They are among the noble houses from the Miaža that can trace their descent from Garth Greenhand.

House Bulwer of Blackcrown is a noble house from the Miaža, sworn to the Hightowers. Blackcrown is located on the northern coast of Whispering Sound. Victaria and her family has taken to rule over Blackcrown until her daughter the heir of Jon Bulwer comes of age.

House Locke of Oldcastle is a noble house from Oldcastle in the north. The Lockes ruled as First Men kings after the Long Night, but they were eventually reduced to vassals by the Kings of Winter from House Stark. After the extinction of House Greystark, the Flints held the Wolfs Den for a century and the Lockes for almost two centuries.

House Blackmont of Blackmont is a major Dornish noble house. Their seat, Blackmont, is on the banks of the Torentine in the Red Mountains of Dorne. The Blackmonts have long fought against the marcher lords of the Dornish Marches to the north. King Benedict Blackmont was defeated in Nymerias War and was one of the six kings sent to the Wall by Nymeria. The Blackmonts also unsuccessfully supported House Yronwood against House Nymeros Martell during the war.

House Jordayne of the Tor is one of the principal noble houses of Dorne. The Tor is situated on the southern coast of the Sea of Dorne. Their blazon is a golden quill on checkered dark and light green. House Jordayne was founded during the coming of the Andals to Dorne, along with Houses Allyrion, Martell, Qorgyle, Santagar, House Uller, and Vaith. At some point, House Martell bent the knee to the Jordayne kings of the Tor. By the time of Nymerias War, House Jordayne was among the bannermen of King Yorick Yronwood, and they fought against Lord Mors Martell and his Rhoynar allies. During the first couple of years of the First Dornish War, King Aegon I Tarharyjen captured several Dornish castles, including the Tor, whose steward surrendered the castle peacefully to Aegon a short time after the death of Lord Jordayne. The Dornishmen quickly recaptured the castle in Aegons absence. In 8 AC, Queen Visenya Tarharyjen mounted on Vhagar, burned Sunspear, Lemonwood, Ghost Hill and the Tor in retaliation for the Dornishmens actions against the stormlands earlier that year. Their words are Let it be written.

House Toland of Ghost Hill is a Dornish noble house sworn to Sunspear, one of the House Martells principal bannermen. Its seat is Ghost Hill. Their arms depict a green dragon biting its tail on gold, the dragon symbolizing that time has no beginning and no end. The Tolands successfully resisted the dragons of Aegon the Conqueror during the First Dornish War. The Lord Toland at the time sent out his champion to face Aegon. After Aegon slew the man, he learned that the man was Lord Tolands mad fool, and that Lord Toland himself had escaped. In later days, the Tolands would take a new banner, showing a dragon biting its own tail, with the colors green in gold in memory of the motley of their brave fool. Prior to the dragon, the Toland banners displayed a ghost. The Dornishmen quickly recaptured Ghost Hill after Aegon left the castle. In 8 AC, Queen Visenya Tarharyjen mounted on Vhagar, burned Sunspear, Lemonwood, Ghost Hill and the Tor in retaliation for the dornishmens actions against the stormlands earlier that year. During the Dragons Wroth, Lady Toland was murdered for the Žalezny Trons ransom on her head.

House Wyl of the Boneway is a house from Wyl in northern Dorne. It is one of the principal houses sworn to House Martell of Sunspear. According to semi-canon sources, they blazon their banners with a black adder.

House Qorgyle of Sandstone is a noble house from Sandstone, located in the dunes of western Dorne. They are among the principal bannermen sworn to House Martell of Sunspear. The Qorgyles were adventuring Andals who established their domains in the unexplored Dornish deserts, settling in the deep dunes and sands of Dorne, fortifying the only well for fifty leagues around. By the time of Nymerias War, the Qorgyles were bannermen of House Yronwood. The Qorgyles supported King Yorick V Yronwood in his unsuccessful war against Lord Mors Martell and Princess Nymeria. Following the war, the Qorgyles became vassals of House Martell.

House Amai is a noble house from the eastern continent of Essos. They are based in the city of Qarth, one of the greatest trading cities in the world. They are known for their wealth and their expertise in trading with the far-off lands of the east, including Yi Ti, Asshai, and the Shadow Lands. They are a key player in the political and economic landscape of the region.

House Lozar is a noble house from the Free City of Braavos, located in the northern part of the city. They are a wealthy and influential family, known for their trade connections and banking operations throughout the Known World.

House Tymai is a powerful family from the city of Volantis, located in the eastern part of the Free Cities. They are a merchant family and one of the main backers of the tiger faction, which advocates for the restoration of the Valyrian Freehold.

House Qhaedarene is a wealthy family from the city of Qarth, located in the southern part of the Free Cities. They are known for their mastery of the trade routes between the Free Cities and the cities of the Slavers Bay region.

House Alayris is a noble family from the city of Lys, located in the western part of the Free Cities. They are a prominent family in the citys political and social scene, known for their influence in the slave trade and their connections to the powerful mage guilds of Lys.

House Pendaerys is a minor noble house in the crownlands. They are sworn to House Tarharyjen of Cmačyny Kamień. The Pendaerys family is known for their black hair and purple eyes, indicating a Valyrian descent. They are neither particularly rich nor particularly powerful, but they are proud of their Tarharyjen heritage and often seek to demonstrate their loyalty to the Tarharyjeny in various ways.

House Moesia is a small noble house from the Vale of Arryn. They are sworn to House Royce of Runestone. The Moesia family is known for their skill in archery and their mastery of falconry. They live in a modest keep surrounded by fields of wheat and barley. Although they are not particularly wealthy or powerful, they are respected by their neighbors for their honesty and loyalty.

House Prestayn is a noble house from the westerlands. They are sworn to House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli. The Prestayn family is known for their love of hunting and their skill with a spear. They live in a grand castle with high walls and towers, overlooking the sea. Although they are not as wealthy or powerful as some of the other noble houses in the westerlands, they are proud of their Łańnistar heritage and fiercely loyal to their liege lords.

The Dimittis clan is a minor house in the North. They are known for their skill as blacksmiths, and are often sought after to make weapons and armor for the other noble houses. The clan is loyal to House Stark, and has served the Starki for generations.

The Golathis clan is a powerful clan in the Iron Islands. They are fierce warriors and skilled sailors, and their ships are feared throughout the Seven Kingdoms. The clan is fiercely independent, and has resisted attempts by the Žalezny Tron to bring them into the fold. They are ruled by a council of elders, and their leader is known as the Sea King.

The Ostyrion clan is a wealthy and influential clan in the Westerlands. They are known for their expertise in mining and metalworking, and are responsible for much of the regions wealth. The clan is allied with House Łańnistar, and provides them with valuable resources in exchange for protection and political support.

Aegon Tarharyjen is the firstborn son of Prince Rhaegar Tarharyjen and Princess Elia Martell. He was born in 281 AC and is currently a young boy of 17 years. Aegon was saved during the Sack of Kings Landing by Ser Willem Darry, who took him and his sister Rhaenys into exile in Essos. Aegon was educated by his mentor, Jon Connington, and has recently returned to Westeros with a small army, hoping to reclaim the Žalezny Tron and restore House Tarharyjen to power.

Jon Connington is a former Hand of the King and a close friend of Prince Rhaegar Tarharyjen. He was exiled after failing to suppress the rebellion of Robert Barateon and was believed to have died of greyscale. However, he secretly survived and lived in Essos for many years, raising and educating Aegon Tarharyjen. Now, he has returned to Westeros with Aegon, hoping to restore House Tarharyjen to power.

House Duckfield is a minor noble house from the Račnyje Ziemli. They are sworn to House Frey of the Twins. Their lands are located near the western border of the Račnyje Ziemli, close to the Golden Tooth. The head of House Duckfield is Ser Wendel Duckfield, a seasoned knight who fought in the War of the Five Kings. Despite their small size, House Duckfield is known for their fierce loyalty to House Frey and their skill at arms.

The men of the Frozen Shore are a culture of free folk who inhabit the Frozen Shore, west of the Frostfangs. They fish along the northern coast of the Bay of Ice. They are known to wear sealskin, ride chariots pulled by wolves and on rare occassions; ride ferocious bears into battle.

Norrey is the formal name given to the Norreys, a mountain clan from the north that inhabits the high mountains north of the wolfswood. Of the mountain clans, the Norreys live closest to the Gift. The chief of the clan is known as The Norrey, although at Minańnie Zimy he is given the treatment of Lord Norrey.

House Drumm of Old Wyk is a noble house from the Iron Islands, tracing their history back for at least eight hundred years. They are the Lords of Old Wyk, the island considered holiest by the ironmen and the first one colonized by the First Men.Some Drumms were rock kings of Old Wyk in antiquity. For instance, the rock king Regnar Drumm, called Raven-feeder, was chosen High King of the Iron Islands by kingsmoot after Erich I Greyiron renounced his crown. The Drumms later joined with the Greyjoys, Hoares, Orkwoods, and Andals to bring down the hereditary House Greyiron.
House Merlyn of Pebbleton is a noble house from the Iron Islands. They are one of the primary houses sworn to Pyke. Their seat of Pebbleton Tower is located at Pebbleton on Great Wyk.

House Farwynd is a noble house from the Iron Islands. Their lands lie on the Lonely Light, an island eight days sail to the northwest of Great Wyk as well as Sealskin Point. The Farwynds and the smallfolk they rule are regarded as queer. Some claim that the Farwynds from the Lonely Light lie with seals to bring forth half-human children, while others claim the Farwynds are skinchangers who can take the forms of sea lions, walruses, and spotted whales. A thousand years after the time of King Brandon the Burner, ironmen sailing out of Great Wyk were blown off course into a cluster of islands eight days sail from the closest shore. Their captain built a tower and a beacon there, took the name Farwynd, and declared the Lonely Light his seat. His descendants prospered and continue to live there, though other ironborn believe them mad.
House Sunderly of Saltcliffe is one of the main nobles houses from the Iron Islands. Their seat is located on the island of Saltcliffe and share the Island with members of House Saltcliffe.
Dom Marbrand - šlachietny dom Zachodnich Ziamiel.
Dom Pajpier - šlachietny dom Račnych Ziamiel.
Dom Strykłend paklaŭsia ŭva addanaści Maładomu Hryfu.
Dom Žo - šlachietny dom Letnich Vyspaŭ.
Dom Ło - były šlachietny dom I Ci, adpraŭleny ŭ vyhnańnie.
Ko Čovakka - lidar Dotrakijskaj vajskovaj bandy.
Dom Farman - šlachietnaja siamja addanaja Zachodnim Ziemlam.
Vajary łajalnyja Allisaru Tornu, zbrojnyja čyny Čornaha Zamku.
Valiryjskaje Karotkaje Lazo Miača Dźvie Ruki

Volny Narod zazvyčaj kličuć adzičełymi na poŭdni ad ściany, bo jany zjaŭlajucca naščadkami Pieršych Ludziej, što byli izalijavany paśla budaŭnictva Ściany i stvaryli svaju ŭłasnuju ŭnikalnuju kulturu. Reštki vołataŭ majuć chaŭrus z Volnym Narodam.

Načny Dazor - heta prysiahnuŭšaje braterstva, zaklikanaje achoŭvać Ścianu, masiŭnuju ledzianuju pabudovu, što adłučaje Siem Karaleŭstvaŭ ad zamiežnych dzikich ziamiel. Zasnavany prykładna 8000 hadoŭ tamu, Načny Dazor zaklikany baranić karaleŭstvy ad pahrozaŭ Poŭnačy: Volnaha Naroda i Biełych Błukačoŭ. Čalcy Načnoha Dazoru, viadomyja jak krumkačy, admaŭlajucca ad ziamiel, tytułaŭ i siemjaŭ, kab słužyć usio žyćcio, źviazaŭšy siabie klatvaj viernaści.

Dalina Arryn, taksama viadomaja jak prosta Dalina, - kraj uva ŭschodniaj častcy Zachadosa. Heta chata Domu Arryn, čyim stałom zjaŭlajecca Arlinaje Hniazdo - farteca, pabudavanaja na viaršyni vysokaj hary. Dalina - surovy horny kraj sa mnostvam uradlivych dalinaŭ i bahatymi minieralnymi resursami. Žychary Daliny luta niezaležnyja i majuć reputacyju izalacyjanistaŭ, pieravažajuć za lepšaje trymacca asabniakom i padtrymlivać ułasny ład žyćcia. Jany viadomyja svaim majsterstvam hornaha boju i vykarystańniem pikaŭ dy inšaj doŭhaj zbroi. Dalinaj tradycyjna kiruje Dom Arryn, jaki ŭtrymlivaje svaje vaładarstvy ŭ krai praz vajskovuju moc, palityčnyja chaŭrusy i stratehičnyja šluby.

Račnyja Ziemli, mieściacca ŭ centry Zachadosa, - uradlivym krai, što charaktaryzujecca šmatlikimi rekami i bahataj sielskaj haspadarkaj. Račnyja Ziemli - heta nie adno karaleŭstva, a chutčej šerah vaładarstvaŭ, što naležać roznym šlachietnym siemjam, jakimi kiruje Dom Talli sa svajho stała, Biahučajraki. Kraj maje stratehičnaje značeńnie z-za svajho centralnaha miescavańnia, što robić jaho ahulnym polem bitvy dla varožych karaleŭstvaŭ, što jaho atačajuć.

Cmačyny Kamień - frakcyja, jakuju ŭznačalvaje Stańnis Barateon, małodšy brat Karala Robierta Barateona i zakonny spadčyńnik Žaleznaha Tronu paśla śmierci Robierta. Stańnis vałodaje mahutnaj fartecaj Cmačynykamień, jakaja niekali była radavym stałom Domu Tarharyjenaŭ. Viadomy svajoj strohaj prychilnaściu da abaviazkaŭ i spraviadlivaści, Stańnis imkniecca zaniać Žalezny Tron i adnavić stabilnaść u karaleŭstvie. Jon kamanduje hroznym fłotam i karystajecca padtrymkaj čyrvonaj śviataryni Melisandry.

Štarmavyja Ziemli, znachodziacca na paŭdniovym uschodzie Zachadosa, - kraja, viadomaha svaim štarmavym nadvorjem i pierasiečanaj miascovaściu. Štarmavyja Ziemli - heta kraina lutych vajaroŭ i tryvałych ludziej, jakimi kiruje Dom Barateonaŭ sa svajho stała, Štarmavoj Miažy. Tut rastuć hustyja lasy, u tym liku staražytny Čyrvony Les i Karaleŭski Les, a taksama ŭražalnyja Čyrvonyja Hory, što stvarajuć paŭdniovuju miažu krainy. Narod Štarmavych Ziemlaŭ maje doŭhuju historyju niezaležnaści i na praciahu stahodździaŭ adbivaŭsia ad šmatlikich uvarvańniaŭ.

Miaža - uradlivy kraj na poŭdni Zachadosa, viadomy svaimi ščodrymi ŭradžajami i bahatymi vinahradnikami. Tut mieścicca niekalki mahutnych šlachietnych damoŭ, naprykład, Tajrełaŭ, čyim stałom zjaŭlajecca Vysokisad. Miaža maje daŭniuju historyju rycarstva i pałacavych manieraŭ, a jaje rycary ličacca adnymi z lepšych u Siami Karaleŭstvach. Na praciahu šmatlikich stahodździaŭ hetym krajem kiruje Dom Tajrełaŭ, i hetaja siamja stała adnoj z najbahatych i ŭpłyvovych u Zachadosie. Tajreły tradycyjna padtrymlivajuć svajo panavańnie praz spałučeńnie vajskovaj mocy, palityčnych chaŭrusaŭ i razumnaj dypłamatyi. Adnak u apošnija hady Miaža stała arenaj zmahańnia roznych frakcyjaŭ za kantrol nad Žaleznym Tronam, a vaładarstva Domu Tajrełaŭ u krai apynułasia pad pytańniem.

Sturhijcy pryjšli z paŭnočnych lasoŭ, z poŭdnia ad ledzianoha mora Bajalik. Stahodździami jany žyli izalavana ŭ ciomnych lasach. Ich kolkaść strymlivałasia śmiarotnymi zimami. Ale pa miery pašyreńnia i zapaŭnieńnia kantynienta Kalradyi Impieryjaj, handlary adpraŭlalisia ŭ lasy ŭ pošukach miodu, bahnavaha žaleza i, pieradusim, futra. Vialikija harady paŭstali ŭ sieci zatokaŭ i azioraŭ, jakija złučyli Sturhijskija ziamli z navakolnym śvietam, pryciahvajučy šukalnikaŭ pryhod z uźbiarežža, stepaŭ i Nordłanda. Z tych por kniazi i bajary hetaj ziamli pačali źviartać svaje pozirki navonki, zarablajučy sabie reputacyju vajaŭničym padychodam da dzieła i svaim dziełavym padychodam da vajny.

Napačatku vašych pryhodaŭ Džofry Barateon zjaŭlajecca Karalom Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ paśla śmierci Karala Robierta Barateona. Zakonnaść jaho haspadarstva asprečvajuć abodva dziadźki, Stańnis i Renli Barateony, śćviardžajučy, što ŭdava Cerseja Łańnistar niasłušnaja jamu.

Braavos - mahutny i bahaty Volny Horad, źmiescavany na bierazie łahuny na krajnim paŭnočnym zachadzie Uschodasa. Zasnavany źbiehłymi rabami, Braavos - heta horad kanałaŭ, tajemnych chodaŭ dy bahataha i razmaitaha nasielnictva. Im kiruje Marski Łord i haradzki sojm - klučniki. U Braavosie znachodzicca znakamity Žalezny Bank, jaki akazvaje bujny finansavy ŭpłyŭ na Siem Karaleŭstvaŭ i inšyja panstvy. Horad taksama viadomy svaimi vybitnymi fiechtavalnikami i tajamničym Domam Čornaha i Biełaha, dzie Biezabličny praktykuje svaje śmiarotnyja majsterstvy.

Dorn - samy paŭdniovy kraj Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ, što adroźnivajecca haračym klimatam, zasušlivymi pustelniami i vialikimi horami. Jaho žychary, viadomyja jak Darnijcy, zaciata niezaležnyja i majuć doŭhuju historyju supracivu zachopnikam. Niahledziačy na farmalnaje ŭklučeńnie ŭ skład Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ šmat stahodździaŭ tamu, Darnijcy praciahvajuć zachoŭvać svaju samabytnaść, u tym liku movu i zvyčai. Kirujučy Dom Martełaŭ doŭhi čas byŭ daminantnaj siłaj Dorna i udałym zachoŭnikam niezaležnaści ad Žaleznaha Tronu, praz stratiehičnyja chaŭrusy i dypłamatyju. Ale paśla niadaŭniaha zabojstva niekalkich čalcoŭ siamji Martełaŭ Dorn apynuŭsia ŭciahnutym u Vajnu Piaci Karaloŭ, i budučynia kraja zastajecca niavyznačanaj.

Žaleznyja Vyspy - žorskaje i niaŭmolnaje miesca, dzie žyvie narod, što zarablaje na žyćcio hrabiežnictvam i piractvam. Niezaležnyja adzin ad adnaho šlachcičy kirujuć Žaleznanarodžanymi i zmahajucca za ŭładu i panavańnie nad inšymi. Žaleznanarodžanyja słaviacca svaim marskim majsterstvam, a ichnich karabloŭ bajacca ŭva ŭsim Viadomym Śviecie. Ale stałyja vojny i zvady robiać ich uraźlivymi dla ŭvarvańnia z macieryka, i im davodzicca ŭvieś čas bałansavać miž imknieńniem da bahaćcia i ŭłady dy patrebaj samazachavańnia.

Pieršyja Vłandyjcy, najmity i avanturysty, havaryli na movach šmatlikich ziemlaŭ. Jany prybyli z-za mora, i abaviazalisia za srebra achoŭvać miežy Impieryi ad niepakornych miascovych plamionaŭ. Jany atrymali svajo imia ad adnaho z pieršych vajskavodaŭ, Viłunda Advažnaha, Vałandyjona na kalradyjskam. Tak jany stali viadomy jak Vłandyjcy. Ichniaja daskanałaja ciažkaja vieršnica nakiroŭvałasia na vorahaŭ Impieratara ad pustečaŭ Aserajaŭ da dalokich stepaŭ. Ale słužboŭcy abmiežavanyja ŭ srodkach nieŭzabavie stali płacić im hrantami na ziamlu i tytułami zamiest srebra, što, mahčyma, było nia samaj dalnabačnaj palitykaj. Vłandyjcy pasialilisia, pažanilisia, pabudavali haspadarki i zachapili blizkija Impierskija zamki jak svaje ŭłasnyja. Zaraz jany - niezaležnaje karaleŭstva, čyje tradycyi ŭzychodziać jak da Kalradyi, hetak i da ich dalokaj radzimy.

Poŭnač - žorski i prastorny kraj, viadomy svaimi surovymi zimami i lutymi ludźmi. Staražytnyja Starki z Minańnia Zimy byli haspadarami hetych ziemlaŭ i kiravali sa svajoj fartecy na praciahu tysiačahodździaŭ. Paŭnočniki - luty i niezaležny narod, jaki pa daŭniaj tradycyi šanuje addanaść i honar vyšej za ŭsio. Chacia Starki histaryčna zjaŭlajucca najmahutnaj siamjoj Poŭnačy, majecca šmat inšych šlachietnych damoŭ z važnym stanoviščam u krai. U apošnija hady, paśla ŭpadku Starkaŭ i praciahu kanfliktaŭ u Siami Karaleŭstvach, Poŭnač stała ahmieniem palityčnych manieŭraŭ i vajskovych dziejańniaŭ.

Dotrakijcy - kačavy narod, što konna vandruje pa nieabsiažnych pašach Uschodasa, viadomych jak Dotrakijskaje Mora. Jany žyvuć zhodna sa strohim kodeksam honaru, najvyšej za ŭsio šanujučy siłu, advahu i majsterstva ŭ bai. Henyja konnyja šlachcičy abjadnany ŭ plamiony, jakija zavucca chałasarami, na čale kožnaha ź jakich staić mahutny pravadyr, viadomy jak chał. Dotrakijcaŭ bajacca ŭva ŭsim Uschodasie za ichniuju lutuju vajarskuju kulturu i schilnaść da rabavańniaŭ dy razboju ŭ zavajavanych imi ziemlach. Ich nie cikaviać atrybuty cyvilizacyi, jany addajuć pieravahu tradycyjnamu ładu žyćcia na adkrytych raŭninach. Z-za kačavoha ładu žyćcia Dotrakijcy viadomyja svajoj niearhanizavanaściu, schilnaściu da zvadaŭ miž roznymi chałasarami.
Žycharoŭ Sarnora časta klikali Vysokimi Ludźmi, jany nasialali kraj vakoł raki Sarn, pakul ich amal nia vyniščyli Dotrakijcy.
Nasielniki Skahoskich Zrezanych Vyspaŭ u Zatocy Ciuleniaŭ.
Naščadki tych, chto pakinuŭ Valiryju da źniščeńnia hetaha horada kataklizmam.
Žychary pieršaha Volnaha Horada Uschodasa, jaki zasnavali Valiryjcy.
Žychary adnaho z Volnych Haradoŭ Uschodasa. Viadomaha jak Horad Viedźmaroŭ.
Žychary samaha paŭnočnaha z Volnych Haradoŭ, źmiescavanaha na vyśpie ŭ Dryhučym Mory.
Žychary samaha zachodniaha z Volnych Haradoŭ, źmiescavanaha na bierazie Zatoki Pentos.
Žychary samaha raźvitaha z Volnych Haradoŭ, źmiescavanaha na bierazie Mora Mirt.
Ludzi z Volnaha Horada, źmiescavanaha ŭ Stupienistych Kamianiach.
Žychary Volnaha Horada, źmiescavanaha na vyśpie ŭ Letnim Mory.
Dziakujučy zołatu i srebru, što zdabyvajecca va ŭzhorkach i skałach, žychary hetaha kraju zjaŭlajucca samymi bahatymi na Zachadasie.
Ludzi Poŭnačy - ciahavity rod. Naščadki Pieršych Ludziej, jakimi kiravali Karali Poŭnačy da zavajovy Aehona.
Dotrakijcy - vajaŭničy kačavy narod, što pierasoŭvajecca vialikimi ordami pa pašach Uschodasa. Ordy zvyčajna zavucca chałasarami.
Žaleznanarodžanyja nasialajuć Žaleznyja Vyspy i pakłaniajucca Patanułamu Bohu. Dla žaleznanarodžanych rabavańnie zachodnich bierahoŭ Zachadasa - ład žyćcia.

Darnijcy ŭ bolšaści svajoj zjaŭlajucca naščadkami naroda, što ŭźnik kala Raki Rojn na Uschodasie. Pryncesa Nimieryja źbiehła sa svajoj radzimy, ratujučysia ad Valiryjcaŭ, i pasialiłasia ŭ Dornie z vialikaj kolkaściu haściej. Toje tłumačyć, čamu bolšaść Darnijcaŭ majuć vyhlad nie padobny na zvyčajnych Zachadasaŭ.
Najbahaciejšy z Volnych Haradoŭ. Tut znachodzicca Žalezny Bank dy Dom Čornaha i Biełaha.
Naščadki Pieršych Ludziej, jakija patrapili ŭ pastku na poŭnačy ad ściany 8000 hadoŭ tamu. Narody, što žyvuć na poŭdnie ad ściany, časta zavuć ich adzičełymi.

Vajskovy orden, jakomu daručana baranić karaleŭstvy ludziej ad usiakaj pahrozy z poŭnačy ad ściany. U ich šerahach časta sustrakajucca badziahi i złačyncy, jakija sprabujuć paźbiehnuć lutaści pravasudździa.
Damy, jakija paklalisia być addanymi šlachcie svajho kraju, ale nasamreč jany addanyja tolki sabie.
Pieršyja Andały, jakija prybyli ŭ Zachadas, pasialilisia ŭ miascovaści, viadomaj siońnia jak Dalina. Heta surovy łandšaft, atočany Harami Miesiaca.

Žychary hetaha kraju žyvuć na skryžavańni šlachoŭ niekalkich inšych mahutnych karaleŭstvaŭ. Padčas zavajovy Tarharyjenaŭ Račnyja Ziemli znachodzilisia pad uładaj Žaleznanarodžanych. Paŭstańnie pad pravadyrstvam Doma Talli dapamahło Aehonu zavajavać hety kraj. U vyniku, u hetym krai byli zdabyty vielizarnyja vaładarstvy.
Žychary vyspaŭ i žychary kala Čornavodnaj Zatoki paśla paŭstańnia Robierta pierajšli pad kantrol Stańnisa Barateona.

Žychary hetych ziemlaŭ nazvany tak z-za častych dzikich štormaŭ, jakija navalvajucca na ichniaje ŭschodniaje ŭźbiarežža z Vuzkaha Mora. Da zavajovy Aehona hety kraj mieŭ ułasnaje niezaležnaje karaleŭstva, jakoje mieła nazvu Štarmavoje Karaleŭstva.
Tutejšyja žychary zjaŭlajucca vychadcami druhoha haspadarstva pa vieličyni z Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ, paśla Paŭnočnaha. Hety kraj maje samyja ŭradlivyja ziemli ŭva ŭsim Zachadasie.

Hetyja ludzi - naščadki staroj Staroj Impieryi His, jakaja była źniščana Valiryjcami padčas Hiskarskich Vojnaŭ. U haradach Zatoki Zaniavolnikaŭ dahetul praktykujecca šmat starych Hiskarskich zvyčajaŭ.
Žychary sprečnych ziamiel pamiž Račnymi i Štarmavymi Ziemlami, jakija z časoŭ Aehona Zavajoŭnika kirujucca niepasredna karalom z Karaleŭskaj Prystani.
Volny horad Norvas - sapraŭdnaja teakratyja, jakoj kirujuć Baradatyja Śviatary. Štodzionnaje žyćcio ludziej stroha padnačalvajecca trom zvanam.
Naščadki tych, chto pakinuŭ Valiryju da taho, jak kataklizm źniščyŭ hety horad.

Volny Narod, taksama viadomy jak Adzičełyja, - heta ludzi, što žyvuć za Ścianoj na krajniaj poŭnačy Zachadosa. Jany admaŭlajuć haspadarstva Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ i ličać siabie niezaležnymi. Žyćcio ŭva surovych umovach z abmiežavanymi resursami prystasavała Volny Narod da vyžyvańnia i ŭtvareńnia roznych plamionaŭ i kłanaŭ. Jany šanujuć volu i indyvidualizm, a ichniaje hramadstva mieniej strukturavana, čym fieadalnaja sistema Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ.

Načny Dazor - heta prysiahnuŭšaje braterstva, zaklikanaje achoŭvać Ścianu, masiŭnuju ledzianuju pabudovu, što adłučaje Siem Karaleŭstvaŭ ad zamiežnych dzikich ziamiel. Zasnavany prykładna 8000 hadoŭ tamu, Načny Dazor zaklikany baranić karaleŭstvy ad pahrozaŭ Poŭnačy: Volnaha Naroda i Biełych Błukačoŭ. Čalcy Načnoha Dazoru, viadomyja jak krumkačy, admaŭlajucca ad ziamiel, tytułaŭ i siemjaŭ, kab słužyć usio žyćcio, źviazaŭšy siabie klatvaj viernaści.

Cmačyny Kamień - frakcyja, jakuju ŭznačalvaje Stańnis Barateon, małodšy brat Karala Robierta Barateona i zakonny spadčyńnik Žaleznaha Tronu paśla śmierci Robierta. Stańnis vałodaje mahutnaj fartecaj Cmačynykamień, jakaja niekali była radavym stałom Domu Tarharyjenaŭ. Viadomy svajoj strohaj prychilnaściu da abaviazkaŭ i spraviadlivaści, Stańnis imkniecca zaniać Žalezny Tron i adnavić stabilnaść u karaleŭstvie. Jon kamanduje hroznym fłotam i karystajecca padtrymkaj čyrvonaj śviataryni Melisandry.

Račnyja Ziemli, mieściacca ŭ centry Zachadosa, - uradlivym krai, što charaktaryzujecca šmatlikimi rekami i bahataj sielskaj haspadarkaj. Račnyja Ziemli - heta nie adno karaleŭstva, a chutčej šerah vaładarstvaŭ, što naležać roznym šlachietnym siemjam, jakimi kiruje Dom Talli sa svajho stała, Biahučajraki. Kraj maje stratehičnaje značeńnie z-za svajho centralnaha miescavańnia, što robić jaho ahulnym polem bitvy dla varožych karaleŭstvaŭ, što jaho atačajuć.

Štarmavyja Ziemli, znachodziacca na paŭdniovym uschodzie Zachadosa, - kraja, viadomaha svaim štarmavym nadvorjem i pierasiečanaj miascovaściu. Štarmavyja Ziemli - heta kraina lutych vajaroŭ i tryvałych ludziej, jakimi kiruje Dom Barateonaŭ sa svajho stała, Štarmavoj Miažy. Tut rastuć hustyja lasy, u tym liku staražytny Čyrvony Les i Karaleŭski Les, a taksama ŭražalnyja Čyrvonyja Hory, što stvarajuć paŭdniovuju miažu krainy. Narod Štarmavych Ziemlaŭ maje doŭhuju historyju niezaležnaści i na praciahu stahodździaŭ adbivaŭsia ad šmatlikich uvarvańniaŭ.

Vałancis - adzin z najstarejšych i najmahutniejšych Volnych Haradoŭ Uschodasa, źmiescavany na paŭdniovym uźbiarežžy. Viadomy jak Pieršaja Dačka Valiryi, Vałancis byŭ zasnavany jak kałonija Valiryjskaha Vaładarstva i zachavaŭ svajo bahaćcie i ŭpłyŭ praz handal i vajskovuju moc. Horad padzieleny vialikim Doŭhim Mostam, uschodniaja častka jakoha adviedziena dla panujučaha kłasa, a zachodniaja - dziela prostych ludziej i raboŭ. Vałancis - centar palityki, kultury i intryhaŭ.

Braavos - mahutny i bahaty Volny Horad, źmiescavany na bierazie łahuny na krajnim paŭnočnym zachadzie Uschodasa. Zasnavany źbiehłymi rabami, Braavos - heta horad kanałaŭ, tajemnych chodaŭ dy bahataha i razmaitaha nasielnictva. Im kiruje Marski Łord i haradzki sojm - klučniki. U Braavosie znachodzicca znakamity Žalezny Bank, jaki akazvaje bujny finansavy ŭpłyŭ na Siem Karaleŭstvaŭ i inšyja panstvy. Horad taksama viadomy svaimi vybitnymi fiechtavalnikami i tajamničym Domam Čornaha i Biełaha, dzie Biezabličny praktykuje svaje śmiarotnyja majsterstvy.

Łorat - adzin z Volnych Haradoŭ Uschodasa, źmiescavany na hrupie vyspaŭ u Dryhučym Mory. Chacia Łorat maje mienšy pamier i ŭpłyŭ, za niekatoryja ź jaho siastrynskich haradoŭ, jon maje bahatuju historyju, što ŭzychodzić da staražytnych budaŭnikoŭ łabiryntaŭ, što stvaryli na vyspach mudrahielistyja łabirynty. Horadam kiruje sojm mahistraŭ, jaki sočyć za handlem i kamiercyjaj. Łorat viadomy svaimi majstravitymi ramieśnikami, u šerahach jakich tkačy i šklary, jakija stvarajuć pryhožyja i daścipnyja vyraby, na jakija majecca vialiki popyt uva ŭsim viadomym śviecie.

Pentos - adzin z volnych haradoŭ Uschodasa, źmiescavany na zachodnim uźbiarežžy kantynienta. Hety šumny horad zjaŭlajecca bujnym centram handlu i kamiercyi. Jon viadomy svaimi akvitnymi rynkami i vytančanaj architekturaj. Pentosam kiruje prync, abrany z najbahatych siemjaŭ horada, ale praŭdzivaja ŭłada ŭ Pentasie naležyć sojmu mahistraŭ, jaki sočyć za ekanamičnymi i palityčnymi spravami. Horad słavicca svaimi dalikatnymi vinami, bahatymi tkaninami i majsterskimi ramieśnikami, tamu siudy zjazdžajucca handlary i vandroŭcy z usiaho viadomaha śvietu.

Norvas, adzin z Volnych Haradoŭ Uschodasa, źmiescavany ŭzdoŭž bierahoŭ raki Nojn na vializarnych sienažaciach kantynienta. Horad padzieleny na dźvie častcy: Vysoki Horad, źmiescavany na viaršyni ŭzhorka, jon zjaŭlajecca domam dziela panujučaha kłasa, i Nižni Horad, dzie žyvuć prostyja ludzi. Norvasam kiruje sojm baradatych śviataroŭ, što ŭšanoŭvajuć boha svajho horada. Norvas viadomy svaimi majstravitymi ramieśnikami, asabliva tkačami habielenaŭ i majstrami pa vyrabie zbroi, i zjaŭlajecca miescam pryznačeńnia dla tych, chto šukaje jakasnyja ramiostvy i ŭnikalnyja relihijnyja zvyčai.

Kochar - Volny Horad Uschodasa, raźmieščany ŭ vialikim Kocharskim Lesu i na bierahach Raki Kchojn. Viadomy jak Horad Viedźmaroŭ, Kochar - miesca tajamnicaŭ i ciomnych majsterstvaŭ, dzie šyroka praktykujecca vyvučeńnie mahii. Horad, jakim kiruje sojm mahistraŭ, słavicca svaimi majsterskimi kavalami, zdolnymi apracoŭvać Valiryjskuju stal - redkaje i kaštoŭnaje ŭmieńnie. Kochar taksama viadomy svajoj hłybokaj pašanaj Čornamu Kazłu - boskaści, jakoj žychary horada štodnia prynosiać achviary.

Myr - adzin z Volnych Haradoŭ Uschodasa, źmiescavany na ŭźbiarežžy Vuzkaha Mora. Viadomy svaimi vydatnymi ramieśnikami i majstrami, Myr - horad inavacyjaŭ i tvorčaści. Myrskija vyraby: vytančanyja dyvany, składany šklany posud i dalikatnyja linzy, karystajucca vialikim popytam uva ŭsim viadomym śviecie. Myram kiruje kankłaŭ mahistraŭ, horad zjaŭlajecca centram handlu i kamiercyi, što pryvablivaje handlaroŭ z usiaho Uschodasa i Zachadosa, jakija imknucca nabyć znakamityja tavary horada.

Łys - adzin z Volnych Haradoŭ Uschodasa, źmiescavany na vyśpie ŭ Letnim Mory. Viadomy jak Parfumnaja Siastra, horad słavicca svaimi duchmianymi sadami i damami zadavalnieńniaŭ. Łyskija ramieśniki majuć pośpiech u stvareńni parfumy, jadaŭ i inšych ałchimičnych ziellaŭ, što robić horad miescam pryciahnieńnia dla tych, chto imkniecca papieścić svaje pačućci. Łysam kiruje sojm mahistraŭ. Horad kvitnieje za košt prybytkovaha handlu pradmietami raskošy, a taksama viadomy svaimi vysokakvalifikavanymi kurtyzankami, jakija karystajucca popytam uva ŭsim viadomym śviecie.

Tajroš - adzin z Volnych Haradoŭ Uschodasa, źmiescavany na skalistaj vyśpie ŭ Vuzkim Mory. Ažyŭleny partovy horad, Tajroš - heta płavilny kacioł kulturaŭ, movaŭ i tradycyjaŭ z usiaho viadomaha śvietu. Horadam kiruje archon, jaki abirajecca z šerahaj bahataj elity horada, Tajroš zjaŭlajecca centram handlu i kamiercyi, asabliva ŭ vobłaści tekstylu i farbavalnikaŭ. Horad słavicca svaim jarkim adzieńniem i branioj, a taksama vybitnymi juvielirami, jakija stvarajuć składanyja i kaštoŭnyja ŭpryhožvańni, jakija karystajucca popytam u šlachty ad Uschodasa da Asšaja.

Staražytnaje karaleŭstva Sarnor niekali było mahutnym i kvitniejučym, ale paśla šerahu razburalnych vojnaŭ i uvarvańniaŭ pieratvaryłasia ŭ svaju cień. Jaho narod, Sarnory, - tryvałaja i hanarlivaja nacyja, što zdoleła zachavać svaju ŭnikalnuju kulturu i tradycyi, niahledziačy na ciažkaści, ź jakimi jana sutykajecca. Pad čałom Viarchoŭnaha Karala šlachietnyja siemji i kłany Sarnora pracujuć razam, kab viarnuć karaleŭstvu byłuju chvału i abaranić svaje ziemli ad unutranych i vonkavych pahrozaŭ. Pa miery adnaŭleńnia siłaŭ Sarnora ich upłyŭ u Viadomym Śviecie praciahvaje raści, i ichni patencyjał jak mocy, ź jakoj treba ličycca, nielha niedaaceńvać.

Dom Tarharyjenaŭ, niekali vialikich vaładaroŭ Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ, ličyŭsia źnikłym paśla žorstkaj vajny za Žalezny Tron, u jakoj zahinuŭ Šalony Karol i jaho dzieci. Ale pa ŭsim panstvie chodziać čutki pra tajamničuju fihuru - prynca Tarharyjenaŭ, jaki źbiraje padtrymku i chaŭruśnikaŭ pa ŭsim Vuzkim Mory. Niekatoryja kažuć, što jon - sapraŭdny cmok, narodžany siarod soli i dymu, jakomu nakanavana kiravać ahniom i kryvioj. Inšyja šepčucca, što jon - simulant, chitry samazvaniec, što imkniecca skarystać chaos u haspadarstvie dziela svaich karyślivych metaŭ. Ale adno lha skazać peŭna - hety Tarharyjen, hety Aehon, pryjdzie. I jon nia spynicca ni pierad čym, kab zajavić pra svaje pravy zakonnaje panavańnie ŭva Zachadasie.
Kłany sa Zrezanych Vyspaŭ z Zatocy Ciuleniaŭ. Z-za adsutnaści kantaktaŭ jany ličać, što kirujuć saboj sami.
Vy majecie hrošy, ja rablu svaju spravu.
Heta zmročny śviet, ja budu rabić toje, što vinien.
Zahojvajcie rany, kirujcie svaim domam, navat pradavajcie tavary.
Dobra, mnie patrebien tolki vašy mieč.

Dalina Arryn, taksama viadomaja jak prosta Dalina, - kraj uva ŭschodniaj častcy Zachadosa. Heta chata Domu Arryn, čyim stałom zjaŭlajecca Arlinaje Hniazdo - farteca, pabudavanaja na viaršyni vysokaj hary. Dalina - surovy horny kraj sa mnostvam uradlivych dalinaŭ i bahatymi minieralnymi resursami. Žychary Daliny luta niezaležnyja i majuć reputacyju izalacyjanistaŭ, pieravažajuć za lepšaje trymacca asabniakom i padtrymlivać ułasny ład žyćcia. Jany viadomyja svaim majsterstvam hornaha boju i vykarystańniem pikaŭ dy inšaj doŭhaj zbroi. Dalinaj tradycyjna kiruje Dom Arryn, jaki ŭtrymlivaje svaje vaładarstvy ŭ krai praz vajskovuju moc, palityčnyja chaŭrusy i stratehičnyja šluby.

Miaža - uradlivy kraj na poŭdni Zachadosa, viadomy svaimi ščodrymi ŭradžajami i bahatymi vinahradnikami. Tut mieścicca niekalki mahutnych šlachietnych damoŭ, naprykład, Tajrełaŭ, čyim stałom zjaŭlajecca Vysokisad. Miaža maje daŭniuju historyju rycarstva i pałacavych manieraŭ, a jaje rycary ličacca adnymi z lepšych u Siami Karaleŭstvach. Na praciahu šmatlikich stahodździaŭ hetym krajem kiruje Dom Tajrełaŭ, i hetaja siamja stała adnoj z najbahatych i ŭpłyvovych u Zachadosie. Tajreły tradycyjna padtrymlivajuć svajo panavańnie praz spałučeńnie vajskovaj mocy, palityčnych chaŭrusaŭ i razumnaj dypłamatyi. Adnak u apošnija hady Miaža stała arenaj zmahańnia roznych frakcyjaŭ za kantrol nad Žaleznym Tronam, a vaładarstva Domu Tajrełaŭ u krai apynułasia pad pytańniem.

Dom Tarharyjenaŭ u minułym kiravaŭ Siamiu Karaleŭstvami. Jaho zasnavaŭ Aehon Zavajoŭnik, jaki ŭznačaliŭ paśpiachovaje ŭvarvańnie ŭ Zachados na svaich cmokach. Panavańnie Tarharyjenaŭ było adznačana čaradoj zavajovaŭ i paŭstańniaŭ, pakul dynastyja nie była zrynuta padčas Paŭstańnia Robierta. Zaraz vyhnanyja Tarharyjeny sprabujuć viarnuć sabie zhubleny tron dy źbirajuć chaŭruśnikaŭ i prychilnikaŭ pa ŭsim vuzkim mory dziela viartańnia ŭłady i ŭpyvu.

Žaleznyja Vyspy - žorskaje i niaŭmolnaje miesca, dzie žyvie narod, što zarablaje na žyćcio hrabiežnictvam i piractvam. Niezaležnyja adzin ad adnaho šlachcičy kirujuć Žaleznanarodžanymi i zmahajucca za ŭładu i panavańnie nad inšymi. Žaleznanarodžanyja słaviacca svaim marskim majsterstvam, a ichnich karabloŭ bajacca ŭva ŭsim Viadomym Śviecie. Ale stałyja vojny i zvady robiać ich uraźlivymi dla ŭvarvańnia z macieryka, i im davodzicca ŭvieś čas bałansavać miž imknieńniem da bahaćcia i ŭłady dy patrebaj samazachavańnia.

Dorn - samy paŭdniovy kraj Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ, što adroźnivajecca haračym klimatam, zasušlivymi pustelniami i vialikimi horami. Jaho žychary, viadomyja jak Darnijcy, zaciata niezaležnyja i majuć doŭhuju historyju supracivu zachopnikam. Niahledziačy na farmalnaje ŭklučeńnie ŭ skład Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ šmat stahodździaŭ tamu, Darnijcy praciahvajuć zachoŭvać svaju samabytnaść, u tym liku movu i zvyčai. Kirujučy Dom Martełaŭ doŭhi čas byŭ daminantnaj siłaj Dorna i udałym zachoŭnikam niezaležnaści ad Žaleznaha Tronu, praz stratiehičnyja chaŭrusy i dypłamatyju. Ale paśla niadaŭniaha zabojstva niekalkich čalcoŭ siamji Martełaŭ Dorn apynuŭsia ŭciahnutym u Vajnu Piaci Karaloŭ, i budučynia kraja zastajecca niavyznačanaj.

Napačatku vašych pryhodaŭ Džofry Barateon zjaŭlajecca Karalom Siami Karaleŭstvaŭ paśla śmierci Karala Robierta Barateona. Zakonnaść jaho haspadarstva asprečvajuć abodva dziadźki, Stańnis i Renli Barateony, śćviardžajučy, što ŭdava Cerseja Łańnistar niasłušnaja jamu.

Poŭnač - žorski i prastorny kraj, viadomy svaimi surovymi zimami i lutymi ludźmi. Staražytnyja Starki z Minańnia Zimy byli haspadarami hetych ziemlaŭ i kiravali sa svajoj fartecy na praciahu tysiačahodździaŭ. Paŭnočniki - luty i niezaležny narod, jaki pa daŭniaj tradycyi šanuje addanaść i honar vyšej za ŭsio. Chacia Starki histaryčna zjaŭlajucca najmahutnaj siamjoj Poŭnačy, majecca šmat inšych šlachietnych damoŭ z važnym stanoviščam u krai. U apošnija hady, paśla ŭpadku Starkaŭ i praciahu kanfliktaŭ u Siami Karaleŭstvach, Poŭnač stała ahmieniem palityčnych manieŭraŭ i vajskovych dziejańniaŭ.

Dotrakijcy - kačavy narod, što konna vandruje pa nieabsiažnych pašach Uschodasa, viadomych jak Dotrakijskaje Mora. Jany žyvuć zhodna sa strohim kodeksam honaru, najvyšej za ŭsio šanujučy siłu, advahu i majsterstva ŭ bai. Henyja konnyja šlachcičy abjadnany ŭ plamiony, jakija zavucca chałasarami, na čale kožnaha ź jakich staić mahutny pravadyr, viadomy jak chał. Dotrakijcaŭ bajacca ŭva ŭsim Uschodasie za ichniuju lutuju vajarskuju kulturu i schilnaść da rabavańniaŭ dy razboju ŭ zavajavanych imi ziemlach. Ich nie cikaviać atrybuty cyvilizacyi, jany addajuć pieravahu tradycyjnamu ładu žyćcia na adkrytych raŭninach. Z-za kačavoha ładu žyćcia Dotrakijcy viadomyja svajoj niearhanizavanaściu, schilnaściu da zvadaŭ miž roznymi chałasarami.
Vy rychtujeciesia zrabić krok u zmročny śviet, haspadarstva šmatlikich tronaŭ! Voś vašy piersanaž. Praciahvajcie, kali hatovyja, albo viartajciesia nazad, kab zrabić źmieny.

Bolšaść dziaciej vakoł vas mieli tolki najbazavuju adukacyju, ale vy zatrymlivalisia paśla ŭrokaŭ, kab vyvučać litary i matematyku. Vy byli začaravany kirmašom, vahami i mierami, likami i koštami, hutarkami pra prybytki i straty.
Vy zaŭsiody byli ŭvažlivyja da inšych ludziej, dobra razumieli ich matyvy, vyvučali, jak upłyvać na ludziej, i apraboŭvali atrymanyja ad darosłych viedy na svaich siabrach.

Vas zaŭsiody pryciahvali žyvioły, i vy pravodzili jak maha bolej času ŭ viaskovych stajniach. Vy ŭmieli supakojvać koniej, i časam vas vyklikali dla taho, kab zaprehčy novych žarabiat. Vy vyvučyli asnovy vieterynarnaha majsterstva, jakija dosyć časta lha užyć i da ludziej.

Razam ź inšymi maładymi ludźmi vy chadzili paśvić aviečak, kozaŭ i bujnuju rahatuju žyviołu na pašach pablizu vioski. Vy adkazvali za adłoŭ badziažnych źviaroŭ i zaŭsiody trymali pad rukoj vialiki kamień, kab u vypadku patreby kinuć jaho ŭ drapiežnikaŭ, što zatailisia.
Vy byli vučniem u miascovaha kavala. Vy navučylisia nahravać i kuć žaleza, bili mołatam pa niekalki hadzinaŭ zapar da bolu ŭ ciahlicach.
Vy dapamahali kapać studni, ramantavać chaty i čynić złamanyja płuhi. Taksama vyvučyli asnovy budoŭli i toje, što treba dla roskvitu ziemlarobčaj hramady.
Viaskovy lekar adpraŭlaŭ vas na ŭzhorki na pošuki karysnych lekavych raślinaŭ. Vy daviedalisia, jakija travy lečać rany albo źnižajuć tempieraturu, i jak ich znajści.
Vy supravadžali miascovaha palaŭničaha, kali jon vypraŭlaŭsia ŭ dzikuju pryrodu, i dapamahali jamu ładzić pastki i łavić drobnuju žyviołu.
Vy vazili tavary svajoj siamji ŭ najblizki horad na prodaž i nabyćcio nieabchodnaha. Heta była ciažkaja praca, ale vy atrymlivali zadavalnieńnie ad kirmašovaj mituśni.
Vy nazirali za trenieravańniami haradzkoj varty ŭ stralbie i ŭdaskanalvańniem płanaŭ pa abaronie ścienaŭ u vypadku abłohi.

Vierchavody bandaŭ, što sočać za truščobami Kalradyi, zaŭsiody majuć patrebu ŭ biednaj moładzi, kab dasyłać i atrymlivać paviedamleńni padčas ziamielnych vojnaŭ. Handlarskija syny i dočki, što šukajuć vostrych adčuvańniaŭ, taksama časam baviać čas u ich kampanii.

Usie harady majuć budaŭničyja praekty, jakija ŭvieś čas patrabujuć jak kvalifikavanych, hetak i niekvalifikavanych pracaŭnikoŭ. Vy daviedalisia jak budujucca padymalniki dy lasy, jak abčesvajucca i ŭkładajucca doški dy kamiani, i atrymali inšyja navyki.
Vy pracavali na kirmašy, pradavali cacki i napoi ažyŭlenym pakupnikam.
Vy dapamahali svajoj siamji vieści spravy, vypraŭlalisia na kirmaš, kab rabić zakupy i sačyli za prybyćciom karavanaŭ.

Vaša siamja naskrebła hrošaŭ na pačatkovuju školnuju adukacyju, i vy vykarystali makčymaść na poŭnuju moc, zachoplena čytali historyju, matematyku i fiłasofiju, dy abmiarkoŭvajučy pračytanaje z nastaŭnikam i adnakłaśnikami.

Vaša siamja naniała pryvatnaha nastaŭnika, i vy ŭ poŭnaj miery skarystalisia hetaj pieravahaj, z zachapleńniem čytajučy historyju, matematyku, fiłasofiju i abmiarkoŭvajučy pračytanaje sa svaim nastaŭnikam i adnakłaśnikami.

Vaša siamja vałodała niekalkimi końmi ŭ haradzkoj stajni, i vy ŭziali na siabie abaviazak kłapacicca pra ich. Mnohija viečary vy vyvodzili ich za ścieny i imčalisia naŭskač pa palach, haniajučysia ź inšymi maładzionami.
Vy pracavali najomnym pracaŭnikom u haradzkoj stajnie. Ułaśniki vyznavali, što vy ŭmiejecie abychodzicca z końmi, i dazvalali vam trenieravać ich, a časam navat abkatvać novych.

Vaša siamja ŭładkavała vas u śvitu Impierskaha strateha. Na vas nie ŭskładali ciažkich abaviazkaŭ. Hałoŭnym čynam vy dastaŭlali paviedamleńni i dahladali jaho kania, ale heta davała vam mahčymaść bačyć płanavańnie kampanijaŭ i rasstanoŭku vajaroŭ u bai.

Vaša siamja ŭładkavała vas pamahatym drobnaha barona Vłandyjskaha Karaleŭstva. Na vas nie ŭskładalisia asnoŭnyja abaviazki, hałoŭnym čynam vy dastaŭlali paviedamleńni i dahladali baronskaha kania, ale heta dało vam mahčymaść bačyć płanavańni kampanijaŭ i rastanoŭku ludziej u bai.

Vaša siamja damoviłasia, što vy budziecie supravadžać pravadyra svajho narodu. Na vas nie ŭskładali ciažkich abaviazkaŭ. Hałoŭnym čynam vy dastaŭlali paviedamleńni i dahladali pravadyrskah kania. Ale heta davała vam mahčymaść bačyć płanavańni kampanijaŭ i rasstanoŭku ludziej u bitvie.

Vy nikoli nie zmahli by nabyć hety ryštunak samastojna, ale vy byli dosyć dobrym najeźnikam, tamu miascovy šlachcič pazyčyŭ vam kania i ryštunak. Vy dałučylisia da braniavanaj vieršnicy i navučalisia z dzidaj.
Vy byli dosyć bujnym i pavažnym junakom, kab pravadyrskaja varta dazvoliła vam trenieravacca poruč ź joj, kab adnojčy vy dałučylisia.
Haradzkija vajary pravodziać bolšuju častku svajho žyćcia ŭ achovie haradzkich ścienaŭ. Hałoŭnym čynam jany trenierujucca sa zbrojaj dalokaha boju, asabliva karysnaj padčas abłohaŭ.
Haradzkija vajary bolšaść svajho času achoŭvajuć haradzkija ścieny. Hałoŭnym čynam jany trenierujucca sa strałkovaj zbrojaj.

Usie haspadarstvy Viadomaha Śvietu vyznajuć kaštoŭnaść dobraj lohkaj vieršnicy i konnych łučnikaŭ i abaviazkova viarbujuć kačeŭnikaŭ i pamiežnikaŭ, zdolnych vykonvać hetyja abaviazki. Vy byli prystojnym najeźnikam, tamu vašyja susiedzi vyrašyli nabyć vam maleńkaha poni i dobry łuk, kab vy mahli vykonvać svoj vajarski abaviazak.

Usie haspadarstvy Kalradyi razumiejuć kaštoŭnaść dobraj lohkaj vieršnicy i abaviazkova rekrutujuć kačeŭnikaŭ i pamiežnych žycharoŭ, jakija vałodajuć navykami dla vykanańnia hetych abaviazkaŭ. Vy byli nahetul dobrym vieršnikam, što vašyja susiedzi dapamahli vam nabyć maleńkaha poni i niekalki drotykaŭ, kab vy zmahli vykonvać svaje abaviazki rušenca.
Rušeńnie ŭzbrojenaje dzidaj i ščytom, nabranaje z drobnych ziemlarobaŭ, zaŭsiody było hruntam usich vojskaŭ Viadomaha Śvietu.

Maładyja rekruty, chudarlavyja, albo zanadta biednyja dla nabyćcia ščyta i brani, zvyčajna ŭstupajuć u šerahi zastrelnikaŭ. Zmahajučysia łukam i drotykami, jany imknucca zastavacca pa-za dasiahalnaściu asnoŭnych siłaŭ voraha.
Mnohija Battanijcy vajujuć jak kierny, univiersalnyja vajary, što mohuć jak atakavać varožuju liniju svaimi dzidami, hetak i dałučycca da apošniaj kryklivaj ataki, kali vorah sasłabnie.

Vy paźbiehli słužby ŭ adnym z hałoŭnych vojskaŭ vašaha haspadarstva, ale zamiest hetaha jechali ŭ abozie ŭśled za vojskam razam z žonkami, kachankami i słuhami vajaroŭ, a taksama tymi, chto zarablaje na žyćcio kłopatam, zabavami albo ašukvańniem vajaroŭ.
Pierad tym jak rušyć u šlach poŭny pryhod, vašym najvialikim dasiahnieńniem było...
była pieramoha nad voraham u boi.

było ŭznačalvańnie paśpiachovaha palavańnia na čałavieka.

Vašaj siamji spatrebiŭsia nadziejny čałaviek, kab advieści karavan u susiedni horad. Vy arhanizavali dastavy, zabiaśpiečyli stały dazor ad razbojnikaŭ, i paśpiachova dastavili karavan u punkt pryznačeńnia.
było vyratavańnie vašaj vioski ad pavodki.
Kali z-za raptoŭnaha štormu miascovy ručaj źnianacku padniaŭsia, vašym susiedziam spatrebiłasia chutkadumnaje kiraŭnictva. Vy zabiaśpiečyli jaho, zahadaŭšy im budavać dambu dla vyratavańnia damoŭ.
było vyratavańnie vašaha haradzkoha kvartału ad pažaru.

Vašyja baćki nia dali vam šmat hrošaŭ, ale jany pakinuli roŭna stolki, kab vy zmahli atrymać pazyku na vialikuju sumu pad budaŭnictva maleńkaj majsterni. Vy viarnuli zapazyčanaje i pradali svajo pradpryjemstva z prybytkam.

Vašyja baćki nia dali vam šmat hrošaŭ, ale pakinuli dosyć, kab vy zmahli nabyć placoŭku niekarystanaj ziamli na ŭskrajku vioski. Vy rasčyścili kamiani i vykapali arašalny roŭ, vyraścili niekalki siezonaŭ uradžaju, a potym pradali jaho sa značnym prybytkam.
Vaŭki i miadźviedzi ŭvieś čas pahražajuć statkam na poŭnačy Kalradyi, a hijeny i leapardy turbujuć poŭdzień. Vy pajšli z hrupaj svaich adnaviaskoŭcaŭ i vypuścili snarad, jaki zabiŭ źviera.
