Vašy krumkač byŭ pierachopleny i zabity {PREDATOR} padčas sproby dabracca da {HERO NAME}!
Voj nie. Krumkač trapiŭ u pastku i byŭ zjedzieny Hru, kali sprabavaŭ dabracca da {HERO_NAME}!
Krumkač ad {FACTION1_NAME} dabiarecca da {ADDRESSEE_TEXT} ciaham {TRAVEL_TIME} dzion.
Krumkač abo nie razumieje, abo jamu nie padabajecca vašy žart, i jon admaŭlajecca ad zadańnia.
Vy viedajecie zamała pra {HERO_NAME} dla abrańnia ŭ jakaści mety dla krumkača.
{HERO_NAME} niadaŭna {?HERO_NAME.GENDER}vyzvaliłasia z pałonu i nie hatovaja{?}vyzvaliŭsia z pałonu i nie hatovy{\?} atrymlivać krumkačoŭ.
{HERO_NAME} zanadta {?HERO_NAME.GENDER}niedaśviedčanaja{?}niedaśviedčany{\?} dla atrymańnia paviedamleńniaŭ ad krumkačoŭ.
Prahlad i redahavańnie vojnaŭ, źviazanych z siužetam Game of Thrones.
Honar Načnoha Dazoru šanuje ŭsich haspadaroŭ i nie padnačalvajecca nivodnamu.
Volny Narod nie ŭdzielničaje ŭ aficyjnaj vajnie.
Vašaja vajna z Načnym Dazoram robić mir niemahčymym.
Bołtany zapłaciać za zdradu svajmu Karalu.
Ja idu za taboj Łord Bołtan...
Kali my vybieramsia adhetul žyvymi, vy atrymajecie maju viečnuju padziaku.
Ja adčuvaju, što za hetym stajać Łańnistary.
Vy musicie pieramahčy svaich pieraślednikaŭ, kab skončyć misiju.
Zatrymać taho, chto pryniasie mnie hałavu Roba Starka!
Rob Stark byŭ zabity padčas vašych uciokaŭ, i takim čynam meta Čyrvonaha Viasiella była vykanana.
Vy nie zmahli vyratavać Roba Starka.

Dvajnuju zbroju možna ŭžyvać tolki asnoŭnaj i druhoj rukoj. Ekipijujcie zbroju asnoŭnaj ruki ŭ druhoje vočka dla zbroi. Natatka: heta nie zvyčajnaja adnaručnaja zbroja, a zbroja dla asnoŭnaj ruki, jakuju lha vykuć u kuźni.

Dvajnuju zbroju možna ŭžyvać tolki asnoŭnaj i druhoj rukoj. Ekipijujcie zbroju druhoj ruki ŭ pieršaje vočka dla zbroi. Natatka: heta nie zvyčajnaja adnaručnaja zbroja, a zbroja dla druhoj ruki, jakuju lha vykuć u kuźni.
Zbroja asnoŭnaj ruki ŭ chibnym vočku!
Zbroja asnoŭnaj ruki mieścicca ŭ druhoje vočka zbroi.
Zbroja druhoj ruki ŭ chibnym vočku!
Zbroja druhoj ruki mieścicca ŭ pieršaje vočka zbroi.
Stańnis Barateon šturmuje Karaleŭskuju Prystań i abstelvajecca dzikim ahniom, što niščyć amal uvieś jaho fłot.

Jamu i jaho ludziam usio ž atrymałasia prarvać ścieny i amal zdabyć pieramohu, kali prybyŭ Tajŭjin z vojskam Tajrełaŭ i prymusiŭ ich niachoćciu adstupić. Bolšaść ściahaŭ Stańnisa albo hinuć, albo vymušany źmianić paddanstva. Stańnis vymušany viarnucca na Cmačyny Kamień, kab abdumać svaje dalejšyja dziejańni.
Aehon prybyvaje ŭ Štarmavyja Ziemli ŭ nadziei zachapić Žalezny Tron.
Mnohija damy Štarmavych Ziamiel padtrymlivajuć jaho pačynańni.
Hrubaja siła, palityka ci prostaje padstupstva - zaraz vy vaładar Karaleŭskaj Prystani.
Vy atrymali prava adpravić usiakaha łorda na Ścianu, karaleŭskaja hvardyja zaraz u vašym rasparadžeńni, dy daśpiechi adnych z najvialikich histaryčnych hierojaŭ Tarharyjenaŭ - u vašym viedańni.
Niežyć Burapienić u Kułaku Pieršych Ludziej
Načny Dazor z honaram baronicca ŭ Kułaku.
Načny Karol zrynuty. Praklon śmierci pakidaje cieły ažyłych, i jany valacca, jak miachi z kostkami.
Usie doli zaležać ad vybaru vyžyłych. Jaki šlach abiarecie vy?
Łord-kamandujučy Načnoha Dazoru Džor Marmont byŭ zabity svaimi ža ludźmi ŭ Trymańni Krastera.
Allisar Torn biare na siabie rolu vykanaŭcy abaviazkaŭ łorda-kamandujučaha, pakul nia vyznačycca lidar.
Dom Talli abjaŭlaje pra svaju addanaść Karalu Poŭnačy.
Maci Cmokaŭ i jaje fłot Biezdakornych i Dotrakijcaŭ rušać na Cmačyny Kamień, jaje radavy dom.
Jak tolki jana prybyła, jaje ŭładu zaŭvažajuć łordy Čornavodnaj Zatoki. Mnohija damy ŭšanoŭvajuć i klanucca ŭva addanaści zakonnaj spadčyńnicy Žaleznaha Trona.
Karol Džofry Barateon byŭ žudasna atručany jadam dušylnik na viasielnym bali.
Mnohija hutarać, što ŭva ŭsim vinny Niačyścik, jaho dziadźka, Ciryjon Łańnistar, jaki byŭ pasadžany ŭ viaźnicu, ale zdoleŭ źbiehčy z karaleŭstva.
Stańnis Barateon pahadžajecca pakinuć Cmačyny Kamień i adpraŭlajecca ŭva Uschodni Nahladnik pa mory, kab dapamahčy Načnomu Dazoru, bo atrymaŭ krumkača ad maestera Aemona z malboj pra dapamohu.
Melisandra spalvaje na vohniščy pałonnaha dziela błasłaŭleńnia Rhłoram ichniaha padarožža.

Neda Starka tolki što pakarali śmierciu za zdradu. Leŭ i voŭk učapilisia adzin adnamu ŭ hłotki. Stańnis i Renli Barateon uzdymajuć svaje ściahi, kab zapatrabavać toje, što, pa ich mierkavańniu, naležyć im pa pravie. Vajna Piaci Karaloŭ pačałasia.

Vy trapili ŭ hety zmročny śviet zmanu i zdrady. Siarod usioj hetaj mituśni pierad vami adkryvajecca mnostva mahčymaściaŭ zrabić sabie imia. Jaki šlach vy abiarecie? Pamiatajcie: kali vy ihrajecie ŭ Hulniu Tronaŭ, vy pieramahajecie ci pamirajecie.
Łord Rykard Karstark pakarany śmierciu Karalom Robam Starkam za toje, što adpomściŭ maładym pałonnym Łańnistaraŭ za śmierć dvuch svaich synoŭ ad rukaŭ Džejmi Łańnistara.
Vojski Domu Karstark viartajucca dachaty ŭ Trymańnie Karaŭ i abviaščajuć karalom Stańnisa Barateona.

U vašy łahier prybyvaje stomleny haniec z navinami pra apošnija padziei. {?PLAYER.GENDER}Pana{?}Pan{\?}, - pačynaje jon, - jak vy, mahčyma, viedajecie, Ruz Bołtan zaŭčasna zahinuŭ, i była vyjaŭlena paskudnaja zmova z udziełam zdrady Damoŭ Bołtan i Frej. Jany chutka pierajšli na bok Zachodnich Ziamiel i zaraz ličacca vorahami Damoŭ Stark i Talli.

Rob Stark atrymaŭ udar u padbarodździe, straciŭ niekalki ściahaŭ i most, ale vajna praciahvajecca. Ci skarystajeciesia vy hetym kanfliktam, kab uźniacca pa leśvicie, albo pačakajecie, pakul asiadzie pył?

Vy čujecie, jak prajazdžaje mima handlar i kryčyć: «Ačyśćcie darohu! Jedźma! U nas kaštoŭny hruz dla Dvajniatkaŭ. Chiba vy nia čuli? Damy Račnych Haspadaroŭ jadnajucca, i ja čuŭ, što na feście budzie sam Małady Voŭk. Tamu preč z darohi, my majem usiaho dva tydni».

Kali vy čujecie naviny, vałasy ŭstajuć dybaram. Vy razumiejecie, što niešta nia tak. Ale što vy možacie zrabić? Kali tolki adsiačy hałavu patrebnaj źmiai i sarvać płan. Ci vy prosta tryźnicie, dumajučy pra ŭsio hetaje?
Z-za niepradbačanych abstavinaŭ Čyrvonaje Viasielle nie adbyłosia!

Da vas nabližajecca haniec z zakłapočanym vyrazam tvaru. {?PLAYER.GENDER}Pana{?}Pan{\?}, - kaža jon, - ja maju važnyja naviny. Platkarać, što Stańnis Barateon źviarnuŭsia da Čyrvonaj Śviataryni Rhłora za dapamohaj u zmahańni za Žalezny Tron. Pa čutkach, jana vałodaje vielizarnaj mocaj i pierakanała Stańnisa źviarnucca da ciomnaj mahii, kab pieramahčy svajho rodnaha brata Renli Barateona.

Słovy viestuna vyklikajuć u vas pačućcio tryvohi. Vam treba zrabić vybar: umiašacca i spynić dziejańni Stańnisa albo siadzieć skłaŭšy ruki i nazirać za raźvićciom padziejaŭ? Vyjście hetaha kanfliktu moža mieć daloka idučyja nastupstvy dla Haspadarstva.

U vašy łahier prybyvaje stomleny haniec z navinami pra apošnija padziei. {?PLAYER.GENDER}Pana{?}Pan{\?}, - pačynaje jon, - jak vy, mahčyma, viedajecie, Stańnis Barateon zahinuŭ. Zaraz pierad jaho ściahami staić najvažny raźviazak: kamu jany paklanucca ŭva addanaści? Mnohija pozirki nakiravany na Renli Barateona, jaki hatovy zjadnać Štarmavyja Ziemli pad svajoj uładaj.

Słovy viestuna słužać napaminam pra toje, što ŭ hulni tronaŭ los moža źmianicca vokamhnienna. Śmierć Stańnisa stvaryła vakuum ułady, i tolki čas pakaža, čym jon budzie zapoŭnieny. Pakul ža vy musicie zachoŭvać pilnaść, prystasoŭvajučysia da łandšaftu Zachodnich Ziamiel, što ŭvieś čas źmianiajecca, pakul vakoł vas stvarajucca i buracca chaŭrusy.
Abiarycie Biełaha Błukača, jaki paviadzie vas u boj suprać žyvych...

Partyi Błukačoŭ patrebien dzień ci dva, kab stać aktyŭnaj, tak što pahulajcie trochi, i vam prapanujuć vybrać Biełaha Błukača dla słužby. Hulnia za Błukača - heta novaja funkcyja; časam ŠI Błukačoŭ moža pavodzić siabie nudna. U takim razie pasprabujcie pieraklučycca na inšaha Błukača. Viesialiciesia!
Vy šukajecie paŭsiul, ale Łorda Starka nidzie niama. Moža, vam varta pačakać dzień-druhi i pahladzieć, ci zjavicca jon.
Ja bolš nie chaču słužyć vam.
Ja žadaju słužyć u Načnym Dazory.
Vaša miłaść, kali łaska, dazvolcie mnie słužyć u vašym vojsku.
Ja žadaju słužyć u vašym vojsku.

Nie čakajcie, što vy budziecie {?PLAYER.GENDER}sapraŭdnaj Načnoj Dazorcaj{?}sapraŭdnym Načnym Dazornym{\?}, ale možacie dałučycca da nas za {GOLD_ICON}{STAGS} u dzień. Za ścianoj Błukačy i Adzičełyja. Upeŭnieny, što žadajecie dałučycca?
Vaša miłaść? Ustań! My nie schilajem kaleniaŭ ni pierad kim za ścianoj. Kali ty zmožaš zabić krumkačoŭ i ŭsio inšaje, što my tut znojdziem, to my ciabie voźmiem.

Słužyć? Ja što, vyhladaju jak {?HERO.GENDER}niejkaja modnaja paŭdniovaja łedzi{?}niejki modny paŭdniovy łord{\?}? Kali ty sapraŭdy chočaš zabivać Błukačoŭ i Krumkačoŭ, to možaš pajści sa mnoj. My nie karystajemsia zołatam, ale možaš rabavać miortvych, kali tabie paščaścić niekaha zabić.
Vy fajna pasłužyli mnie ŭ minułym. Vielmi dobra, ja zrablu vam honar słužyć u majoj asabistaj hvardyi.
Kali vy žadajecie dałučycca, ja mahu płacić vam {GOLD_ICON}{STAGS} u dzień. Kali pratrymajeciesia dosyć doŭha, my možam abmierkavać pavieličeńnie zarobka. Upeŭnieny, što žadajecie dałučycca?
Kali vy žadajecie dałučycca da partyi {HERO.NAME}, to spačatku adklučycie funkcyju Serve As Soldier u čarzie zahruzki.
Vy vajavali suprać frakcyi {HERO.NAME} zanadta niadaŭna, kab dałučycca da {?HERO.GENDER}jaje{?}jaho{\?}.
Jak {?HERO.GENDER}karaleva{?}karol{\?}, {HERO.NAME} budzie pryjmać na słužbu tolki sałdataŭ, jakim {?HERO.GENDER}jana{?}jon{\?} daviaraje {?HERO.GENDER}.

Dałučeńnie da partyi łorda zvolnić usich vajaroŭ z vašaj partyi. Upeŭnieny, što žadajecie praciahnuć?
Što? Vy tolki što pryjšli! Dobra, kali ja nie mahu na vas raźličvać, tady možacie iści.
Mnie nie padabajecca, što vy sychodzicie, ale rabicie, što musicie.

Ciapier, kali vašaje karaleŭstva pała, mnie prydasca vašy mieč.
Vy šlachietny i daviali svaju vartaść, moj mieč z vami da kanca maich dzion.
Słužyć vam? Preč z maich vačej!
Ja dałučusia da vašaj spravy, ale mnie treba šmat aleniaŭ i, mahčyma, trochi załatych cmokaŭ, kab raźličycca z abaviazkami.
Ličycie, što ŭsio hatova, sardečna zaprašaju! Vy zaŭždy budziecie mieć miesca za maim stałom.
Heta nadmierny košt dla čałavieka, jaki nia maje doma.
Vajna adabrała ŭ mianie zašmat hrošaj, ja viarnusia, jak tolki zdabudu zdabyču.
Cudoŭna! Ja budu słužyć vam z hetaha dnia i da kanca svaich dzion.
Navat syšedšyja šlachcičy majuć patrebu ŭ miasie i miedavusie, mahčyma, našyja šlachi jašče pierasiakucca...

Vy ŭpeŭnieny, što žadajecie stać vasałam {KINGDOM}? Kali vy pahadziciesia, vy refarmujecie svaju ŭłasnuju partyju, papoŭniŭšy jaje vajarami, i atrymajecie zamak, kali taki majecca. Vy bolš nia zmožacie vykonvać vasalnyja kvesty.

Vy musicie davieści svaju hodnaść ({AMOUNT}) da {HERO.NAME} pierš čym {?HERO.GENDER}jana{?}jon{\?} dazvolić vam uziać na siabie dadatkovyja abaviazki
Vykarystoŭvać miešaninu z ryštunka vašaj partyi i vašaha ŭłasnaha ryštunka
Ciapier, kali vy dałučylisia da {KINGDOM}, vy bolš nia možacie vykonvać hety kvest.

Kab zamacavać svoj status lehiendarnaha vajara haspadarstva, vy musicie vykanać nastupnyja mety, pakul słužycie. Paśla ich vykanańnia vy zmožacie stać vasałam {KINGDOM}, i vam buduć daravany vajary i ŭłasny zamak.
Mnie treba bolej ludziej dla svajoj asabistaj śvity. Pakažycie mnie kandydataŭ u Karaleŭskuju Hvardyju?
Ja žadaju rekrutavać vartu vašaha domu.
Zdajecca, vy - {?HERO.GENDER}karaleva{?}karol{\?} nia toj krainy. Pasprabujcie zavajavać Zachadas, a potym viartajciesia da mianie.
Prabačcie, chto vy? Chopić marnavać moj čas.
Prabačcie, {?HERO.GENDER}šlachcianka{?}šlachcič{\?}, ale Karaleŭskaja Hvardyja pryznačana dla... nu, karaloŭ.
Viadoma, Vaša Miłaść. Kolki čałaviek vam patrabujecca?
Bo vy - {?HERO.GENDER}šlachcianka{?}šlachcič{\?}, našyja ludzi ŭ vašym viedańni.
Chacia Dom {HOUSE} bolej nie isnuje, ja pa-raniejšamu rychtuju ludziej za adpaviedny košt.
{?HERO.GENDER}Pani{?}Panovie{\?} {HERO.NAME}, maja pavaha. Našyja ludzi buduć słužyć pad vašym čałom za peŭnuju płatu.
Vy nia možacie rekrutavać vajaroŭ domu pakul zjaŭlajeciesia najmitam.
Tolki karol, jaki siadzić na Žaleznym Tronie, moža rekrutavać Karaleŭskuju Hvardyju.
{CASTELLAN.NAME} nie dazvalaje vam rekrutavać vajaroŭ domu, bo {?CASTELLAN.GENDER}jaje{?}jaho{\?} {?HERO.GENDER}łedzi{?}łord{\?} nia viedaje vas dosyć dobra ({RELATION}).
Vy nia možacie rekrutavać vajaroŭ domu padčas abłohi.
Davajcie vyrašym hetaje starym šlacham. Ja vyklikaju vas na duel!
Ja čakaju vašaj zdačy, kali vy prajhrajecie!
My musim sustrecca adzin na adzin da bojki našych vojskaŭ!
Ja tak nia dumaju. Našyja vojski syducca ŭ bojcy!
Tady my musim sustrecca na poli.
Kolki vy hatovyja pastavić na svaje navyki?
Davajcie vyprabujem našyja navyki adzin na adzin.
Vy ładzicie rychtavańni, kab hodna sustreć svajho supiernika ŭ hanarovym boi.
Vy zdabyli pieramohu ŭ dueli! Ale haniebny supiernik admoviŭsia zdacca!
Havaryć z Maham Maram Tunam Docham Ŭeham
Ja hatovy rasstacca z niekalkimi, za słušnuju canu... Kolki žadajecie kupić?
Vielmi pryjemna mieć z vami spravu.[if:convo_grateful]
Žadajecie nabyć maich Biezdakornych dla abarony svajho karavana?
Žadajecie nabyć maich Biezdakornych dla asabistaj achovy?

Ja zacikaŭleny ŭ palapšeńni svajho ryštunka.
Tak, my možam hetaje zrabić. Jaki ryštunak vy majecie na ŭvazie?
Krumkač nia moža nieści Biezdakornaha, navat kali schopić jaho za kaŭnier.
{NAME} nia maje Biezdakornych na prodaž vam.
Vy pradali Biezdakornych hetamu karavanu zanadta niadaŭna, kab nabyvać ich.
Karavan nia moža pradać vam stolki Biezdakornych, bo jamu brakuje siłaŭ.
Vy kupili Biezdakornych u hety karavan zanadta niadaŭna, kab pradavać ich.
{NAME} nia maje patreby ŭ Biezdakornych zaraz.
{NAME} nia maje patreby ŭ takoj kolkaści Biezdakornych.
Lepiej pačać z nula, čym karystacca hetaj štukaj, ale heta vašyja hrošy.[if:convo_normal]
Dobra, tut nia tak šmat pracy, ale ja pierakanany, što my zmožam štości zrabić dla vas.[if:convo_pondering]
Zaraz ja pahavaru z chłopcami zzadu i pahladžu, što my možam z hetym zrabić.[ib:confident][if:convo_thinking]
My tolki što atrymali partyju vysakajakasnych materyjałaŭ, jakija vydatna pasujuć dla palapšeńnia hetaha ryštunka.[ib:confident2][if:convo_relaxed_happy]

Vy daviedalisia, što Ruz Bołtan płanuje zabić Roba Starka na viasielli jaho dziadźki ŭ Dvajniatkach. Kali vy paśpiejecie dabracca da jaho ŭ čas, mahčyma, vy majecie šaniec sarvać zmovu suprać žyćcia Roba.
Vy paśpiachova praduchilili Čyrvonaje Viasielle! Rob Stark praciahvaje žyć jak Karol Poŭnačy. Aproč taho, Ruz Bołtan byŭ uziaty ŭ pałon!
Vy paśpiachova praduchilili Čyrvonaje Viasielle! Rob Stark praciahvaje žyć jak Karol Poŭnačy.
Starki adpravili vam uznaharodu {GOLD_ICON}5000 za vyratavańnie svajho Karala.
Starki adpravili vam uznaharodu {GOLD_ICON}5000 za pałanieńnie Ruza Bołtana!
Vy nie zmahli vykanać kvest u čas.
Vy nia možacie bolej kamandavać kampańjonami.

Dačakaŭšysia nočy, vy prabirajeciesia ŭ zamak i znachodzicie Roba Starka. Patłumačyŭšy jamu pra zmovu suprać jaho žyćcia, jon zhadžajecca rušyć uśled za vami z zamka. Vartaŭniki papiaredžany pra ŭvarvańnie ŭ zamak i pryviedzieny ŭ stan pavyšanaj hatovaści.
Vy musicie mieć 20 rovień, kab viedać sakret Maha
Abiarycie pažadany ryštunak z saboj u boj

Chaj nia kažuć, što ja nie {?HERO.GENDER}miłasernaja karaleva{?}miłaserny karol{\?}. Chacia ja {?HERO.GENDER}mahła{?}moh{\?} by pakarać śmierciu ciabie za toje, što ty padniaŭ suprać mianie zbroju, ale zamiž taho ja pryhavorvaju ciabie da žyćcia na Ścianie.
Pa zahadu {?HERO.GENDER}jaje šlachietnaści Karalevy{?}jaho šlachietnaści Karala{\?} {HERO.NAME}, {PRISONER.NAME} pryhavorvajecca da pažyćciovaha źniavoleńnia na Ścianie.
Vaša frakcyja musić vałodać Karaleŭskaj Prystańniu, kab lehitymna adsyłać pałonnych na Ścianu.
Vy nia možacie adpravić ludziej na Ścianu, pakul vajujecie z Načnym Dazoram.
Vy nia možacie adpravić lidara frakcyi na Ścianu.
Volny Narod nia budzie słužyć na Ścianie.
Vy nia možacie adpravić žančynu na Ścianu.
Na Ścianu lha adpraŭlać tolki šlachtu z Zachadasa.
Kab skarystacca hetaj mahčymaściu, vy musicie sustrecca z {CHARACTER} prynamsi adzin raz.
Ciapier my padarožničajem tolki z adnym Biezdakornym... Pradać jaho - zrabić siabie ŭraźlivymi. Ale za maleńkuju dapłatu my padumajem pra hetaje.
Zaraz my vandrujem ulehcy, majem usiaho dva Biezdakornych dla abarony karavana. Ale my hatovyja pradać vam adnaho ź ich.
My hatovyja rasstacca z niekalkimi Biezdakornymi za słušnuju canu... Kolki žadajecie nabyć?
Tak, my majem miesca dla jašče adnaho.
Zaŭždy rady być bolš abaronienymi ŭ darozie. Kolki majecie?

Charrenchoł - najvialikaja farteca ŭ Siami Karaleŭstvach, stoł Domu Vent u Račnych Ziemlach na paŭnočnym uźbiarežžy Voka Boha. Ale z časoŭ svajho spaleńnia cmačynym ahniom padčas Zavajovy Aehona farteca pieratvaryłasia ŭ zmročnaje i zrujnavanaje miesca. Trymańni Charrenchołu - najbahatyja na Zachadasie, jany zajmajuć šyrokija pali zialonych uradlivych ziemlaŭ, što raspaścirajucca da ŭzhorkaŭ Domu Ŭod la Karonnych Ziemlaŭ.

Kryvavaja Brama - farteca, što baronić zachodniaje ŭzbočča Daliny Arryn na šlachu da Arlinaha Hniazda, stału Domu Arryn. Pad čałom Rycara Bramy, jakoha pryznačaje Abaronca Daliny, Kryvavaja Brama na praciahu tysiačahodździaŭ zjaŭlajecca hałoŭnym abarončym umacavańniem Daliny. Pavodle mitaŭ, bolš za tuzin vojskaŭ było źniščana padčas sproby ŭziać jaje ŭ Eru Hierojaŭ.
Runnykamień - farteca Daliny Arryn. Stoł Domu Rojs źmiescavany na paŭvyśpie na poŭnačy ad Zatoki Krabaŭ, na ŭschodzie ad Čyrvonaj Fartecy i na poŭdnie ad Čajkahradu.

Choł Doŭhiłuk, stoł Domu Chanter, - farteca, źmiescavanaja ŭ Dalinie Arryn. Horad znachodzicca na poŭdnie ad Palcaŭ, na ŭschodzie ad Domu Serca i na poŭnačy ad Staroha Jakara. Chutčej za ŭsio, jon miaściŭsia ŭ pieradhorjach pamiž hornym chrybtom i ŭschodniaj častkaj daliny.
Ucios Merlinha - vioska blizu Chołu Doŭhałuka.
Žałudovy Choł, stoł Domu Małalesu, - farteca Račnych Ziamiel, u jakich panuje Dom Talli Biahučajraki. Farteca mieścicca da paŭdniovaha ŭschodu ad Biahučajraki, poruč z uzhorkam Vysokaje Serca.
Šparki Vadaspad - vioska la Žałudovaha Chołu.

Marski Vartavy - farteca Račnych Ziamiel. Stoł Domu Mallistar, vasalnaha domu trymańnia Domu Talli Biahučajraki. Zamak staić na poŭnačy ad Biahučajraki, na ŭźbiarežžy Žaleznaj Zatocy. Jon mieścicca miž Čyrvonym i Błakintym Videlcami Tryzubu. Marski Vartavy pabudavany dziela achovy ad maradzioraŭ Žaleznych Vyspaŭ.
Choł Krumkačajedreva - farteca Račnych Ziamiel. Heta stoł Domu Čornalesu, vasalnaha domu trymańnia Dom Talli Biahučajraki. Farteca mieścicca na poŭnačy ad Biahučajraki, la ŭźbiarežža Žaleznaj Zatocy.
Vendzki Haradok - vioska la Chołu Krumkačajedreva.

Kamiennaja Zaharadź - farteca Račnych Ziamiel. Stoł Domu Brakienaŭ, vasalnaha domu trymańnia Dom Talli Biahučajraki. Zamak znachodzicca na ŭschodzie ad Biahučajraki, na poŭdnie ad Čyrvonaha Videlca Tryzuba.
Młyn Myšahub - vioska la Chołu Krumkačajedreva.
Karčma Čałaviek na Kaleniach - vioska la Kamiennaj Zaharadzi.
Choł Stohsiena - stoł Domu Erroł Štarmavych Ziamiel. Jon lažyć na ŭschodzie ad Karaleŭskaj Darohi, na poŭnočnym uschodzie ad Bronzavaj Bramy i na poŭdni ad Karaleŭskaha Lesu.
Štarmavy Viecier - vioska la Chołu Krumkačajedreva.

The Eyrie is the principal stronghold of House Arryn. It is located in the Vale of Arryn near the east coast of Westeros. The Eyrie straddles the top of a peak in the Mountains of the Moon several thousand feet above the valley floor below. It is approached by a narrow causeway and road. Those who would approach the Eyrie must pass through three way-castles guarding the ascent - and then must proceed in single file, making them very vulnerable to archers. For these reasons, the Eyrie is considered impregnable to any attack.
Gulltown is the largest city in the Vale of Arryn, the region controlled by House Arryn of the Eyrie. The city is located east of the Eyrie and south of Runestone on the east coast of the Vale.
Saltpans is a seaside village near the border between the Vale and Račnyje Ziemli. It is named for its salt-harvesting industry.

Pentos is one of the Free Cities, located on the western coastline of Essos, across the Narrow Sea from Westeros. It is a large, rich city-state of merchant lords. People and things from Pentos are known as Pentoski. Pentos is located at roughly the mid-latitude of the Free Cities, between Braavos in the north and Volantis in the south. It is due east of Kings Landing, directly across the Narrow Sea. It is surrounded by fertile coastal plains known as the Flatlands.

Braavos is one of the Free Cities located to the east of Westeros. It is the northern-most, the richest, and arguably the most powerful of the Free Cities. Described as a city of seafarers and master swordsmen, Braavos consists of hundreds of tiny islands connected by stone bridges. Its main landmarks include the Titan of Braavos, the House of Black and White and the citys famed Iron Bank. The people of Braavos are known as Braavosi.

Lorath is one of the Free Cities located to the east of Westeros. It is located on an island just off the northern coast of Essos, east and slightly south of Braavos. The Shivering Sea lies to its north and an inlet of water known as Lorath Bay lies to the south. Lorath is the least-known of the Free Cities, due to its isolated location and the lack of any notable ports further east.

The castle of Bitterbridge is the seat of House Caswell in the Miaža, the region controlled by House Tajreł of Vysokisad. The castle is located in the north east of the region where the Mander first crosses the Roseroad.

Rooks Rest is a coastal castle in the Crownlands which answers directly to the King on the Žalezny Tron. It is located north and east of Kings Landing on the north coast of Blackwater Bay, east of Duskendale but west of Crackclaw Point.
Bronzegate, the seat of House Buckler, is a castle in the Stormlands. The castle is located north of Storms End just off the Kingsroad, southwest of Haystack Hall.
Greenstone is a castle on the island of Estermont in the stormlands. It is the seat of House Estermont.
Stonedance, the seat of House Massey, is a castle in the Crownlands. The castle is located south of Sharp Point, on the peninsula south of Blackwater Bay.

Griffins Roost is a castle in the Stormlands, the region controlled by House Barateon of Storms End. It is the seat of House Connington. The castle is located south-west of Storms End on the western edge of Shipbreaker Bay.
Harvest Hall is a castle in the Dornish Marches, serving as the seat of House Selmy.

Sharp Point is the seat of House Bar Emmon in the crownlands. The castle is located along the Gullet at the northern end of Masseys Hook, north of Stonedance. It has a large watchtower upon which a great fire burns atop.

Cmačyny Kamień stands upon the eponymous island located in Blackwater Bay. It is the ancestral seat of House Tarharyjen and currently the stronghold of House Barateon of Cmačyny Kamień, a cadet branch of House Barateon of Storms End. It is within the Crownlands, the capital region of the Seven Kingdoms. Given as a sort of a slight, Cmačyny Kamień is ruled by Lord Stańnis Barateon.

Weeping Town is a town in the Stormlands, to the south-east of the Rainwood and along the Sea of Dorne. It possibly contains a seat for a noble house, called the Weeping Tower. Weeping Town is a market town ruled by House Whitehead. It includes three inns: the Broken Ščyt, the Loon, and the Drunken Dornishman. The town was named for King Daeron I Tarharyjen, as it is the place his corpse was brought after his death in the Conquest of Dorne.

Located on the southeastern coast of Westeros overlooking Shipbreaker Bay Storms End is a formidable fortress and the ancestral seat of House Barateon. One of the mightiest fortresses on the entire continent, Storms End has endured many sieges but has never fallen to any attacker in its millennia-long history. Its seaward wall is 80 feet thick with a 150 feet drop into the sea below. The castle is said to be protected by spells woven into its walls that prevent magic from penetrating its defenses. Storms End is now home to Renli Barateon of the Stormlands.

Kings Landing was founded by King Aegon I Tarharyjen, King of the Andals and the First Men. It is the capital, and largest city, of the Six Kingdoms. Located on the east coast of Westeros in the Crownlands, just north of where the Blackwater Rush flows into Blackwater Bay and overlooking Blackwater Bay, Kings Landing is the site of the Žalezny Tron and the Red Keep, the seat of the King of the Andals and the First Men. Kings Landing is currently ruled by Džoffry Barateon.

Duskendale is a large town of several thousand inhabitants in the Crownlands. The town is built around its harbor and has cobbled streets. Chalk cliffs lie to the north and low limestone hills shelter it to the west. Fishing villages dot the coastal road for miles in either direction.

Maidenpool is a town in the Račnyje Ziemli, the region controlled by House Talli of Biahučajaraka. It is the seat of House Mooton. It is located at the estuary of the Trident near the border of the Crownlands. It is located to the north of Kings Landing and north-east of Harrenhal. Maidenpool is famed in song as the location where the foolish knight Florian met and fell in love with Jonquil. It is said he fell in love with her when he saw her bathing with her sisters.
Ghoyan Drohe is a small castle in the Velvet Hills of Essos, north of the Flatlands and east of Pentos. It lies on the banks of the Little Rhoyne, west of its confluence with the Rhoyne.
Ny Sar is a castle in Essos at the confluence of the Rhoyne and the Noyne rivers. It once contained the palace of Princess Nymeria but was destroyed by the Valyrian Freehold.
Ar Noy is a castle in Essos on the banks of the Qhoyne, near its confluence with the Darkwash. To the northeast is Qohor and to the southwest, Dagger Lake.
Mistwood is the seat of House Mertyns in the stormlands. It is located in the southern rainwood in Nakidka Wrath.

Cornfield is a castle in the Westerlands. The seat of House Swyft, a knightly house sworn to House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli, it is located southeast of Skała Kasterli and Lannisport and northeast of Crakehall.
Iksa Keria is a Braavosi castle in northwestern Essos.
Siakiera Castle is located on a penninsula of land known as The Siakiera in northern Essos.

Honeyholt is a castle in the Miaža, the region controlled by House Tajreł of Vysokisad, and the seat of House Beesbury. The castle is located between Oldtown and Brightwater Keep, on the banks of the Honeywine river.

Norvos is one of the Free Cities located to the east of Westeros. It lies in the interior plains of Essos on the Noyne, a tributary of the massive Rhoyne River. The Free City of Pentos is located to the southwest and Qohor to the southeast. Norvos is on the route leading from the Narrow Sea to the Dothraki Sea, and as such pays tribute to passing Dothraki khalasars. People and things from Norvos are known as Norvoshi. The city is famed for its warrior-priests, the Bearded Priests of Norvos and its fine made axes.

Volantis is one of the Free Cities located to the east of Westeros. The southernmost and oldest of the Free Cities, it lies on the southern coast of Essos, where the mighty Rhoyne River meets the Summer Sea. It was founded as a colony of Valyria many centuries ago and is a great port. People from Volantis are known as Volantine.

Volon Therys is a small town in western Essos. The town is located not far to the north-west of Volantis, where the Rhoyne begins to separate out into its delta. The town is located on the western side of the river.
Valysar is a town in western Essos. The city is located north-west of Volantis on the western bank of the Rhoyne.
Selhorys is a town in western Essos, located on the eastern bank of the Rhoyne. The town is located north of Volantis and Valysar.

Qohor is one of the nine Free Cities in western Essos, located between the Narrow Sea and the grasslands held by the Dothraki. It is several weeks ride east of Pentos on the western edge of the vast Forest of Qohor. Like most of the Free Cities, Qohor was founded as a colony of the Valyrian Freehold, specifically as a religious center for worship of the deity known as the Black Goat. People from Qohor are known as Kocharski. The city itself is renowned for its immensely skilled blacksmiths, who possess the rare knowledge of how to reforge Valyrian steel.

Tumbleton is a town in the Miaža, the region controlled by House Tajreł of Vysokisad. Located north-east of Vysokisad, close to the headwaters of the Mander, it is located in the extreme northeast of the Miaža, and very close to the border with the Crownlands. It is not far to the southwest of Kings Landing.

Coldwater Burn is the seat of House Coldwater in the Vale of Arryn. It is located near the mouth of a river west of the Fingers. The castle of Snakewood is nearby beyond a mountain range to the south.

The castle of Strongsong is the seat of House Belmore in the Vale of Arryn. It is situated near a series of lakes within the Mountains of the Moon; a nearby river flows east through a valley to Hearts Home. The Eyrie is to the southeast.
Hammerhorn is a castle located in Great Wyk, the largest of the Iron Islands. It serves as the seat of House Goodbrother and lies in the Hardstone Hills.
Located near the border of the unexplored waters of the Sunset Sea, Lonely Light is a castle located on the island, the smallest of the Iron Islands, of the same name.

Crasters Keep is the name given to a small, fortified castle located several days journey beyond the Wall. It is the abode of Craster, a wildling who lives there with his daughter-wives, and also serves as the Nights Watchs only refuge beyond the Wall.

Fist of the First Men is a landmark in the wilderness beyond the Wall. It is an ancient ring castle located at the crown of a defensible round hill with an excellent view of the surrounding countryside.

Dyre Den is a castle on Crackclaw Point in the Crownlands. A small castle with three crooked towers, the Dyre Den lies on a wind-carved cliff above the end of the bayside road from Maidenpool. The castle is accessible from below by a steep and narrow cleft in the cliff, with the stony path leading up to the castle walls.

Torrhens Square is a castle in the north and the seat of House Tallhart. It is south of the wolfswood, southwest of Minańnie Zimy, and north of Barrowton, on the northern shore of a large lake. Torrhens Square has stone walls thirty feet high with square towers at each corner. Its square keep is considered strong.

Sisterton, a small mean town, rank with the odors of pig waste and rotting fish, is located on Sweetsister, an island of the Three Sisters, in the Bite. The seat of House Borrell, Sisterton is known as a den for smugglers. Its streets are made of mud and planks, while its are houses daub-and-wattle hovels roofed with straw. By the Gallows Gate there are always hanged men with their entrails dangling out.

Lordsport is a port town on the island of Pyke, in the Iron Islands, and the seat of House Botley. It is the largest town in the Iron Islands, and the main port for Pyke island. This also makes it the main port in service to nearby Pyke castle, the seat of House Greyjoy. Once burned to the ground during the Greyjoy Rebellion as a prelude to the Siege of Pyke castle, Lordsport was rebuilt in intervening years to its former glory.

Pyke is the stronghold and seat of House Greyjoy, located on the island of the same name, which is one of the seven major Iron Islands. The castle is the regional capital of the Iron Islands as a whole. Pyke is an ancient stronghold and the cliff it was built on has been eroded by the sea leaving the towers standing on stone stacks. The towers are connected by swaying rope bridges. The rocky moss covered stone at its base is not suitable for ships landing so traffic to the island flows through the nearby harbor town Lordsport. It is currently ruled by Balon Greyjoy – the King of the Iron Islands.
Frostfangs Camp, named after the mountain range in the far north of the continent of Westeros, is home to the Volny Narod clan.

Hull is a port town on the coast of Driftmark. Hull arose from three modest fishing villages which grew together at the time in which House Velaryon grew in wealth and power from the treasures brought by Lord Corlys Velaryon from his voyages.

Thenn is named after the Thenn people. They are the most advanced and best equipped of the wildling tribes, as well as the most disciplined. Thenns shave their heads bald and engage in self-scarification as well as cannibalism, feasting on the flesh of their enemies.

Hardhome is a Volny Narod fishing village located beyond the Wall on a sheltered bay along the Shivering Sea, situated at the tip of the large peninsula known as Storrolds Point. Many of the Volny Narod who survived the battle for the Wall and were not captured by the forces of Stańnis Barateon fled to Hardhome.
Hellholt is the seat of House Uller in southern Dorne. Although grim and stinking Hellholt is a strong castle located near the source of the river Brimstone, east of Sandstone and west of Vaith.
Alnor is a castle south of The Tree of Crowns. Seat to House Pendaerys, its position close to the sea makes it perfect of traders seeking wealth.

The seat of House Yronwood, the formidable castle of Yronwood is near the mouth of a river whose source is to the west near Skyreach in the foothills of the Red Mountains, which are along the Sea of Dorne. It sits at the southern end of the Boneway as a guardian against intruders.
Kingsgrave is the seat of House Manwoody in Dorne. It is located in the Red Mountains approximately halfway through the Princes Pass, north of Skyreach and south of the tower of joy.
The Tree of Crowns is a Tyroshi castle west of Myrth.

Bhorash is a castle on the northern coast of Slavers Bay in Essos. It lies south of the Painted Mountains and northeast of the Black Cliffs. Bhorash is connected by Valyrian roads to Mantarys and Tolos. It is unknown if Bhorash was founded by the Valyrian Freehold.
Wyl is a castle in Dorne, the region of Westeros controlled by House Martell of Sunspear. The castle is located south-west of Storms End and is the northern-most castle to hold fealty to Sunspear.

Chroyane is a castle located at the confluence of the Lhorulu and the Rhoyne on the continent of Essos, at the far southern tip of the Golden Fields. Chroyane is said to have streets made of water and houses of gold.
Sar Mell castle of the Rhoynar that sits on the eastern bank of the Rhoyne to the north of Volantis in western Essos. Almost directly across the river to the west sits the city of Volon Therys.

Sunspear is the capital of Dorne, southernmost of the Seven Kingdoms, located in the far southeast of the continent on the Summer Sea. It consists of a strong, fortified castle and a town that sprawls around it. It is a town built largely of mud and straw. The towns largest structure is Kapjo Tower, a 150-feet structure with a pinnacle of shining steel. The city is currently the seat of House Martell.

Astapor, also known as the Red City, is the southernmost of the three great city-states of Slavers Bay. A noted stopping point for ships bound from Qarth to the Free Cities and Westeros, Astapor is home of the infamous Unsullied, eunuch slave-soldiers considered by many to be the finest infantry troops in the World. Astapors sigil, like that of the other cities of Slavers Bay, is that of the harpy, the ancient symbol of the Ghiscari Empire, of which Astapor was once part. Though culturally still identifying itself as Ghiscari, Astapor is an independent city-state and is not aligned with New Ghis, which seeks to restore the Ghiscari Empire, to the south.

Yunkai, known also as the Yellow City, is one of the three great Ghiscari city-states of Slavers Bay, located southwest of Meereen and north of Astapor. Bedslaves, trained in the way of the seven sighs, are Yunkais chief export.

Lys is one of the Free Cities located off the coast of Essos. It lies south of Pentos, northwest of Volantis and north of the Summer Isles. The city stretches across several islands, which are separated from mainland Essos by narrow straits. Lys also has territorial possessions on the nearby regions of the mainland, east of Tyrosh and south of Myr. The famous pleasure houses of Lys are known to train the finest bed-slaves and prostitutes in the world, and they form the basis of the citys thriving export industry. Lys is also famous for producing a rare and difficult to detect poison known as the tears of Lys.

Tyrosh is one of the Free Cities located to the east of Westeros. It is situated on an island at the eastern end of the Stepstones, an island chain that extends across the Narrow Sea. According to legend, there used to be a land-bridge linking Westeros and Essos, of which the Steptones are the only remnants. Therefore, Tyrosh is the closest of the Free Cities to Westeros, located not far from Dorne and the island of Tarth. Due to its central location between Westeros and the other Free Cities, and its proximity to constant wars between Lys and Myr in the Disputed Lands. Tyrosh is often seen as a major world hub for hiring the services of various professional mercenary companies, to serve in the various conflicts of these different regions.
Vaith is a town in Dorne, the region controlled by House Martell of Sunspear. The castle is located in the center of Dorne, near the headwaters of the Vaith river and east of Hellholt.
Planky Town is a town in Dorne, the region controlled by House Martell. It lies at the mouth of the Greenblood River, near the Martells former seat at Sunspear, and is the main port of Dorne.

Myr is one of the Free Cities located to the east of Westeros. A major seaport, the city overlooks a large body of water known as the Sea of Myrth, an inlet of the Narrow Sea. The Free City of Pentos lies to the north and the Disputed Lands lie to the south. People and things from Myr are known as Myrish. The citys craftsmen are renowned throughout the known world for their lenses and finery and Myrish lace is a highly sought after commodity.

Horn Hill is the seat of House Tarly in the Miaža. It is located southeast of Vysokisad. Horn Hill has a sept within its walls and a pond that lies below the castle as well as woods that are teeming with game.

Blackcrown is a castle in the Miaža, the region controlled by House Tajreł of Vysokisad. The castle is located southwest of Vysokisad and Oldtown, on the northern side of Whispering Sound, the estuary of the River Honeywine. The castle overlooks the Redwyne Straits.

Crakehall Castle, is the seat of House Crakehall in the southwestern westerlands. It is located on the Searoad along the Sunset Sea, south of Lannisport and north of Old Oak. Cornfield and Red Lake are east of Crakehall. There is a large forest in the vicinity of the castle, known for abnormally large boar.

Cleganes Keep is a castle in the Westerlands. It is the seat of House Clegane, a knightly house holding fealty to House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli. The castle is located south-east of Skała Kasterli in the heart of the Westerlands.

Skała Kasterli is the ancestral castle of House Łańnistar. It is located on the western coast of Westeros on a rocky promontory overlooking the Sunset Sea. It overlooks the major city of Lannisport. A major goldmine is located under Skała Kasterli. It is one of the most productive mines in the realm and provides House Łańnistar with their wealth.

The Golden Tooth is a small castle in the Westerlands. It is the seat of House Lefford, a noble house sworn to House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli. It is located near the River Road, in the pass between two mountainous areas, northeast of Skała Kasterli and southwest of Biahučajaraka. It is a strong keep commanding the hill road between the Westerlands and the Račnyje Ziemli. It is generally held that in order to attack the Westerlands from the east, one must take the Tooth to have a secure passage.

Sunhouse, the seat of House Cuy, is a castle in the Miaža, the region controlled by House Tajreł of Vysokisad. The castle is located on the south coast of Westeros, east of the Redwyne Straits and southeast of Oldtown.
Goldengrove is a castle in the Miaža, it is the seat of House Rowan. The castle is located north of Vysokisad near the border of the Westerlands.
Ashford is a settlement in the Miaža, the region controlled by House Tajreł of Vysokisad. It is located on the Cockleswhent river north east of Vysokisad. Ashford Castle is also found here.

Biahučajaraka is the seat of House Talli, the Lord Paramounts of the Trident and the Račnyje Ziemli. It was built as an island fortress by Axel Talli. Prior to the War of the Five Kings, Lord Hoster Talli is the Lord of Biahučajaraka.

Stoney Sept is a large town in the Račnyje Ziemli, the region controlled by House Talli of Biahučajaraka. The town is located south-east of Biahučajaraka, near the border of the Westerlands and close to the source of the Blackwater Rush.

Vysokisad is the seat of House Tajreł and is the regional capital of the Miaža. Located on the banks of the river Mander, Vysokisad sits astride the Roseroad, a major thoroughfare linking Oldtown and Kings Landing. Vysokisad also forms the southern terminus of the the Searoad, which leads to Lannisport. As Kings Landing, Oldtown, and Lannisport are the first, second, and third largest cities in the realm, heavy trade and traffic across a large swath of southern Westeros ultimately passes through Vysokisad.

Oldtown is the second largest and most populated city in the Seven Kingdoms, and by far the oldest major city in Westeros, dating back to the time of the First Men. It is located in the far southwest of the continent, at the mouth of the River Honeywine where it opens into Whispering Sound and the Sunset Sea beyond. The city is also notable as the site of the Citadel, home of the Order of Maesters, as well as the Starry Sept, the former center of the Faith of the Seven in Westeros.

The Arbor is a large island off the southwestern coast of Westeros, separated from the mainland by the Redwyne Straits. It is part of the Miaža and its rulers, House Redwyne, hold fealty to House Tajreł of Vysokisad. House Redwyne controls a large fleet from the Arbor. The Arbor is famous across much of the known world for its high-quality wines.
Kayce is the seat of House Kenning of Kayce in the westerlands.The town is located along the Sunset Sea on a peninsula south of Fair Isle and west of Skała Kasterli.

Lannisport is a large city located on the west coast of Westeros, on the Sunset Sea just south of Skała Kasterli, the seat of House Łańnistar. A cadet branch of the Lannisters rules the city in the name of House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli. It is a bustling seaport.

Moat Cailin is an ancient stronghold of the First Men on the northern edge of the great swamp known as the Neck, in the south of the north. It is less than twenty miles from the headwaters of the Fever River. This castle is one of the norths most important strongholds, though much of it now stands in ruins. It commands the causeway, the safe route for armies to travel through the swamps of the Neck.

Greywater Watch is a castle in the Neck. It is ruled by House Reed, a vassal house holding fealty to House Stark of Minańnie Zimy. It is a castle built upon a crannog, one of the man-made floating islands of the swamps.

Mormont Keep is a castle on Miadźviedžaja Vyspa in the North. It is named for House Mormont, its historical rulers. It is a wood-walled castle with a smoky keep. The Mormonts hall is built of huge logs and is surrounded by an earthen palisade.
Flints Finger is a castle in the North. The structure is south-west of Minańnie Zimy, and lies between the Neck and Nakidka Kraken on the southern edge of Blazewater Bay.
Totava is a Braavosi castle home to House Fregar.
Norrey Keep, seat to House Norrey, is a large castle north of Minańnie Zimy and east of Deepwood Motte.
The Shadow Tower is a castle on the Wall. It is located close to the western end of the Wall. Shadow Tower is one of only three castles on the Wall still manned by the Nights Watch.
Eastwatch by the Sea is a castle and port located at the far eastern end of the Wall, where the Wall drops into an inlet of the Shivering Sea called the Bay of Seals.

Fairmarket is a town in the Račnyje Ziemli, the region controlled by House Talli of Biahučajaraka. The town is located besides the Blue Fork of the Trident and north of the Red Fork, southeast of Wendish Town.

According to legend, House Stark has held Minańnie Zimy for 8,000 years, though it has been considerably expanded upon over the centuries. It was said to have been built by House Starks founder, Bran the Builder, during the Age of Heroes, who was also said to have constructed the Wall and even Storms End. Minańnie Zimy is the capital of the Kingdom of the North and the seat and the ancestral home of the royal House Stark. The city is located alongside the Kingsroad as it makes its way from the Wall to the capital of the Six Kingdoms, Kings Landing, more than a thousand miles to the south. It boast a very large castle located at the center of the city from where the head of House Stark, Rob Stark, rules over his people.

White Harbor is a large city in the North. It is one of the major cities of Westeros, located where the White Knife River flows into the Bite. It is the seat of House , a vassal house holding fealty to House Stark of Minańnie Zimy. White Harbor is the main seaport of the North.
Barrowton is a town in the North, the region ruled by House Stark of Minańnie Zimy, and the seat of House Dustin. Barrowton is located south-west of Minańnie Zimy, in the Barrowlands.

Čorny Zamak is the primary headquarters and redoubt of the Nights Watch. It is located roughly halfway along the length of the Wall on its southern side, at the northern end of the Kingsroad. Founded 8000 BC, it is a dark and chilling home to those unfortunate enough to garrison.
Oros is a small castle in the Valyrian peninsula in southern Essos.
Hesh is a castle located in the Lhazar region of Essos. It is northwest of Lhazosh and west of Kosrak. A trade route from Hesh extends through the Khyzai Pass to Meereen.
Vaes Athjikhari is a castle west of Vaes Dothrak owned by Ko Forzho of the Dothraki Horde.
Vaes Leisi is a castle northwest of Vaes Dothrak. This castle belongs to Ko Moro of the Dothraki Horde.

Mardosh is found upon the northern leg of the River Sarne, leading to the Shivering Sea. To the North is the Sarne Delta along with cities of Saath, Sarys and Morosh. To the south is the city of Kyth.

Rain House is a castle in the Stormlands. It is the seat of House Wylde. The castle is located south-east of Storms End, near the eastern tip of a peninsula extending into the Narrow Sea. It overlooks the southern coastline of Shipbreaker Bay, south of the island of Tarth.
Vaes Efe is a small castle south of Vaes Dothrak.
Cerwin is a midsized castle tucked inside a hillside west of Minańnie Zimy and east of Barrowtow. It is the seat of House Cerwyn of The North.

Hornwood is a castle in the north and the seat of House Hornwood. The castle is located in the Hornwood forest near the northwestern edge of the Sheepshead Hills and the Hornwood lands also neighbor those of House Bolton to the north.

Meereen is the northernmost and greatest of the three great city-states of Slavers Bay, north of Yunkai and Astapor. It is located at the mouth of the Skahazadhan River, which flows from its origins in Lhazar through the mountains separating Meereen and the rest of Slavers Bay from the Red Waste. The Dothraki Sea lies to the north, beyond the river. The wealthiest residents live in pyramids.

Mantarys is a city-state located in the Valyrian peninsula, northeast of the Free City of Volantis and northwest of Slavers Bay. It is situated at the base of the Valyrian peninsula, opposite from the ruins of Old Valyria at the southern end. It is also located at the northeastern tip of the Sea of Sighs, an internal sea on the peninsula. Mantarys is the only overland waystop of any note for travelers and merchants taking the land route from the Free Cities to Slavers Bay. The people of Mantarys are known as Mantari.

Vaes Dothrak is a city in the Dothraki Sea, located near the far northeastern edge of the region. It lies in the shadow of a single, vast peak known by the Dothraki as the Mother of Mountains. The entrance to Vaes Dothrak is marked by two large statues depicting a pair of stallions.

Vaes Diaf is a city in Essos in the Dothraki sea, south of the Kingdom of Sarnor and north of Meereen. It was originally called Hazdahn Mo, but it is now known by its Dothraki language name, Vaes Diaf, meaning City of the Skull.

Kyth is a Sarnori city located in Essos, west of the Bone Mountains, in the centre of the Kingdom of Sarnor. It is notable as an agricultural hub for the Sarnori. Kyth is one of the smallest Sarnori cities, although is still large by Westerosi standards. Much of the city and its surroundings reflect its heralding as an agricultural hub for the Kingdom of Sarnor.

Saath is a city in northern Essos. Saath is a small port city populated by the Tall Men, descendants of the ancient Sarnori. It was the only city of the Kingdom of Sarnor to survive the rise of the Dothraki during the Century of Blood.

The Dreadfort is a fortress in the north and the seat of House Bolton in northeastern Westeros. Located on the banks of the upper Weeping Water, it is southeast of the Lonely Hills and north of the Sheepshead Hills. The Dreadfort is a strong fortress city with high walls and triangular merlons that look like sharp stone teeth. It has thick stone walls and massive towers. The Dreadfort is ill omened, for it is said the Boltons keep torture chambers and a special room where they hang the flayed skins of their enemies, including several Kings in the North.

Deepwood Motte is the seat of House Glover in the north. The wooden motte-and-bailey town lies in the northern wolfswood, east of Sea Dragon Point. East and west of Deepwood are fields of oat and barley. North of the castle Motte lie tidal flats leading to the Bay of Ice. Deepwood is five leagues south of the Bay of Ice and three hundred miles northwest of Minańnie Zimy.

The Twins, sometimes known as the Crossing, is the seat of House Frey in the northern riverlands, located south of the bogs of the Neck and west of the kingsroad. A fortified crossing of the Green Fork of the Trident, the Twins consists of identical castles on each side of the river and a tower in the middle of the bridge which connects them. It is one of the most formidable strongholds of the Seven Kingdoms.

Harroway is a town in the riverlands that sits along the Trident, upriver of the ruby ford. It is the seat of House Harroway. Harroway has a seven-sided sept, a two-story inn, and a stone roundtower. A wide, flat-bottomed boat at the ferry has a dozen oarlocks, a wooden house on its deck, and is decorated with two carved horse heads.

Hearts Home is a town in the Vale of Arryn and is the seat of House Corbray, a vassal house holding fealty to House Arryn of the Eyrie. It is located on the northern shore where a glacial river flows into a narrow bay of the narrow sea. Upriver to the west is Strongsong, while directly north is a forest. Snakewood is located to the northeast along the bay, while the Eyrie is south across a mountain range.
Evenfall Hall is the seat of House Tarth in the stormlands. It is located on the western coast of the island of Tarth along Shipbreaker Bay.

Starfall is a castle in Dorne, the region controlled by House Martell of Sunspear, and the seat of House Dayne. The castle is located in the far west of Dorne, near the border with the Miaža and south of Blackmont.

The city of Aquos Dhaen, glistening like a pearl on the coast of the Azure Sea, invites you to experience its ancient charm and vibrant culture. Its cobbled streets tell tales of knights and dragons, while its grand cathedrals and castles stand as testaments to a bygone era of chivalry and magic. Wander through the bustling marketplace, where merchants from distant lands peddle their wares under the watchful eyes of the city guard. Seek knowledge in the labyrinthine library or unravel the mysteries of the royal court. With its stunning scenery, captivating history, and enchanting atmosphere, Aquos Dhaen offers an escape into a realm where fantasy and reality intertwine.

Nestled amidst rolling hills and lush forests, lies the medieval city of Myrth. Its cobblestone streets, lined with ancient stone buildings and vibrant market stalls, exude an air of enchantment and mystery. From the colossal castle that dominates the skyline to the quaint cottages nestled along the rivers edge, Myrth is a tapestry of architectural wonders. As sunlight dances through the stained-glass windows of the grand cathedral, whispering secrets to the winds, a sense of timeless beauty envelopes the city. Myrth, a sanctuary for wanderers and a haven for dreamers, invites you to delve into its rich history, unravel its hidden legends, and discover the magic that awaits within its ancient walls.

In the tapestry of time, where myth and legend intertwine, there lies the city of Bolozo. Its ancient walls, adorned with intricate carvings, tell tales of a bygone era where knights and dragons roamed the land. The cobblestone streets echo with the footsteps of merchants and minstrels, each one weaving their own story into the rich tapestry of this vibrant city. As the sun sets, casting long shadows over the spires and towers, Bolozo transforms into a place of enchantment, where whispers of magic and wonder fill the air. Prepare to embark on a journey into the heart of fantasy, for within the gates of Bolozo, a world of wonder awaits.

Within the emerald embrace of lush forests and atop the crest of a thousand rolling hills, stands the venerable city of Rhyos. Its fortifications, constructed of granite and arcane magic, are said to shimmer under the moons gaze like a ring of radiant halos. The spires of its ethereal towers pierce the heavens, and the bustling streets below hum with life; merchants peddling their wares, bards spinning tales of old, and the laughter of children playing in the fountains. Yet, beyond the citys walls, whispers of ancient secrets and long-lost treasures in hidden realms linger in the air, beckoning the daring and curious to embark on quests of wonder and peril.

In the realms of the forgotten, where nightmares roam free, lies the city of Tolero Aeskio. Enshrouded in an eternal mist, this forsaken metropolis whispers tales of arcane secrets and ancient curses. Its cobblestone streets bear witness to forgotten battles and untold horrors, while the air itself is thick with the stench of death and decay. Within the towering walls of Tolero Aeskio, dark forces lurk, preying upon the souls of the living for their sinister purposes. Only the brave and foolhardy dare tread within its cursed borders, for the city holds an insatiable hunger for those who cross its path.

Within the emerald embrace of lush forests and atop the crest of a thousand rolling hills, stands the venerable medieval city of Menetragos. Its fortifications, constructed of granite and arcane magic, are said to shimmer under the moons gaze like a ring of radiant halos. The spires of its ethereal towers pierce the heavens, and the bustling streets below hum with life; merchants peddling their wares, bards spinning tales of old, and the laughter of children playing in the fountains. Yet, beyond the citys walls, whispers of ancient secrets and long-lost treasures in hidden realms linger in the air, beckoning the daring and curious to embark on quests of wonder and peril.
Draconys is a city founded by the Valyrian Freehold. Draconys was presumably ruined during the Doom of Valyria, yet it stands rich and glorious in Essos.

Ironrath is a castle situated in the Wolfswood in the North of Westeros. It is the seat of House Forrester. Constructed approximately 1,500 years ago by Cedric Forrester and his triplet sons. Cedric and his sons raised their fortress, an imposing stronghold surrounded by towering ironwood trees, on the edge of the largest ironwood forest in Westeros, placing the Forresters in a position of great strategic advantage. Ironrath is a testament to the strength and endurance of Ironwood.

Highpoint is a stone castle situated in the North of Westeros. It is the seat of House Whitehill. Highpoint was built one thousand years ago, on the massive wealth accumulated by the mass sale of Ironwood from the Whitehill portion. This was one of the greatest castles of stone in the North, bar Minańnie Zimy, the Dreadfort and Torrhens Square. It was a marvel that stood far above the Wooden Keeps that were its neighbors.
Widows Watch is a castle in the North. It is the seat of House Flint. South-east of Minańnie Zimy, Widows Watch is located on a peninsula extending into the northern mouth of the Bite.
Ramsgate is a castle in the North, the region ruled by House Stark of Minańnie Zimy. Ramsgate is located south-east of Minańnie Zimy, near the mouth of the Broken Branch river.
Oldcastle is a castle in the North. It is located on the northern coast of the Bite, south-east of White Harbor, and not far from the mouth of the White Knife river.

Goldgrass is a keep within the walls of Barrowton in The North. The small wooden castle is the seat of House Stout, which is directly sworn to House Dustin of Barrowton. The keep guards the eastern gate into Barrowton, beyond which is the vast rolling plains of the barrowlands. They blazon arms as chevronny russet and gold.

The Nightfort is a castle of the Nights Watch along the Wall. The only one whose steps up the side of the Wall were carved into the ice. It sits between Icemark to the west and Deep Lake to the east. The Nightfort figures in some of Old Nans scariest stories.
Hornfoot lies in the foothills of the Frostfangs, far away from the coasts. The hard rocky terrain in the mountains hardens and blackens the souls of those who reside here.

The Rills is castle in the north ruled by House Ryswell. It is located southeast of the Stony Shore, north of Blazewater Bay, and west of the barrowlands. The castles name suggests it has numerous streams and brooks at and around its borders.
Redfort is the ancient seat of House Redfort in the Vale of Arryn. It is located in the south of the valley. It is southeast of the Eyrie, south of Ironoaks, and north of Wickenden.
Wickenden is a town in the Vale of Arryn, the region controlled by House Arryn of the Eyrie. The town is on the southern coast of the Vale, just across the bay from Maidenpool.

Pinkmaiden Castle is the seat of House Piper in the southwestern riverlands. The castle is located on the Red Fork south of Biahučajaraka, southeast of Acorn Hall, northwest of Stoney Sept, and northeast of Hornvale.
Orkwood is a castle in the Iron Islands. Seat of House Orkwood who blazon their arms as dark green pines strewn closely together on yellow.

The Crag is the stronghold ruled by House Westerling, a vassal of the Lannisters. The castle is run-down and partially ruined, as the Westerlings, though an ancient House with blood of the First Men, have fallen on hard times and can no longer maintain it. The castle is located north-east of Skała Kasterli, overlooking the Sunset Sea on the west coast of Westeros.

Hornvale is the seat of House Brax in the eastern westerlands. It is situated in hilly and mountainous terrain near the headwaters of the Red Fork, south of the Golden Tooth and north of Deep Den and the Goldroad.
Rosby is a castle and the seat of House Rosby, northwest of Blackwater Bay in the crownlands.
Darry is an old, relatively small castle. The seat of House Darry in the riverlands.
Fellwood is a castle in the Stormlands, the region controlled by House Barateon of Storms End. The castle is located north-west of Storms End and south of Kings Landing, at the edge of the Kingswood.
Nakidka Wrath is a large castle in the stormlands on the narrow sea, bordered to the north by Shipbreaker Bay, to the east by Estermont in the narrow sea, and to the south by the Sea of Dorne.

Blackhaven is the seat of House Dondarrion in the southwestern stormlands. Part of the Dornish Marches, it is located in the northern Red Mountains near the Dornish border, north of the Wyl and south of the Cockleswhent.
Banefort is a castle in the Westerlands. It is located south-westernmost point of Ironmans Bay, on the shores of the Sunset Sea and north of the Crag.

Silverhill is a castle in the Westerlands, the region controlled by House Łańnistar of Skała Kasterli. The castle is located in the woodlands south-east of Skała Kasterli and south of Deep Den. It is ruled by House Serrett.

Old Oak is a castle in the Miaža. It is the seat of House Oakheart, a vassal house holding fealty to House Tajreł of Vysokisad. The castle is located in the north-west of the Miaža. It is north west of Vysokisad on the Searoad near the border with the Westerlands.
Bandallon is a castle in the Miaža, the region controlled by House Tajreł of Vysokisad. The castle is located west of Brightwater Keep on the southwestern coast of the continent of Westeros.
Blackmont,a castle in Dorne, is the seat of House Blackmont. It is near the confluence of two rivers which form the Torentine, north of High Hermitage and Starfall in the western Red Mountains.
The Tor is a castle in Dorne, the region of Westeros that is controlled by House Martell of Sunspear. The castle is located in the north of Dorne on the shore of the Sea of Dorne.
Ghost Hill is a castle in Dorne, the region controlled by House Martell of Sunspear. The castle is located in the north-east of Dorne on the shores of the Sea of Dorne.

Sandstone is a castle in Dorne, the region controlled by House Martell of Sunspear, and the seat of House Qorgyle. The castle is located in the south-west of Dorne, between the Brimstone and the Torentine in the deepest part of the Dornish desert. It is west of the Hellholt.

Lhazosh is a city in the Lhazar region of Essos. It is located southeast of Hesh and southwest of Kosrak. A trade route from Lhazosh extends southeast through the red waste to the ruined cities of Vaes Orvik and Vaes Shirosi.
Elyria is a city on an island just off the coast of Essos, in the western part of Slavers Bay. It is west of Tolos and southeast of Mantarys.

Tolos is a city in Essos. The city is located on the northwestern coast of Slavers Bay, in the base of the Valyrian peninsula. It is southeast of Mantarys and southwest of the ruined city Bhorash. The island city of Elyria is west of Tolos.
Grey Gallows is a castle on one of the islands that make up the Stepstones, a series of islands bridging from Essos to Westeros. It lies to the south of Bloodstone.

The impressive Sunstone castle boasts eight strong, square towers that surround the castle. They reach twice the height of the walls and are connected by towering, heavy walls made of dark red stone. Stained glass windows are scattered generously across the walls in a seemingly random pattern, along with same-sized holes for archers and artillery. A large gate with heavy metal doors and strong defenses protects those in need from the treacherous lands outside and its the only easy way in, any other side would be futile. A handful of waterfalls flow into various small rivers and provide the precious farm fields outside the castle with needed water. This castle has clearly stood the test of time and its inhabitants are intend on making sure it stays that way for ages to come.

Tolerrol has eleven slim, square towers form a protective wall on two sides of the castle and are connected by large, vast walls made of bronze stone. Elegant windows are scattered generously around the walls in seeminly perfect symmetry, along with symmetric holes for archers and artillery. A regular gate with enormous metal doors, a regular bridge and archer holes guards the only place with water within these hot, dry lands and its the only easy way in, but easy is very relative here. Remnants of broken siege engines, swords and shields litter the fields outside, a painful reminder of a past war. This castle has clearly stood the test of time and its inhabitants are intend on making sure it stays that way for ages to come.

Gelona boast ten massive, round towers that are scattered in a seemingly random pattern, but have been build for an ideal defense and are connected by large, heavy walls made of dark red stone. Elegant windows are scattered thinly across the walls in a seemingly random pattern, along with asymmetric crenelations for archers and artillery. A regular gate with great metal doors, a draw bridge and hot oil pots offers a warm haven within these cold, isolated lands and its the only way in, at least without taking down the castle walls. Plain fields of a type of grass cover most of the fields outside of the castle, adding to the castles aesthetics. This castle has clearly stood the test of time, the rocks of the walls are aged and vines and plants grow inside the cracks, but this castle will last for ages to come.

Iksa Calo has ten slim, round towers form a protective wall on two sides of the castle and are connected by large, vast walls made of white stone. Elegant windows are desigened around the walls in seeminly perfect symmetry, along with symmetric holes for archers and artillery. A regular gate with enormous metal doors, a large bridge and archer holes guards the only place with water within these hot, dry lands and its the only easy way in, but easy is very relative here. Remnants of broken siege engines, swords and shields litter the fields outside, a painful reminder of a past war. This castle has clearly stood the test of time and its inhabitants are intend on making sure it stays that way for ages to come.

Dull windows are scattered thinly across the walls in an asymmetric pattern, along with overhanging crenelations for archers and artillery. A moderate gate with heavy wooden doors, a draw bridge and a moat guards the last stronghold along this rough shorelineand its the only way in, at least to those unfamiliar with the castle and its surroundings. Dull windows are scattered generously across the walls in a seemingly random pattern, along with same-sized holes for archers and artillery. Wayfarers Rest is the seat of House Vance in the riverlands located in the western part of the region near the Red Fork and the border with the westerlands.
Ashemark is the castle of House Marbrand in the westerlands. Located in hilly terrain, the castle is situated southeast of the Crag, northwest of the Golden Tooth, and north of Sarsfield.

Red Lake is the seat of House Crane in the Miaža. The castle is located on the northeastern shore of a lake of the same name in the northwest of the Miaža, near the regions border with the westerlands. Red Lake is northwest of Goldengrove, northeast of Old Oak, and southeast of Cornfield.

The castle of Driftwood Hall is the seat of House Stane on the Island of Skagos. It is a small keep positioned near the sea, with a small group of villages that dot the area around Driftwood Hall. There is also a small pier jutting out into the shivering sea.
Old Wyk is a castle on one of the islands of the same name that sits on the Iron Islands. Considered the holiest of the isles.
Pebbleton is a castle on the island of Great Wyk. It is governed by House Merlyn, and is the home to roughly seven thousand people, most of whom work in the fishing industry.
Saltcliffe is a castle on one of the islands that make up the Iron Islands. According to a semi-canon source, House Saltcliffe rules the island and is named after it.
Ten Towers is a castle located in Harlaw, the easternmost of the Iron Islands. It serves as the seat of House Harlaw.

Last Hearth is an town of the North, the seat of House Umber, a vassal house holding fealty to House Stark of Minańnie Zimy. It is located south of the Gift, east of the Kingsroad and north of the Last River.

The Frozen Shore is a castle name given to the northern coastline of the Bay of Ice, located beyond the Wall in the far northwest of Westeros. It is separated from the Haunted Forest and the Wall by the mountain range known as the Frostfangs. The Skirling Pass links the Haunted Forest to the Frozen Shore. The Land of Always Winter lies to the north.

Karhold is the seat of House Karstark, a vassal house holding fealty to House Stark of Minańnie Zimy. It is located in the far east of the North, south of the Bay of Seals and inland from the coast of the Shivering Sea. The city was founded by Karlon Stark, a younger son of the then-King in the North after he was rewarded with lands by his father for putting down a rebellion by House Bolton of the Dreadfort.
